input: I have a plan to speak to thee.
target: I have a mind to strike thee ere thou speak'st .

input: Well said, that's right.
target: Well said .

target: And friends with Caesar .

target: Th' art an honest man .

target: Fie upon "But yet." "But yet" is as a jailer to bring forth Some monstrous malefactor .

input: Prithee Poured out the pack of matter to mine ear, The good and bad together.
target: Prithee , friend , Pour out the pack of matter to mine ear , The good and bad together .

target: He's friends with Caesar , In state of health , thou say'st , and , thou say'st , free .

target: For the best turn i' th' bed .

target: The most infectious pestilence upon thee !

target: Thou shalt be whipped with wire and stewed in brine , Smarting in ling'ring pickle !

target: Say 'tis not so , a province I will give thee And make thy fortunes proud .

target: The blow thou hadst Shall make thy peace for moving me to rage , And I will boot thee with what gift beside Thy modesty can beg .

target: He is married ?

target: To punish me for what you make me do Seems much unequal .

target: He's married to Octavia .

target: Oh , that his fault should make a knave of thee , That art not what th' art sure of !

target: The merchandise which thou hast brought from Rome Are all too dear for me .

target: Lie they upon thy hand And be undone by 'em !

target: Good your highness , patience .

target: In praising Antony , I have dispraised Caesar .

target: Many times , madam .

target: I am paid for 't now .

target: O Iras , Charmian !

target: Tis no matter. , Go to the fellow , good Alexas .

target: Let him not leave out The color of her hair .

target: Bring me word how tall she is .

target: Lead me to my chamber .

target: Lord Alexas , sweet Alexas , most anything Alexas , almost most absolute Alexas , where's the soothsayer that you praised so to th' Queen ?

target: Oh that I knew this husband , which , you say , must charge his horns with garlands !

target: I make not , but foresee .

target: Pray , then , foresee me one .

target: Wrinkles forbid !

target: Most meet That first we come to words , and therefore have we Our written purposes before us sent , Which , if thou hast considered , let us know If 'twill tie up thy discontented sword And carry back to Sicily much tall youth That else must perish here .

target: What was 't That moved pale Cassius to conspire ?

target: Take your time .

target: Thou canst not fear us , Pompey , with thy sails .

target: We'll speak with thee at sea .

target: At land , thou know'st How much we do o'ercount thee .

target: At land indeed Thou dost o'ercount me of my father's house , But since the cuckoo builds not for himself , Remain in 't as thou mayst .

input: Tell us how you are taking the offers we have sent you, for this is from the present.
target: Be pleased to tell us , For this is from the present , how you take The offers we have sent you .

input: There's a point to it.
target: There's the point .

input: What it is worth embracing is not something that should be entreated to.
target: Which do not be entreated to , but weigh What it is worth embraced .

target: You have made me offer Of Sicily , Sardinia .

input: To send Measures of wheat to Rome, I must Rid the sea of pirates.
target: And I must Rid all the sea of pirates , then , to send Measures of wheat to Rome .

input: This greeded upon to part with unhacked edges and bear back Our targes.
target: This 'greed upon To part with unhacked edges and bear back Our targes undinted .

target: That's our offer .

target: Know then I came before you here a man prepared To take this offer , but Mark Antony Put me to some impatience .

target: Let me have your hand .

target: I did not think , sir , to have met you here .

target: The beds i' th' East are soft , and thanks to you , That called me timelier than my purpose hither , For I have gained by 't .

input: I know that she won't come to my heart to make my heart her own.
target: Well , I know not What counts harsh Fortune casts upon my face , But in my bosom shall she never come To make my heart her vassal .

target: Well met here .

target: I hope so , Lepidus .

target: That will I , Pompey .

target: No , Antony , take the lot .

target: But , first or last , Your fine Egyptian cookery shall have The fame .

target: I have heard that Julius Caesar Grew fat with feasting there .

target: You have heard much .

target: I have fair meanings , sir .

target: And fair words to them .

target: Then so much have I heard .

target: And I have heard Apollodorus carried , What , I pray you ?

target: How far'st thou , soldier ?

input: Four feasts are toward, for I suppose.
target: Well , And well am like to do , for I perceive , Four feasts are toward .

target: Let me shake thy hand .

input: I didn't dislike thee at all.
target: I never hated thee .

input: I've watched the fight when I've envied the behavior of the person.
target: I have seen thee fight When I have envied thy behavior .

target: Sir , I never loved you much , but I ha' praised ye When you have well deserved ten times as much As I have said you did .

input: Enjoy your plainness.
target: Enjoy thy plainness .

input: I invite you all to join me in the galley.
target: It nothing ill becomes thee. , Aboard my galley I invite you all .

target: Will you lead , lords ?

target: Show 's the way , sir .

input: Come and see it.
target: Come .

target: At sea , I think .

target: We have , sir .

input: You have done well by the water.
target: You have done well by water .

input: You are by land.
target: And you by land .

input: I will praise any man that will praise me, even though it can not be denied what I have done by land.
target: I will praise any man that will praise me , though it can not be denied what I have done by land .

target: Nor what I have done by water .

input: You are by land.
target: And you by land .

input: My land service is denied there.
target: There I deny my land service .

target: But give me your hand , Menas .

target: If our eyes had authority , here they might take two thieves kissing .

target: But there is never a fair woman has a true face .

input: They steal people's hearts.
target: They steal hearts .

target: If he do , sure he can not weep 't back again .

target: Ay , Lepidus .

target: In me 'tis villainy , In thee 't had been good service .

input: It's not my profit that leads mine honor, it's mine honor, it's not my profit.
target: Thou must know , 'Tis not my profit that does lead mine honor ; Mine honor , it .

target: Repent that e'er thy tongue Hath so betrayed thine act .

target: Desist , and drink .

target: This health to Lepidus !

target: Caesar and Antony have ever won More in their officer than person .

target: Who does i' th' wars more than his captain can Becomes his captain's captain ; and ambition , The soldier's virtue , rather makes choice of loss Than gain which darkens him .

target: I could do more to do Antonius good , But 'twould offend him , and in his offense Should my performance perish .

target: Thou hast , Ventidius , that Without the which a soldier and his sword Grants scarce distinction .

target: Thou wilt write to Antony ?

target: Where is he now ?

input: Are the brothers still together?
target: What , are the brothers parted ?

input: He is gone after they dispatched with Pompey.
target: They have dispatched with Pompey ; he is gone .

input: I have instructed the cowardice to run and show their shoulders, and I have fled myself.
target: I have fled myself , and have instructed cowards To run and show their shoulders .

input: Begone friends, begone.
target: Friends , begone .

input: I have resolved a course which has no need of you.
target: I have myself resolved upon a course Which has no need of you .

input: Don't be here.
target: Begone .

input: I blush to look upon that, I followed that.
target: Oh , I followed that I blush to look upon !

input: My hairs do revolt, for the white Reprove the brown for rashness, and they do it for fear and doting.
target: My very hairs do mutiny , for the white Reprove the brown for rashness , and they them For fear and doting .

input: Begone friends, begone.
target: Friends , begone .

input: You will get letters from me to some friends that will sweep your way.
target: You shall Have letters from me to some friends that will Sweep your way for you .

input: Pray for you, look not sad, and don't say anything bad about yourself.
target: Pray you , look not sad , Nor make replies of loathness .

input: Take the hint, which my despair proclaims.
target: Take the hint Which my despair proclaims .

input: Let that be left and then we can move on.
target: Let that be left Which leaves itself .

input: To the seaside straightway!
target: To the seaside straightway !

input: I will give you the ship and the treasure.

target: Leave me , I pray , a little .

input: I have lost command, so please pray for me, I need you to do so.
target: Pray you now , Nay , do so , for indeed I have lost command .

input: What else is there?
target: Why , what else ?

input: Allow me to sit down.
target: Let me sit down .

input: Oh, fie, fie, fie!
target: Oh , fie , fie , fie !

input: The lady is referred to as Madame!
target: Madam !

input: Good Empress, good madam.
target: Madam , O good Empress !

input: The Queen, my lord, the Queen.
target: The Queen , my lord , the Queen .

input: Speak to him, go to him, madam.
target: Go to him , madam , speak to him .

input: He is notqualitied with shame.
target: He is unqualitied with very shame .

input: Well then, keep me going.
target: Well then , sustain me .

input: Sir, arise, most noble sir.
target: Most noble sir , arise .

input: The Queen is approaching.
target: The Queen approaches .

input: Her head is declining, and death will seize her, but your comfort makes the rescue possible.
target: Her head's declined , and death will seize her but Your comfort makes the rescue .

input: I have offended reputation, a most un noble swerving.
target: I have offended reputation , A most unnoble swerving .

input: The queen is Sir.
target: Sir , the Queen .

input: Is it possible that she has led me to Egypt?
target: Oh , whither hast thou led me , Egypt ?

target: O my lord , my lord , Forgive my fearful sails !

input: I didn't think you would have followed me.
target: I little thought You would have followed .

input: My heart was to the rudder that was tied by the strings, and I should be towed after.
target: Egypt , thou knew'st too well My heart was to thy rudder tied by th' strings , And thou shouldst tow me after .

target: O'er my spirit Thy full supremacy thou knew'st , and that Thy beck might from the bidding of the gods Command me .

input: My pardon, my pardon!
target: Oh , my pardon !

input: The young man must send humble treaties, dodge and palter in the shifts of lowness, who with half the world played as I pleased, Making and marring fortunes.
target: Now I must To the young man send humble treaties , dodge And palter in the shifts of lowness , who With half the bulk o' th' world played as I pleased , Making and marring fortunes .

input: You were aware that my sword was made weak by my affection and that it would Obey it on all cause.
target: You did know How much you were my conqueror , and that My sword , made weak by my affection , would Obey it on all cause .

input: I tell you to fall not a tear.
target: Fall not a tear , I say .

input: All that is won and lost is what one of them rates.
target: One of them rates All that is won and lost .

target: Give me a kiss .

input: The schoolmaster was sent to repay me.
target: Even this repays me. , We sent our schoolmaster .

target: Know you him ?

target: Such as I am , I come from Antony .

target: I was of late as petty to his ends As is the morn-dew on the myrtle leaf To his grand sea .

input: Be true to yourself.
target: Be 't so .

input: Don't waste your time at the office.
target: Declare thine office .

input: He salutes thee, and requires to live in Egypt, which not granted, he reduces his requests, and to thee sues to let him breathe between the heavens and earth.
target: Lord of his fortunes he salutes thee , and Requires to live in Egypt ; which not granted , He lessens his requests , and to thee sues To let him breathe between the heavens and earth A private man in Athens .

input: This was for him.
target: This for him .

input: Next, Cleopatra admits her greatness, and of thee craves The circle of the Ptolemies for her heirs.
target: Next , Cleopatra does confess thy greatness , Submits her to thy might , and of thee craves The circle of the Ptolemies for her heirs , Now hazarded to thy grace .

input: I don't have any ears to Antony's request.
target: For Antony , I have no ears to his request .

target: The Queen Of audience nor desire shall fail , so she From Egypt drive her all-disgraced friend Or take his life there .

target: This if she perform , She shall not sue unheard .

input: To both of them.
target: So to them both .

input: Fortune will pursue thee.
target: Fortune pursue thee !

input: He should be brought through the bands.
target: Bring him through the bands .

input: Caesar, I am going.
target: Caesar , I go .

input: Observe how Antony becomes his flaw, and what he does speaks in every power that moves.
target: Observe how Antony becomes his flaw , And what thou think'st his very action speaks In every power that moves .

target: Caesar , I shall .

input: What are we going to do, Enobarbus?
target: What shall we do , Enobarbus ?

target: Is Antony or we in fault for this ?

target: Antony only , that would make his will Lord of his reason .

input: Why should he be following?
target: Why should he follow ?

input: The itch of his affection should not have nicked his captainship when half of the world opposed it.
target: The itch of his affection should not then Have nicked his captainship at such a point When half to half the world opposed , he being The mered question .

input: It was a shame that his loss was your flying flags and leave his navy looking at them.
target: Twas a shame no less Than was his loss , to course your flying flags And leave his navy gazing .

input: Peace and Prithee.
target: Prithee , peace .

input: Is that his answer, sir?
target: Is that his answer ?

input: Ay, my lord.
target: Ay , my lord .

input: The Queen will have courtesy, so she will yield us up.
target: The Queen shall then have courtesy , so she Will yield us up ?

input: He says that.
target: He says so .

input: Let her know that he will fulfill her wishes with principalities.
target: Let her know 't. , And he will fill thy wishes to the brim With principalities .

input: My lord, that head, my lord?
target: That head , my lord ?

input: The messenger from Caesar was a man.
target: A messenger from Caesar .

input: There is no more ceremony.
target: What , no more ceremony ?

input: My women, Against the rose may they stop their nose, That kneeled unto the buds, sir.
target: See , my women , Against the blown rose may they stop their nose , That kneeled unto the buds. , Admit him , sir .

target: At your noble pleasure .

target: He stays upon your will .

target: What are you ?

target: Fulvia thy wife is dead .

target: Where died she ?

target: In Sicyon .

target: Her length of sickness , with what else more serious Importeth thee to know , this bears .

target: Forbear me .

input: Caesar's will is not known.
target: Caesar's will ?

target: Hear it apart .

target: None but friends .

target: Say boldly .

target: So haply are they friends to Antony .

target: He needs as many , sir , as Caesar has , Or needs not us .

target: If Caesar please , our master Will leap to be his friend .

target: For us , you know Whose he is we are , and that is Caesar's .

input: Caesar said that he should not consider what case he stands in, further than Caesar.
target: So. , Thus then , thou most renowned : Caesar entreats Not to consider in what case thou stand'st , Further than he is Caesar .

target: He knows that you embrace not Antony As you did love , but as you feared him .

target: For he partly begs To be desired to give .

target: It much would please him That of his fortunes you should make a staff To lean upon .

target: What's your name ?

target: My name is Thidias .

target: Most kind messenger , Say to great Caesar this in deputation : I kiss his conqu'ring hand .

target: Tell him I am prompt To lay my crown at 's feet , and there to kneel .

target: By Jove that thunders !

target: Take hence this jack and whip him .

target: Moon and stars !

target: Were 't twenty of the greatest tributaries That do acknowledge Caesar , should I find them So saucy with the hand of she here , what's her name Since she was Cleopatra ?

target: Whip him , fellows , Till like a boy , you see him cringe his face And whine aloud for mercy .

target: This jack of Caesar's shall Bear us an errand to him .

input: Is 't coming to this?
target: Oh , is 't come to this ?

input: I found you to be a bit cold upon Dead Caesar's trencher.
target: I found you as a morsel cold upon Dead Caesar's trencher .

input: Is it possible that he hated him?
target: Cried he ?

target: He did ask favor .

target: Alack , our terrene moon is now eclipsed , And it portends alone the fall of Antony .

target: To flatter Caesar , would you mingle eyes With one that ties his points ?

target: Not know me yet ?

target: Coldhearted toward me ?

target: As it determines , so Dissolve my life !

target: I am satisfied .

target: Caesar sits down in Alexandria , where I will oppose his fate .

target: Dost thou hear , lady ?

target: It is my birthday .

target: We will yet do well .

input: Do this.

input: We'll speak to them, and tonight I'll force The wine to look through their scars.
target: We'll speak to them , and tonight I'll force The wine peep through their scars. , Come on , my Queen , There's sap in 't yet .

target: When valor preys on reason , It eats the sword it fights with .

target: He calls me "boy" and chides as he had power To beat me out of Egypt .

target: Let the old ruffian know I have many other ways to die , meantime Laugh at his challenge .

input: Make boot of his distraction, give him no breath, but do it now.
target: Give him no breath , but now Make boot of his distraction .

input: Good guard for itself because of never anger.
target: Never anger Made good guard for itself .

input: Let our heads know that tomorrow is the last day of many battles.
target: Let our best heads Know that tomorrow the last of many battles We mean to fight .

input: There are some people within our files that served Mark Antony but were late.
target: Within our files there are , Of those that served Mark Antony but late , Enough to fetch him in .

target: See it done And feast the army .

input: They have earned the waste, and we have a store to do it.
target: We have store to do 't , And they have earned the waste .

target: Poor Antony !

target: What's your pleasure , sir ?

target: If they suffer our departure , death's the word .

target: I must be gone .

input: Allow women to die under a compelling circumstance.
target: Under a compelling occasion , let women die .

target: It were pity to cast them away for nothing , though between them and a great cause they should be esteemed nothing .

target: Cleopatra , catching but the least noise of this , dies instantly .

target: I have seen her die twenty times upon far poorer moment .

input: I think that she has such a celerity in dying that she commits some loving act upon herself.
target: I do think there is mettle in death , which commits some loving act upon her , she hath such a celerity in dying .

target: She is cunning past man's thought .

input: She cannot be called her winds and waters sigh and tears.
target: We can not call her winds and waters sighs and tears .

target: He will not fight with me , Domitius ?

target: No .

input: Being twenty times of better fortune, he thinks, he is twenty men to one.
target: He thinks , being twenty times of better fortune , He is twenty men to one .

input: I'll fight by sea and land tomorrow.
target: Tomorrow , soldier , By sea and land I'll fight .

input: Shall make my honor live again, or I will live and die in the blood.
target: Or I will live Or bathe my dying honor in the blood Shall make it live again .

input: I will cry and strike, "Take all."
target: I'll strike and cry , "Take all." Well said .

target: Come on !

target: Call forth my household servants .

target: You have served me well , And kings have been your fellows .

target: Well , my good fellows , wait on me tonight .

target: Know , my hearts , I hope well of tomorrow , and will lead you Where rather I'll expect victorious life Than death and honor .

target: Tomorrow is the day .

target: And you .

target: Content .

target: Sleep a little .

Thou art The armorer of my heart .

target: The morn is fair .

target: Good morrow , General .

target: Peace !

input: Antony's triumph on himself was not Caesar's.
target: Not Caesar's valor hath o'erthrown Antony , But Antony's hath triumphed on itself .

input: So it should be, that Antony should conquer him, but woe 'tis so.
target: So it should be , that none but Antony Should conquer Antony , but woe 'tis so !

input: This dotage of our general's O'erflows is the measure.
target: Nay , but this dotage of our general's O'erflows the measure .

input: The files and musters of the war have glowed like plated Mars, now bend, and turn the office and devotion of their view upon a tawny front.
target: Those his goodly eyes , That o'er the files and musters of the war Have glowed like plated Mars , now bend , now turn The office and devotion of their view Upon a tawny front .

input: The captain's heart burst in the fights and he lost his temper and became the bellows and the fan to cool off the gypsies.
target: His captain's heart , Which in the scuffles of great fights hath burst The buckles on his breast , reneges all temper And is become the bellows and the fan To cool a gypsy's lust .

input: Look at where they come.
target: Look where they come .

input: You will see that the triple pillar of the world turned into a strumpet's fool when you take but good note.
target: Take but good note , and you shall see in him The triple pillar of the world transformed Into a strumpet's fool .

input: It is time to see and behold.
target: Behold and see .

input: Tell me how much it will cost if it is love.
target: If it be love indeed , tell me how much .

input: There's a weakness in the love that can be overcome.
target: There's beggary in the love that can be reckoned .

input: How far to be beloved will be set by me.
target: I'll set a bourn how far to be beloved .

input: Is it possible that he needs to find out new heaven and new earth.
target: Then must thou needs find out new heaven , new earth .

input: My good lord, I received news from Rome.
target: News , my good lord , from Rome .

input: I am dying in Egypt, I am dying.
target: I am dying , Egypt , dying .

input: Until many thousand kisses the poor last, I lay my lips upon them.
target: Only I here importune death awhile , until Of many thousand kisses the poor last I lay upon thy lips .

input: Dear my lord, I dare not, but I will be taken, Lest I be taken.
target: I dare not , dear , Dear my lord , pardon , I dare not , Lest I be taken .

input: Not the imperious show of the full-fortuned Caesar will be brooches with me.
target: Not th' imperious show Of the full-fortuned Caesar ever shall Be brooched with me .

input: I am safe if knife, drugs, serpents, sting, or operation are involved.
target: If knife , drugs , serpents , have Edge , sting , or operation , I am safe .

input: Your wife, with her modest eyes, will no longer acquire honor Demuring upon me.
target: Your wife Octavia , with her modest eyes And still conclusion , shall acquire no honor Demuring upon me .

input: Good friends and assist.
target: Assist , good friends .

input: I am gone, quick or not.
target: Oh , quick , or I am gone .

input: Here's a sport indeed.
target: Here's sport indeed !

input: How heavy does my lord weigh?
target: How heavy weighs my lord !

input: The strong-winged Mercury should fetch thee up and set thee up by Jove's side if I had great Juno's power.
target: Had I great Juno's power , The strong-winged Mercury should fetch thee up And set thee by Jove's side .

input: And welcome, welcome, welcome!
target: And welcome , welcome !

input: Don't die when you've been alive.
target: Die when thou hast lived .

input: I would wear them out if my lips were that power.
target: Had my lips that power , Thus would I wear them out .

input: A very heavy sight.
target: A heavy sight !

input: I am dying in Egypt, I am dying.
target: I am dying , Egypt , dying .

input: Give me a glass of wine and let me speak.
target: Give me some wine and let me speak a little .

input: None about Caesar is my resolution and my hands.
target: My resolution and my hands I'll trust , None about Caesar .

input: My spirit is moving now.
target: Now my spirit is going .

input: I can no longer do that.
target: I can no more .

input: Noblest of men, I'm dying.
target: Noblest of men , woo't die ?

input: Do you have any care for me?
target: Hast thou no care of me ?

input: In this dull world, which in absence is no better than a sty, shall I abide?
target: Shall I abide In this dull world , which in thy absence is No better than a sty ?

input: My lord, my lord.
target: My lord !

input: The garlands of the war were withered.
target: Oh , withered is the garland of the war .

input: The pole of the soldier is falling.
target: The soldier's pole is fall'n !

input: Young boys and girls are at a higher level than men.
target: Young boys and girls Are level now with men .

input: The odds are gone, and there is nothing left remarkable beneath the visiting moon.
target: The odds is gone , And there is nothing left remarkable Beneath the visiting moon .

input: She's dead as well, our leader.
target: She's dead too , our sovereign .

input: The lady is called Lady.
target: Lady !

input: The lady is referred to as Madame!
target: Madam !

input: O madam, madam, madam.
target: O madam , madam , madam !

input: The queen of Egypt is the empress.
target: Royal Egypt , Empress !

input: Iras has peace, peace, peace.
target: Peace , peace , Iras .

input: The maid that milks does the meanest chares, and e'en a woman, and commanded.
target: No more but e'en a woman , and commanded By such poor passion as the maid that milks And does the meanest chares .

input: It's all but naught.
target: All's but naught .

input: What do you think about women?
target: How do you , women ?

input: Good cheer, what, what!
target: What , what , good cheer !

input: Charmian, why, how now.
target: Why , how now , Charmian ?

input: My girls are noble!
target: My noble girls !

input: Take heart sirs, good sirs.
target: Good sirs , take heart .

input: We'll bury him, and then, what's brave, what's noble, let's do it after the high Roman fashion, and make death proud to take us.
target: We'll bury him , and then , what's brave , what's noble , Let's do 't after the high Roman fashion And make death proud to take us .

input: Come and go away.
target: Come , away .

input: The case of that huge spirit is now cold.
target: This case of that huge spirit now is cold .

input: Ah, women, women.
target: Ah , women , women !

input: Come and see it.
target: Come .

input: We don't have a friend, but resolution and the briefest end.
target: We have no friend But resolution , and the briefest end .

input: Go to him and try to get him to give up.
target: Go to him , Dolabella , bid him yield .

input: He mocks the pauses that he makes because he is so frustrated.
target: Being so frustrate , tell him , he mocks The pauses that he makes .

input: I will. Caesar, I shall.
target: Caesar , I shall .

input: Where is that located?
target: Wherefore is that ?

input: What art do we see that appears to us?
target: And what art thou that dar'st Appear thus to us ?

input: I am named after a person.
target: I am called Dercetus .

input: I served Mark Antony, who was the best to be served.
target: Mark Antony I served , who best was worthy Best to be served .

input: He stood up and spoke, and I wore my life to spend time with his detractors.
target: Whilst he stood up and spoke , He was my master , and I wore my life To spend upon his haters .

input: I will yield thee up my life if you don't.
target: If thou pleasest not , I yield thee up my life .

input: What is the meaning of 't he say'st?
target: What is 't thou say'st ?

input: Antony is dead, I said to Caesar.
target: I say , O Caesar , Antony is dead .

input: A greater crack should be made by the breaking of so great a thing.
target: The breaking of so great a thing should make A greater crack .

input: The world should have shook lions into civil streets and citizens into their dens.
target: The round world Should have shook lions into civil streets And citizens to their dens .

input: The death of Antony is not a big deal.
target: The death of Antony Is not a single doom .

input: A moiety of the world was the name that was given.
target: In the name lay A moiety of the world .

input: Now my dearest Queen, please stand farther from me.
target: Now , my dearest Queen , Pray you , stand farther from me .

input: The matter is what?
target: What's the matter ?

input: There's some good news, I know by that eye.
target: I know by that same eye there's some good news .

input: The married woman is wondering what you may do.
target: What , says the married woman you may go ?

input: Would she have allowed you to come if she had not given you leave?
target: Would she had never given you leave to come !

input: Let her not say "I will keep you here"
target: Let her not say 'tis I that keep you here .

input: I don't have the power to do anything.
target: I have no power upon you .

input: You are with her.
target: Hers you are .

input: The gods know that the queen was betrayed by the gods.
target: The gods best know , Oh never was there queen So mightily betrayed !

input: The treasons were planted at the first.
target: Yet at the first I saw the treasons planted .

input: Who have been false to Fulvia, Cleopatra, and why should I think you can be mine.
target: Cleopatra , Why should I think you can be mine , and true , Though you in swearing shake the throned gods , Who have been false to Fulvia ?

input: To be entangled with those mouth-made vows, which break themselves in swearing.
target: Riotous madness , To be entangled with those mouth-made vows Which break themselves in swearing !

input: When you sued staying, it was the right time to say something.
target: When you sued staying , Then was the time for words .

input: No going at that time.
target: No going then !

input: Our lips and eyes were filled with eternal bliss, our brows were bent, but our parts were not so poor.
target: Eternity was in our lips and eyes , Bliss in our brows' bent , none our parts so poor But was a race of heaven .

input: Art turned into the greatest liar when he said they were still the greatest soldier of the world.
target: They are so still , Or thou , the greatest soldier of the world , Art turned the greatest liar .

input: This is the sword he has.
target: This is his sword .

input: He had a wound that I robbed.
target: I robbed his wound of it .

input: It was stained with his most noble blood.
target: Behold it stained With his most noble blood .

input: Look you, sad friends, The gods rebuke me, but it is tidings that will wash the eyes of the kings.
target: Look you , sad friends , The gods rebuke me , but it is tidings To wash the eyes of kings .

input: Waged is equal with him in taints and honors.
target: His taints and honors Waged equal with him .

input: You gods will give us some faults to make us men, but a rarer spirit never did steer humanity.
target: A rarer spirit never Did steer humanity , but you gods will give us Some faults to make us men .

input: Caesar is touched by someone.
target: Caesar is touched .

input: I have shown to thee that a declining day is possible.
target: I must perforce Have shown to thee such a declining day , Or look on thine .

input: Good friends, listen to me.
target: Hear me , good friends ,

input: At some meeter season, I will let you know.
target: But I will tell you at some meeter season .

input: The business of this man is not visible to him.
target: The business of this man looks out of him .

input: We'll listen to what he has to say.
target: We'll hear him what he says .

input: She should be bid have a good heart.
target: Bid her have good heart .

input: She will know of us by some of ours, how honorable and how kindly we will be for her, for Caesar can not live to be ungentle.
target: She soon shall know of us , by some of ours , How honorable and how kindly we Determine for her , for Caesar can not live To be ungentle .

input: The gods are caretakers of thee.
target: So the gods preserve thee !

input: "Come hither, Proculeius"
target: Come hither , Proculeius .

input: Go and tell her that she was purposed no shame.
target: Go and say We purpose her no shame .

input: Bring us what she says and how you find her, with your speediest.
target: Go , And with your speediest bring us what she says And how you find of her .

input: I will. Caesar, I shall.
target: Caesar , I shall .

input: Go you along with me.
target: Gallus , go you along .

input: To second Proculeius, where is Dolabella?
target: Where's Dolabella , To second Proculeius ?

input: There is a dog called Dolabella.
target: Dolabella !

input: Let him be alone, for I remember how he's been employed.
target: Let him alone , for I remember now How he's employed .

input: He is going to be ready in time.
target: He shall in time be ready .

input: Go with me and see what I can show you.
target: Go with me and see What I can show in this .

input: To be Caesar is not very impressive.
target: Tis paltry to be Caesar .

input: He's a minister of Fortune's will, not being Fortune.
target: Not being Fortune , he's but Fortune's knave , A minister of her will .

input: Caesar sent a greeting to the Queen of Egypt, and offered to study what fair demands should be in order to grant her.
target: Caesar sends greeting to the Queen of Egypt , And bids thee study on what fair demands Thou mean'st to have him grant thee .

input: What is the name of this person?
target: What's thy name ?

input: I am named Proculeius.
target: My name is Proculeius .

input: Antony did not tell me of you, but I do not want to be deceived.
target: Antony Did tell me of you , bade me trust you , but I do not greatly care to be deceived , That have no use for trusting .

input: To keep decorum, you must tell your master that he must have a queen and that he must beg.
target: If your master Would have a queen his beggar , you must tell him , That majesty , to keep decorum , must No less beg than a kingdom .

input: He will give me so much of my own as I will kneel to him with thanks if he pleases.
target: If he please To give me conquered Egypt for my son , He gives me so much of mine own as I Will kneel to him with thanks .

input: Be of good cheer, be of good cheer.
target: Be of good cheer .

input: You are fall'n into a princely hand.
target: You're fall'n into a princely hand .

input: There is nothing to fear.
target: Fear nothing .

input: Let me report to him, and you will find a conqueror that will pray for kindness, where he for grace is kneeled.
target: Let me report to him Your sweet dependency , and you shall find A conqueror that will pray in aid for kindness Where he for grace is kneeled to .

input: Tell him that I am his fortune's vassal, and that I will send him the greatness he has got.
target: Pray you , tell him I am his fortune's vassal , and I send him The greatness he has got .

input: I would look him in the face if I learned a doctrine of obedientness.
target: I hourly learn A doctrine of obedience , and would gladly Look him i' th' face .

input: I will report this to you, dear lady.
target: This I'll report , dear lady .

input: You can see how easily she will be surprised.
target: You see how easily she may be surprised .

input: The queen is a Royal Queen.
target: Royal Queen !

input: O Cleopatra!
target: O Cleopatra !

input: Hold, worthy lady, hold!
target: Hold , worthy lady , hold !

input: Do not think that you are wrong, who are in this Relieved but not betrayed.
target: Do not yourself such wrong , who are in this Relieved but not betrayed .

input: What happens to our dogs when they die too?
target: What , of death too , That rids our dogs of languish ?

input: Cleopatra, don't ruin my master's bounty by your own actions.
target: Cleopatra , Do not abuse my master's bounty by Th' undoing of yourself .

input: Let the world see His nobleness, which your death will never allow to happen.
target: Let the world see His nobleness well acted , which your death Will never let come forth .

input: Where art and death are located.
target: Where art thou , Death ?

input: Come hither, come.
target: Come hither , come !

input: Come and take a queen that is worth a lot of babes and beggars.
target: Come , come and take a queen Worth many babes and beggars !

input: Oh, temperance, lady!
target: Oh , temperance , lady !

input: I'll ruin this mortal house if Caesar doesn't do what he can.
target: This mortal house I'll ruin , Do Caesar what he can .

input: I will not wait for you at your master's court, nor will I be reprimanded with the sober eye of dull Octavia.
target: Know , sir , that I Will not wait pinioned at your master's court , Nor once be chastised with the sober eye Of dull Octavia .

input: Is it possible that they will hoist me up and show me the shouting varletry of Rome?
target: Shall they hoist me up And show me to the shouting varletry Of censuring Rome ?

input: Rather a ditch in Egypt, be gentle grave unto me.
target: Rather a ditch in Egypt Be gentle grave unto me .

input: Lay me stark naked on the mud and let the waterflies blow me away.
target: Rather on Nilus' mud Lay me stark naked and let the waterflies Blow me into abhorring .

input: Hang me up in chains rather than make my country's high pyramid.
target: Rather make My country's high pyramides my gibbet And hang me up in chains !

input: You don't end these thoughts of horror until you find cause in Caesar.
target: You do extend These thoughts of horror further than you shall Find cause in Caesar .

input: What have you done to your master Caesar? He has sent for thee.
target: Proculeius , What thou hast done thy master Caesar knows , And he hath sent for thee .

input: I will take the Queen to my guard.
target: For the Queen , I'll take her to my guard .

input: It will content me the best.
target: So , Dolabella , It shall content me best .

input: Don't be aggressive to her.
target: Be gentle to her .

input: You have heard of me, most noble Empress?
target: Most noble Empress , you have heard of me ?

input: I can not tell.
target: I can not tell .

input: When boys or women tell their dreams, you laugh.
target: You laugh when boys or women tell their dreams .

input: Is 't not your trick'.
target: Is 't not your trick ?

input: I don't understand, Madame.
target: I understand not , madam .

input: I had a dream that Antony was the emperor.
target: I dreamt there was an emperor Antony .

input: I might see another man, but such another sleep.
target: Oh , such another sleep , that I might see But such another man !

input: His arm was Crested the World.
target: His reared arm Crested the world .

input: For his bounty, there was no winter and an autumn that grew the more by reaping.
target: For his bounty , There was no winter in 't , an autumn 'twas That grew the more by reaping .

input: His crowns and crownets were walked in his livery.
target: In his livery Walked crowns and crownets .

input: Plates dropped from his pocket as he walked.
target: Realms and islands were As plates dropped from his pocket .

input: Think you could be such a man, as I dreamt of?
target: Cleopatra , Think you there was or might be such a man As this I dreamt of ?

input: No madam, gentle.
target: Gentle madam , no .

input: You lie in wait for the gods to hear you.
target: You lie up to the hearing of the gods .

input: An Antony were nature's piece that wasgainst fancy, Condemning shadows quite.
target: Nature wants stuff To vie strange forms with fancy , yet t' imagine An Antony were nature's piece 'gainst fancy , Condemning shadows quite .

input: Good madam, hear me, I need you.
target: Hear me , good madam .

input: Your loss is as you are, great, and you have to deal with it.
target: Your loss is as yourself , great , and you bear it As answering to the weight .

input: I would never pursue success, but I do feel a grief that smites my very heart, by the rebound of yours.
target: Would I might never O'ertake pursued success , but I do feel , By the rebound of yours , a grief that smites My very heart at root .

input: I would like to say thank you, sir.
target: I thank you , sir .

input: Do you know what Caesar means to do with me.
target: Know you what Caesar means to do with me ?

input: I don't want you to know what I would you know.
target: I am loath to tell you what I would you knew .

input: You must rise, you will not kneel.
target: Arise , you shall not kneel .

input: I am praying that you will rise.
target: I pray you , rise .

input: The gods are going to have it.
target: Sir , the gods Will have it thus .

input: Take to you without hard thoughts.
target: Take to you no hard thoughts .

input: I'll be taking my leave.
target: I'll take my leave .

input: And may go through the entire world.
target: And may , through all the world !

input: Hang in what place you please, we, your scutcheons and your signs of conquest, are yours.
target: Tis yours , and we , Your scutcheons and your signs of conquest , shall Hang in what place you please .

input: My good lord, I am here.
target: Here , my good lord .

input: How are you now, lady?
target: How now , lady ?

input: I would have the same amount of inches as him.
target: I would I had thy inches .

input: Thou should know that there was a heart in Egypt.
target: Thou shouldst know There were a heart in Egypt .

input: The strong necessity of time commands our services for a while, but my full heart is still in use with you.
target: Hear me , Queen : The strong necessity of time commands Our services awhile , but my full heart Remains in use with you .

input: Our Italy is a shining example of civil swords.
target: Our Italy Shines o'er with civil swords .

input: Sextus Pompeius makes his way to the port of Rome.
target: Sextus Pompeius Makes his approaches to the port of Rome .

input: Is Fulvia's death is my more particular, and that most with you should safe my going.
target: My more particular , And that which most with you should safe my going , Is Fulvia's death .

input: Is Fulvia going to die?
target: Can Fulvia die ?

input: She is dead, my Queen.
target: She's dead , my Queen .

input: You will advise me in all for Cleopatra.
target: You shall advise me in all for Cleopatra .

input: This is the brief of money, plate, and jewels that I have.
target: This is the brief of money , plate , and jewels I am possessed of .

input: It's exactly valued, not things that are unimportant.
target: Tis exactly valued , Not petty things admitted .

input: Where are Seleucus?
target: Where's Seleucus ?

input: Here, my friend.
target: Here , madam .

input: This is the person that I have in charge of my finances.
target: This is my treasurer .

input: Let him speak, my lord, upon his peril, that I have reserved to myself nothing.
target: Let him speak , my lord , Upon his peril , that I have reserved To myself nothing .

input: I had to keep my lips sealed because I was going to speak that which is not.
target: Madam , I had rather seal my lips Than to my peril speak that which is not .

input: What have I kept away from?
target: What have I kept back ?

input: Enough to purchase what you have made known.
target: Enough to purchase what you have made known .

input: Cleopatra did not blush.
target: Nay , blush not , Cleopatra .

input: You can see, Caesar.
target: See , Caesar !

input: Oh my gosh, how pomp is followed!
target: Oh , behold How pomp is followed !

input: This Seleucus makes me wild because of their insensitivity.
target: The ingratitude of this Seleucus does Even make me wild .

input: Thou shalt return, I warrant thee.
target: Thou shalt Go back , I warrant thee !

input: I'll catch their eyes, even though they had wings.
target: But I'll catch thine eyes , Though they had wings .

input: It's rarely base!
target: Oh , rarely base !

input: Not what you have reserved or what you acknowledged, put we I' th' roll of conquest.
target: Cleopatra , Not what you have reserved nor what acknowledged Put we i' th' roll of conquest .

input: Continue to be yours, still.
target: Still be 't yours .

input: You can bestow it at your pleasure, and believe Caesar's no merchant, to make prize with you of things that merchants sold.
target: Bestow it at your pleasure , and believe Caesar's no merchant , to make prize with you Of things that merchants sold .

input: Therefore be cheered.
target: Therefore be cheered .

input: No, dear Queen, for we intend to dispose of you as yourself will give us counsel.
target: No , dear Queen , For we intend so to dispose you as Yourself shall give us counsel .

input: Feed and sleep are important things to do.
target: Feed and sleep .

input: We remain your friend because of our care and pity for you.
target: Our care and pity is so much upon you That we remain your friend .

input: And so, adieu.
target: And so , adieu .

input: My lord and my master are together.
target: My master , and my lord !

input: Not so, that's right.
target: Not so .

input: Adieu, Adieu.
target: Adieu .

input: Charmian, but, hark thee.
target: But , hark thee , Charmian .

input: Good lady Finish, good lady.
target: Finish , good lady .

input: Madame, I will.
target: Madam , I will .

input: The Queen is not located.
target: Where's the Queen ?

input: Sir, behold.
target: Behold , sir .

input: There is a dog called Dolabella.
target: Dolabella !

input: You should make your best use of this.
target: Make your best use of this .

input: I have fulfilled my promise and performed Your pleasure.
target: I have performed Your pleasure and my promise .

input: I will remain your debtor, please.
target: Dolabella , I shall remain your debtor .

input: Your servant is me.
target: I your servant .

input: Good Queen, good adieu.
target: Adieu , good Queen .

input: I need to attend on Caesar.
target: I must attend on Caesar .

input: Thank you farewell and thanks again.
target: Farewell , and thanks .

input: Iras, what do you think about the situation?
target: Now , Iras , what think'st thou ?

input: In Rome, as well as I, an Egyptian puppet will be shown.
target: Thou an Egyptian puppet shalt be shown In Rome , as well as I .

input: The mechanic slaves with greasy aprons, rules, and hammers will lift us up to the view.
target: Mechanic slaves With greasy aprons , rules , and hammers shall Uplift us to the view .

input: The gods do not allow it.
target: The gods forbid !

input: Iras, it's most certain, Nay.
target: Nay , 'tis most certain , Iras .

input: Oh, the good gods.
target: Oh , the good gods !

input: That is certain.
target: Nay , that's certain .

input: I will never see 't.
target: I'll never see 't !

input: I am certain that my nails are stronger than mine eyes.
target: For I am sure mine nails Are stronger than mine eyes .

input: That's the way to fool their preparation and to conquer their most absurd intentions.
target: Why , that's the way To fool their preparation and to conquer Their most absurd intents .

input: Now, Charmian.
target: Now , Charmian !

input: Show my women how to act like a queen.
target: Show me , my women , like a queen .

input: My best clothes should be fetch.
target: Go fetch My best attires .

input: Where is this noise located?
target: Wherefore's this noise ?

input: There is a rural fellow that will not be denied of his presence.
target: Here is a rural fellow That will not be denied your Highness' presence .

input: He brings you some figs.
target: He brings you figs .

input: Allow him to come in.
target: Let him come in .

input: May an instrument do a noble deed, what a poor instrument.
target: What poor an instrument May do a noble deed !

input: The man brings me freedom.
target: He brings me liberty .

input: I have nothing of woman in me because my resolution has been placed.
target: My resolution's placed , and I have nothing Of woman in me .

input: From head to foot, I am marble- constant.
target: Now from head to foot I am marble-constant .

input: No planet is of mine at the moment.
target: Now the fleeting moon No planet is of mine .

input: This is the person.
target: This is the man .

input: Don't go to him, and leave him.
target: Avoid , and leave him .

target: Let me stay the growth of his beard , if thou delay me not the knowledge of his chin .

input: The wrestler's heels were tripped up by the young man and your heart was broken in an instant.
target: It is young Orlando , that tripped up the wrestler's heels and your heart both in an instant .

input: The devil take a mocking tone.
target: Nay , but the devil take mocking .

input: I believe in him, 'tis he.
target: I ' faith , coz , 'tis he .

input: Are you talking about the city of Orlando?
target: Orlando ?

input: There is a city named after it, Orlando.
target: Orlando .

input: What did he think when he saw him?
target: What did he when thou saw'st him ?

input: What was said by him?
target: What said he ?

input: What did he look like?
target: How looked he ?

input: Where in the world did he go?
target: Wherein went he ?

input: What is it that makes him here?
target: What makes him here ?

input: I wonder if he asked for me.
target: Did he ask for me ?

input: Where is he still located?
target: Where remains he ?

input: What happened to him with thee.
target: How parted he with thee ?

input: And when will you see him again?
target: And when shalt thou see him again ?

input: Answer me in a single word.
target: Answer me in one word .

input: Do he know that I am in the forest and wearing man's clothing?
target: But doth he know that I am in this forest and in man's apparel ?

input: Looks like he is as fresh as he was the day he wrestled.
target: Looks he as freshly as he did the day he wrestled ?

input: Take a taste of my finding him, and enjoy it.
target: But take a taste of my finding him , and relish it with good observance .

input: He was under a tree like a dropped acorn.
target: I found him under a tree like a dropped acorn .

input: It may well be called Jove's tree when it drops fruit.
target: It may well be called Jove's tree when it drops forth such fruit .

input: Good madam, give me an audience for me.
target: Give me audience , good madam .

input: Proceed as you please.
target: Proceed .

input: He was stretched along like a wounded knight in there.
target: There lay he , stretched along like a wounded knight .

input: It is a pity to see such a sight, but it becomes the ground.
target: Though it be pity to see such a sight , it well becomes the ground .

input: I want you to cry "holla" to the other person.
target: Cry "holla" to thy tongue , I prithee .

input: It curvets suddenly.
target: It curvets unseasonably .

input: He was furnished like a hunting dog.
target: He was furnished like a hunter .

input: Oh, frightening.
target: Oh , ominous !

input: He comes to destroy my heart.
target: He comes to kill my heart .

input: I would not have to burden myself with singing my song.
target: I would sing my song without a burden .

input: I am brought out of tune by Thou.
target: Thou bring'st me out of tune .

input: Do you not know that I am a woman?
target: Do you not know I am a woman ?

input: I have to speak when I think about something.
target: When I think , I must speak .

input: It was sweet, say on.
target: Sweet , say on .

input: You bring me out of here.
target: You bring me out .

input: Soft, comes he not here.
target: Soft , comes he not here ?

input: Tis he.
target: Tis he .

input: I am thankful for your company, but I have been alone for a long time.
target: I thank you for your company , but , good faith , I had as lief have been myself alone .

input: For fashion sake, I thank you for your society, but I had also.
target: And so had I , but yet , for fashion sake , I thank you too for your society .

input: God, please be with you.
target: God be wi ' you .

input: We need to meet as little as possible.
target: Let's meet as little as we can .

input: I would like us to be better strangers.
target: I do desire we may be better strangers .

input: I am praying that you don't write love songs in the barks of trees.
target: I pray you mar no more trees with writing love songs in their barks .

input: I am praying that you don't read my verse with prejudice.
target: I pray you mar no more of my verses with reading them ill- favoredly .

input: Do you know the name of your love's name?
target: Rosalind is your love's name ?

input: Just, yes.
target: Yes , just .

input: I don't like her name at all.
target: I do not like her name .

input: What is her stature?
target: What stature is she of ?

input: It was just as high as my heart.
target: Just as high as my heart .

input: You have a good amount of pretty answers.
target: You are full of pretty answers .

input: Being in love is the worst fault you can have.
target: The worst fault you have is to be in love .

input: I will not change for your good virtue.
target: Tis a fault I will not change for your best virtue .

input: I am weary of you.
target: I am weary of you .

input: There I will see my own figure.
target: There I shall see mine own figure .

input: I have to be either a fool or a cipher.
target: Which I take to be either a fool or a cipher .

input: I won't tarry with you anymore.
target: I'll tarry no longer with you .

input: Good Signior Love, farewell.
target: Farewell , good Signior Love .

input: I am happy that you are leaving.
target: I am glad of your departure .

input: Good Monsieur Melancholy, adieu.
target: Adieu , good Monsieur Melancholy .

input: Very well, very well.
target: Very well .

input: What do you think would be the answer?
target: What would you ?

input: You should ask me the time of the day.
target: You should ask me what time o ' day .

input: There isn't a clock in the forest.
target: There's no clock in the forest .

input: There is no true lover in the forest if you sigh every minute and groan every hour, it would detect the lazy foot of time as well as a clock.
target: Then there is no true lover in the forest , else sighing every minute and groaning every hour would detect the lazy foot of time as well as a clock .

input: Marry, do I, sir, and I came to discuss a matter with you.
target: Marry , do I , sir , and I came to acquaint you with a matter .

input: I have been told that your younger brother is going to try to get me to fall.
target: I am given , sir , secretly to understand that your younger brother Orlando hath a disposition to come in disguised against me to try a fall .

input: Tomorrow, sir, I wrestle for my credit, and he that escapes me without some broken limb will acquit him well.
target: Tomorrow , sir , I wrestle for my credit , and he that escapes me without some broken limb shall acquit him well .

input: I would not be able to foil your brother because he is young and tender for your love, as I must for my own honor if he comes in.
target: Your brother is but young and tender , and , for your love I would be loath to foil him , as I must for my own honor if he come in .

input: I came to you to let you know that it was a thing of his own search and that he would run into disgrace if you did not stay him from his intendment.
target: Therefore , out of my love to you , I came hither to acquaint you withal , that either you might stay him from his intendment or brook such disgrace well as he shall run into , in that it is a thing of his own search and altogether against my will .

input: I would like to thank thee for your love to me. I will be more than happy to requite.
target: Charles , I thank thee for thy love to me , which thou shalt find I will most kindly requite .

input: I had noticed my brother's purpose and tried to discourage him from it, but he is determined to go ahead with it.
target: I had myself notice of my brother's purpose herein and have by underhand means labored to dissuade him from it ; but he is resolute .

input: I will tell thee that it is the stubbornest young fellow of France who is full of ambition and jealousy, a secret and villainous contriver against me, and his natural brother.
target: I'll tell thee , Charles : it is the stubbornest young fellow of France , full of ambition , an envious emulator of every man's good parts , a secret and villainous contriver against me his natural brother .

input: Use your discretion, therefore.
target: Therefore use thy discretion .

input: I broke his neck as his finger, I did it as a lie.
target: I had as lief thou didst break his neck as his finger .

input: I speak but brotherly of him, but should I anatomize him to thee as he is, I must blush and weep, and he must look pale and wonder.
target: I speak but brotherly of him , but should I anatomize him to thee as he is , I must blush and weep , and thou must look pale and wonder .

input: The swift foot of time is something that should be considered.
target: And why not the swift foot of time ?

input: Had not that been correct?
target: Had not that been as proper ?

input: By no means, sir.
target: By no means , sir .

input: Time travels in different ways with different people.
target: Time travels in diverse paces with diverse persons .

input: I will tell you who time ambles withal, who time trots withal, who time gallops withal, and who he stands still withal.
target: I'll tell you who time ambles withal , who time trots withal , who time gallops withal , and who he stands still withal .

input: Who does he trot withal?
target: I prithee , who doth he trot withal ?

input: Who is blessed with time withal?
target: Who ambles time withal ?

input: These are the times that are good.
target: These time ambles withal .

input: Who is he going to gallop with?
target: Who doth he gallop withal ?

input: Who stays it with us?
target: Who stays it still withal ?

input: When lawyers are on vacation, they sleep between term and term, and then they don't know how time moves.
target: With lawyers in the vacation , for they sleep between term and term , and then they perceive not how time moves .

input: Where do you live, pretty youth?
target: Where dwell you , pretty youth ?

input: Are you a native of this place?
target: Are you native of this place ?

input: Where she is kindled is where you see her as the cony.
target: As the cony that you see dwell where she is kindled .

input: Your accent is not the same as what you could buy in a dwelling.
target: Your accent is something finer than you could purchase in so removed a dwelling .

input: I have been told so many times.
target: I have been told so of many .

input: I was taught to speak by an old religious uncle who was an inland man who fell in love with a woman there.
target: But indeed an old religious uncle of mine taught me to speak , who was in his youth an inland man , one that knew courtship too well , for there he fell in love .

input: I am thankful that I am not a woman, because I have heard him read many lectures against it, and that he generally taxed their whole sex withal.
target: I have heard him read many lectures against it , and I thank God I am not a woman , to be touched with so many giddy offenses as he hath generally taxed their whole sex withal .

input: Do you remember any of the bad things that he said about women?
target: Can you remember any of the principal evils that he laid to the charge of women ?

input: There wasn't a single principal.
target: There were none principal .

input: I recount some of them, prithee.
target: I prithee , recount some of them .

input: I will not cast away my health but on those that are sick.
target: No , I will not cast away my physic but on those that are sick .

input: There is a man in the forest who abuses our young plants with carving "Rosalind" on their barks, as well as hanging epitaphs on hawthorns and Elegies on the trees.
target: There is a man haunts the forest that abuses our young plants with carving "Rosalind" on their barks , hangs odes upon hawthorns and elegies on brambles , all , forsooth , deifying the name of Rosalind .

input: He is so love-shaked that I can't believe it.
target: I am he that is so love-shaked .

input: I am praying that you tell me your remedy.
target: I pray you tell me your remedy .

input: There is no evidence of my uncle's marks on you.
target: There is none of my uncle's marks upon you .

input: I am sure you are not prisoner because he taught me how to know a man in love in which cage of rushes.
target: He taught me how to know a man in love , in which cage of rushes I am sure you are not prisoner .

input: What were his marks when he was younger?
target: What were his marks ?

input: I pardon you for the lean cheek, sunken blue eye, and beard that you have not, but for the fact that you have had in.
target: A lean cheek , which you have not ; a blue eye and sunken , which you have not ; an unquestionable spirit , which you have not ; a beard neglected , which you have not , but I pardon you for that , for simply your having in beard is a younger brother's revenue .

input: Your hose should be ungartered, your bonnet should be unbanded, your sleeve should be unbuttoned, and your shoe should not be untied, because you are showing a careless desolation.
target: Then your hose should be ungartered , your bonnet unbanded , your sleeve unbuttoned , your shoe untied , and everything about you demonstrating a careless desolation .

input: You are not a man like this.
target: But you are no such man .

input: You seem to love yourself more than any other person, and that's because you are point-device.
target: You are rather point-device in your accouterments , as loving yourself than seeming the lover of any other .

input: I would make them believe that I love them.
target: Fair youth , I would I could make thee believe I love .

input: Is it possible that I believe it?
target: Me believe it ?

input: Is he the one who hangs the verse on the trees, because Rosalind is so admired?
target: But , in good sooth , are you he that hangs the verses on the trees wherein Rosalind is so admired ?

input: I swear to thee, youth, by the white hand of Rosalind, that he is that unfortunate he is.
target: I swear to thee , youth , by the white hand of Rosalind , I am that he , that unfortunate he .

input: As your rhymes speak, are you so in love?
target: But are you so much in love as your rhymes speak ?

input: How much can't be expressed with rhyme or reason.
target: Neither rhyme nor reason can express how much .

input: The reason why love is not punished and cured is that the lunacy is so ordinary that the whippers are in love with each other.
target: Love is merely a madness and , I tell you , deserves as well a dark house and a whip as madmen do , and the reason why they are not so punished and cured is that the lunacy is so ordinary that the whippers are in love , too .

input: I say that I cure it by counsel.
target: Yet I profess curing it by counsel .

input: Did you ever cure anything?
target: Did you ever cure any so ?

input: Yes, one, and in this manner.
target: Yes , one , and in this manner .

input: Youth, I would not be cured.
target: I would not be cured , youth .

input: I would cure you if you would call me and come to my cote every day and woo me.
target: I would cure you if you would but call me Rosalind and come every day to my cote and woo me .

input: By the faith of my love, I will do it.
target: Now , by the faith of my love , I will .

input: Tell me the location of it.
target: Tell me where it is .

input: Go with me to it, and I'll show you where you live, and by the way, you'll tell me where in the forest you live.
target: Go with me to it , and I'll show it you ; and by the way you shall tell me where in the forest you live .

input: Will you join us?
target: Will you go ?

input: Good youth, with all my heart.
target: With all my heart , good youth .

input: Come, sister, will you go? I must be called Rosalind.
target: Nay , you must call me Rosalind. , Come , sister , will you go ?

input: Good to see you come apace,Audrey.
target: Come apace , good Audrey .

input: I will bring your goats with me.
target: I will fetch up your goats , Audrey .

input: Do you have any simple feature content?
target: Doth my simple feature content you ?

input: Lord, you have features that warrant us!
target: Your features , Lord warrant us !

input: What features do you have?
target: What features ?

input: I would think that the gods had made thee poetical.
target: Truly , I would the gods had made thee poetical .

input: I don't know what the word "poetical" means.
target: I do not know what "poetical" is .

input: Is it honest when it is said and done.
target: Is it honest in deed and word ?

input: Is that a true thing?
target: Is it a true thing ?

input: For the truest poetry is the most feigning, and lovers are given to poetry, and what they swear in poetry may be said as lovers they do not really.
target: No , truly , for the truest poetry is the most feigning , and lovers are given to poetry , and what they swear in poetry may be said as lovers they do feign .

input: Is it possible that the gods made you poetical?
target: Do you wish then that the gods had made me poetical ?

input: I do, truly, for I swear to you that I am honest.
target: I do , truly , for thou swear'st to me thou art honest .

input: I might have some hope if he were a poet.
target: Now , if thou wert a poet , I might have some hope thou didst feign .

input: Is it possible that you wouldn't have me honest?
target: Would you not have me honest ?

input: Unless you are hard-favored, honesty coupled with beauty is to have honey a sauce to sugar.
target: No , truly , unless thou wert hard-favored , for honesty coupled to beauty is to have honey a sauce to sugar .

input: I pray the gods will make me honest because I am not fair.
target: Well , I am not fair , and therefore I pray the gods make me honest .

input: I am not a slut and I thank the gods for that.
target: I am not a slut , though I thank the gods I am foul .

input: Praise the gods for their foulness and sluttyness may come later.
target: Well , praised be the gods for thy foulness ; sluttishness may come hereafter .

input: What do you think about that?
target: But what though ?

input: Courage is what it is.
target: Courage .

input: That is the gift from his wife, not his own.
target: Well , that is the dowry of his wife ; 'tis none of his own getting .

input: Horns, what do you think?
target: Horns ?

input: Even so is true.
target: Even so .

input: The men are poor alone.
target: Poor men alone ?

input: No, no, no.
target: No , no .

input: The deer of the noblest variety are as large as the bandit.
target: The noblest deer hath them as huge as the rascal .

input: Is the single man a blessed man?
target: Is the single man therefore blessed ?

input: No, that's not true.
target: No .

input: The forehead of a married man is more honorable than the bare brow of a bachelor, as a walled town is more worthier than a village.
target: As a walled town is more worthier than a village , so is the forehead of a married man more honorable than the bare brow of a bachelor .

input: Sir Oliver, you are well met, here comes you.
target: Here comes Sir Oliver. , Sir Oliver Martext , you are well met .

input: Will you dispatch us under the tree or will we accompany you to your chapel?
target: Will you dispatch us here under this tree , or shall we go with you to your chapel ?

input: Is there anything here that the woman can get?
target: Is there none here to give the woman ?

input: She won't be taken on a gift of any man.
target: I will not take her on gift of any man .

input: She must be given, or the marriage is not lawful.
target: Truly , she must be given , or the marriage is not lawful .

input: What do you think about it, sir?
target: How do you , sir ?

input: You are very pleasant to be around.
target: You are very well met .

input: You should be protected for your last company.
target: God 'ild you for your last company .

input: I am very happy to see you.
target: I am very glad to see you .

input: Even a toy in hand here, sir.
target: Even a toy in hand here , sir .

input: Please be covered, pray.
target: Nay , pray be covered .

input: Is it possible that you will be married?
target: Will you be married , motley ?

input: The ox had his bow, the horse had his curb, and the falcon had her bells, so wedlock would be nibbling on them.
target: As the ox hath his bow , sir , the horse his curb , and the falcon her bells , so man hath his desires ; and as pigeons bill , so wedlock would be nibbling .

input: Will you, being a man of your breeding, be married under a bush like a beggar?
target: And will you , being a man of your breeding , be married under a bush like a beggar ?

input: If you want to know what marriage is, get you to church and have a good priest.
target: Get you to church , and have a good priest that can tell you what marriage is .

input: One of you will prove that a shrunk panel is the same as green timber.
target: Then one of you will prove a shrunk panel and , like green timber , warp , warp .

input: Let me counsel thee with you, go with me.
target: Go thou with me , and let me counsel thee .

input: Come with me, sweet Audrey.
target: Come , sweet Audrey .

input: We must either be married or living in bawdry.
target: We must be married , or we must live in bawdry. , Farewell , good Master Oliver , not 'T is no matter .

input: Ne'er a fanciful knave of them all will violate me out of my calling.
target: Ne'er a fantastical knave of them all shall flout me out of my calling .

input: Never talk to me again.
target: Never talk to me .

input: I will break down.
target: I will weep .

input: I have the grace to consider that tears do not become a man.
target: Do , I prithee , but yet have the grace to consider that tears do not become a man .

input: Is it possible that I don't cause to weep.
target: But have I not cause to weep ?

input: It's as good a cause as one would desire.
target: As good cause as one would desire .

input: Please weep.
target: Therefore weep .

input: The touch of holy bread is what makes his kissing so sacred.
target: And his kissing is as full of sanctity as the touch of holy bread .

input: I am very happy to have hither to you.
target: I am heartily glad I came hither to you .

input: I will give him his payment if he shows up tomorrow.
target: If he come tomorrow , I'll give him his payment .

input: I'll never wrestle for prize more if he ever goes alone again.
target: If ever he go alone again , I'll never wrestle for prize more .

input: Good farewell, Charles.
target: Farewell , good Charles .

input: But this wrestler will clear all and it will not be long.
target: But it shall not be so long ; this wrestler shall clear all .

input: You've heard him swear, he was downright crazy.
target: You have heard him swear downright he was .

input: He is in the forest with your father.
target: He attends here in the forest on the duke your father .

input: The duke had a lot of questions for me.
target: I met the duke yesterday and had much question with him .

input: He let me go because he laughed.
target: So he laughed and let me go .

input: When there is a man like that, what do we say to our fathers?
target: But what talk we of fathers when there is such a man as Orlando ?

input: That's a man who is brave.
target: Oh , that's a brave man .

input: Who arrives here?
target: Who comes here ?

input: After the shepherd that complained of love, who you saw sitting by me on the turf, Praising the proud disdainful shepherdess that was his mistress, you asked the master and mistress.
target: Mistress and master , you have oft inquired After the shepherd that complained of love , Who you saw sitting by me on the turf , Praising the proud disdainful shepherdess That was his mistress .

input: Those in love get sustenance from the sight of lovers.
target: The sight of lovers feedeth those in love .

input: Do not judge me, sweet Phoebe.
target: Sweet Phoebe , do not scorn me .

input: Do not, that's for sure.
target: Do not , Phoebe .

input: Say that you don't love me, but don't say so in bitterness.
target: Say that you love me not , but say not so In bitterness .

input: For shame, for shame, Lie not to say mine eyes are murderers, because they are counterfeit.
target: Now counterfeit to swoon , why , now fall down ; Or if thou canst not , Oh , for shame , for shame , Lie not , to say mine eyes are murderers .

input: Show the wound mine eye that was made.
target: Now show the wound mine eye hath made in thee .

input: I darted at thee and hurt thee, but now mine eyes.
target: But now mine eyes , Which I have darted at thee , hurt thee not .

input: I am certain that there is no force in eyes that can hurt.
target: Nor , I am sure , there is no force in eyes That can do hurt .

input: If ever, as that ever may be near, you meet in some fresh cheek the power of fancy, and then you know the wounds invisible that love's keen arrows make.
target: O dear Phoebe , If ever , as that ever may be near , You meet in some fresh cheek the power of fancy , Then shall you know the wounds invisible That love's keen arrows make .

input: Come not close to me until that time.
target: But till that time Come not thou near me .

input: I will not pity thee until that time comes, and I will afflict myself with the mocks.
target: And when that time comes , Afflict me with thy mocks , pity me not , As till that time I shall not pity thee .

input: But, mistress, know yourself.
target: But , mistress , know yourself .

input: Down on your knees, thank heaven, for a good man's love, for I must tell you friendly in your ear, Sell when you can, and you are not for all markets.
target: Down on your knees And thank heaven , fasting , for a good man's love , For I must tell you friendly in your ear , Sell when you can ; you are not for all markets .

input: Take the man's offer, cry the man mercy, love him.
target: Cry the man mercy , love him , take his offer .

input: So shepherd, take her to thee.
target: So take her to thee , shepherd .

input: I like you other than that.
target: Besides , I like you not .

input: Will you go, sister? Shepherd, please ply her hard.
target: Will you go , sister ? , Shepherd , ply her hard .

input: Come, sister, look on him better, and be not proud.
target: Come , sister. , Shepherdess , look on him better , And be not proud .

input: All the world could see, but none could be so abused as he was.
target: Though all the world could see , None could be so abused in sight as he .

input: pity me, I am so sorry.
target: Sweet Phoebe , pity me .

input: I am sorry for Silvius, I am sorry.
target: Why , I am sorry for thee , gentle Silvius .

input: If you give love to my grief and I give love to my grief, you will both be extermined.
target: If you do sorrow at my grief in love , By giving love your sorrow and my grief Were both extermined .

input: I have my love for him.
target: Thou hast my love .

input: Is that not neighborly?
target: Is not that neighborly ?

input: I would be happy to have you.
target: I would have you .

input: Why did that make you want to vomit?
target: Why , that were covetousness .

input: But don't look for any more recompense than what you have already been given.
target: But do not look for further recompense Than thine own gladness that thou art employed .

input: Do you know the youth that talked to me?
target: Know'st thou the youth that spoke to me erewhile ?

input: I have met him and he has bought the cottage and the bounds that the old carlot once was master of.
target: Not very well , but I have met him oft , And he hath bought the cottage and the bounds That the old carlot once was master of .

input: I ask for him, but I don't think I love him.
target: Think not I love him , though I ask for him .

input: He talks well, but what do I care about words?
target: Tis but a peevish boy , yet he talks well , But what care I for words ?

input: Words do well, when he speaks them pleases those that hear them.
target: Yet words do well When he that speaks them pleases those that hear .

input: He's proud, but he's not very pretty, and yet his pride becomes him.
target: It is a pretty youth , not very pretty , But sure he's proud , and yet his pride becomes him .

input: He's going to make a good man.
target: He'll make a proper man .

input: He is not very tall, yet he is tall for his years.
target: He is not very tall , yet for his years he's tall .

input: His leg is not as good as it could be, but it is well.
target: His leg is but so-so , and yet 'tis well .

input: He had a pretty redness in his lip, a little riper and more lusty red, than that mixed in his cheek, and it was just the difference.
target: There was a pretty redness in his lip , A little riper and more lusty red Than that mixed in his cheek : 'twas just the difference Betwixt the constant red and mingled damask .

input: What did he have to do to chide me?
target: For what had he to do to chide at me ?

input: He said my eyes were black and my hair was black, and now I am remembered as such.

target: Yet I hate not Orlando .

target: Doth he not deserve well ?

target: Let me love him for that , and do you love him because I do .

target: With his eyes full of anger .

target: Me , uncle ?

target: You , cousin .

input: If that beest is found near our public court within the next ten days, Thou diest for it.
target: Within these ten days if that thou beest found So near our public court as twenty miles , Thou diest for it .

target: I do beseech your Grace , Let me the knowledge of my fault bear with me .

target: If with myself I hold intelligence Or have acquaintance with mine own desires , If that I do not dream or be not frantic , As I do trust I am not , then , dear uncle , Never so much as in a thought unborn Did I offend your Highness .

input: All traitors will do that.
target: Thus do all traitors .

input: If their purgation consisted of words, they are as innocent as grace itself.
target: If their purgation did consist in words , They are as innocent as grace itself .

target: Let it suffice thee that I trust thee not .

target: Thou art thy father's daughter .

input: Enough has been said.
target: There's enough .

target: So was I when your Highness took his dukedom .

target: So was I when your Highness banished him .
