target: My father was no traitor .

target: Then , good my liege , mistake me not so much To think my poverty is treacherous .

target: Ay , Celia , we stayed her for your sake .

target: I was too young that time to value her , But now I know her .

target: Firm and irrevocable is my doom Which I have passed upon her .

target: I can not live out of her company .

input: You are a fool, niece.
target: You are a fool. , You , niece , provide yourself .

target: Know you before whom , sir ?

target: I know you are my eldest brother , and in the gentle condition of blood you should so know me .

target: I have as much of my father in me as you , albeit , I confess , your coming before me is nearer to his reverence .

target: Thou hast not , cousin .

target: Know'st thou not the duke Hath banished me , his daughter ?

target: What shall I call thee when thou art a man ?

target: But what will you be called ?

target: Would he not be a comfort to our travel ?

target: Leave me alone to woo him .

target: Now go we in content To liberty , and not to banishment .

target: Are not these woods More free from peril than the envious court ?

target: These are counselors That feelingly persuade me what I am." Sweet are the uses of adversity , Which , like the toad , ugly and venomous , Wears yet a precious jewel in his head .

target: Happy is your Grace , That can translate the stubbornness of fortune Into so quiet and so sweet a style .

target: I love to cope him in these sullen fits , For then he's full of matter .

target: Know you not , master , to some kind of men Their graces serve them but as enemies ?

target: Why , what's the matter ?

target: Within this roof The enemy of all your graces lives .

target: Yet this I will not do , do how I can .

input: I will subject myself to the malice of a diverted blood and bloody brother.
target: I rather will subject me to the malice Of a diverted blood and bloody brother .

input: But don't do that.
target: But do not so .

input: Allow me to be your servant.
target: Let me be your servant .

input: I am strong and lusty, even though I look old, for in my youth I never used hot and rebellious liquors in my blood, nor did I use the means of weakness and debility.
target: Though I look old , yet I am strong and lusty , For in my youth I never did apply Hot and rebellious liquors in my blood Nor did not with unbashful forehead woo The means of weakness and debility .

input: My age is like a lusty winter, but kindly.
target: Therefore my age is as a lusty winter , Frosty but kindly .

input: I'm willing to go with you.
target: Let me go with you .

input: I'll do the service of a younger man for you.
target: I'll do the service of a younger man In all your business and necessities .

input: The constant service of the antique world, when service sweat for duty, not for meed, is how well in the old man appears.
target: O good old man , how well in thee appears The constant service of the antique world , When service sweat for duty , not for meed .

input: But come your ways.
target: But come thy ways .

input: We'll go along with each other, and we'll light upon some settled low content.
target: We'll go along together , And ere we have thy youthful wages spent , We'll light upon some settled low content .

input: I will follow thee to the last gasp with truth and loyalty, Master.
target: Master , go on , and I will follow thee To the last gasp , with truth and loyalty .

input: I have lived here for seventeen years, but now live in a different place.
target: From seventeen years till now almost fourscore Here lived I , but now live here no more .

input: It is too late a week after seventeen years for many of them to seek their fortunes.
target: At seventeen years , many their fortunes seek , But at fourscore , it is too late a week .

input: To die well and not my master's debtor can not be better than fortune can be.
target: Yet fortune can not recompense me better Than to die well , and not my master's debtor .

input: How weary are my spirits, Jupiter!
target: O Jupiter , how weary are my spirits !

input: If my legs were not tired, I wouldn't care about my spirits.
target: I care not for my spirits , if my legs were not weary .

input: I can not go any further.
target: I can not go no further .

input: I had to bear with you than I had to bear you.
target: For my part , I had rather bear with you than bear you .

input: The more fool I am, the more I am in Arden.
target: Ay , now am I in Arden , the more fool I .

input: Good Touchstone, Ay, be so.
target: Ay , be so , good Touchstone .

input: Look at the young man and old man who are talking.
target: Look you who comes here , a young man and an old in solemn talk .

input: Is it possible that you laid hands on me, villain?
target: Wilt thou lay hands on me , villain ?

input: I am not a bad person.
target: I am no villain .

input: I wouldn't take this hand from my brother until the other pulled out his tongue and said so.
target: Wert thou not my brother , I would not take this hand from thy throat till this other had pulled out thy tongue for saying so .

input: He has railed against himself.
target: Thou hast railed on thyself .

input: Be patient, be a sweet masters.
target: Sweet masters , be patient .

input: For your father's remembrance, please be at peace.
target: For your father's remembrance , be at accord .

input: I want to let me go.
target: Let me go , I say .

input: I will not until I get what I want.
target: I will not till I please .

input: You will hear me, I will.
target: You shall hear me .

input: You were charged by my father to give me good education.
target: My father charged you in his will to give me good education .

input: You have trained me to be like a peasant, hiding from me all the gentlemanlike qualities.
target: You have trained me like a peasant , obscuring and hiding from me all gentlemanlike qualities .

input: The spirit of my father is strong in me, and I will no longer be able to endure it.
target: The spirit of my father grows strong in me , and I will no longer endure it .

input: When that is spent, what do you do, beg?
target: And what wilt thou do , beg when that is spent ?

input: Well, sir, get you in.
target: Well , sir , get you in .

input: I won't be troubled with you for a long time.
target: I will not long be troubled with you .

input: Some part of your will will be part of it.
target: You shall have some part of your will .

input: I am praying you leave me.
target: I pray you leave me .

input: That is the way to make her dislike you.
target: That is the way to make her scorn you still .

input: O Corin, I know how I love her.
target: O Corin , that thou knew'st how I do love her !

input: I think that I have loved ere now.
target: I partly guess , for I have loved ere now .

input: No, Corin, being old, you can't guess, though in your youth, you were a true lover.
target: No , Corin , being old , thou canst not guess , Though in thy youth thou wast as true a lover As ever sighed upon a midnight pillow .

input: I think man never loved so much as he did if he had ever been like mine. How many ridiculous actions have he been drawn to by his fantasy?
target: But if thy love were ever like to mine , As sure I think did never man love so , How many actions most ridiculous Hast thou been drawn to by thy fantasy ?

input: I have forgotten about a thousand of them.
target: Into a thousand that I have forgotten .

input: Oh, ne'er love was so great then.
target: Oh , thou didst then ne'er love so heartily .

input: If the love that made thee run into it was the only folly, then he has not loved it.
target: If thou rememb'rest not the slightest folly That ever love did make thee run into , Thou hast not loved .

input: If he has not sat as I do now, he will wear the hearer in her praise.
target: Or if thou hast not sat as I do now , Wearying thy hearer in thy mistress's praise , Thou hast not loved .

input: My passion now makes me, if Thou has not broken from company Abruptly.
target: Or if thou hast not broke from company Abruptly , as my passion now makes me , Thou hast not loved .
O Phoebe , Phoebe , Phoebe !

input: I have by hard adventure found my own, the poor shepherd.
target: Alas , poor shepherd , searching of thy wound , I have by hard adventure found mine own .

input: And I have mine as well.
target: And I mine .

input: When I was in love, I broke my sword and begged him to take it so I could go to Jane Smile.
target: I remember when I was in love I broke my sword upon a stone and bid him take that for coming a- night to Jane Smile .

input: I remember the kissing of her batler, and the cow's dugs that her hands had milked.
target: And I remember the kissing of her batler , and the cow's dugs that her pretty chopped hands had milked .

input: I remember the wooing of a peascod instead of her, from whom I took two cods, and gave her them again, and cried, "wear these for my sake."
target: And I remember the wooing of a peascod instead of her , from whom I took two cods and , giving her them again , said with weeping tears , "Wear these for my sake." We that are true lovers run into strange capers .

input: All nature is mortal in nature and love mortal in folly.
target: But as all is mortal in nature , so is all nature in love mortal in folly .

input: Thou speak'st wise than the art ware of.
target: Thou speak'st wiser than thou art ware of .

input: I will be ware of mine own wit until I break my shins against it.
target: Nay , I shall ne'er be ware of mine own wit till I break my shins against it .

input: Jove, Jove, this shepherd's passion is much upon my fashion.
target: Jove , Jove , this shepherd's passion Is much upon my fashion .

input: And mine, but it doesn't stay the same with me.
target: And mine , but it grows something stale with me .

input: One of you question if the man will give us any food if he gets gold.
target: I pray you , one of you question yond man , if he for gold will give us any food .

input: It's peace, it's fool.
target: Peace , fool .

input: He's not a descendant of the kinsman.
target: He's not thy kinsman .

input: Who makes the calls?
target: Who calls ?

input: Sir, your betters, sir.
target: Your betters , sir .

input: I prithee, shepherd, if that love or gold can in this desert place, buy entertainment, bring us where we may rest ourselves and feed us.
target: I prithee , shepherd , if that love or gold Can in this desert place buy entertainment , Bring us where we may rest ourselves and feed .

input: I pity her and wish that her sake was more important than mine. My fortunes were more able to relieve her.
target: Fair sir , I pity her And wish , for her sake more than for mine own , My fortunes were more able to relieve her .

target: But I am shepherd to another man And do not shear the fleeces that I graze .

target: Besides , his cote , his flocks , and bounds of feed Are now on sale , and at our sheepcote now , By reason of his absence , there is nothing That you will feed on .

input: What is he going to purchase from his flock and pasture?
target: What is he that shall buy his flock and pasture ?

input: That young swain that you saw here, that little cares about buying anything.
target: That young swain that you saw here but erewhile , That little cares for buying anything .

input: If it stands with honesty, I ask that you buy the cottage, pasture, and the flock, and that you pay for it with honesty.
target: I pray thee , if it stand with honesty , Buy thou the cottage , pasture , and the flock , And thou shalt have to pay for it of us .

input: We will make sure that the wages are mended.
target: And we will mend thy wages .

input: The thing is to be auctioned off.
target: Assuredly the thing is to be sold .

input: You should go with me.
target: Go with me .

input: If you like to report The soil, the profit, and this kind of life, I will give you your very faithful feeder and buy it with your gold right now.
target: If you like upon report The soil , the profit , and this kind of life , I will your very faithful feeder be And buy it with your gold right suddenly .

input: More, more, I prithee, more.
target: More , more , I prithee , more .

input: Monsieur Jaques, it will make you melancholy.
target: It will make you melancholy , Monsieur Jaques .

input: I would like to thank you.
target: I thank it .

input: More, I prithee more.
target: More , I prithee , more .

input: As a weasel sucks eggs, I can suck the melancholy out of a song.
target: I can suck melancholy out of a song as a weasel sucks eggs .

input: More, I prithee more.
target: More , I prithee , more .

input: My voice is not perfect.
target: My voice is ragged .

input: I know that I can't please you.
target: I know I can not please you .

input: Another stanzo is on the way.
target: Come , more , another stanzo .

input: I don't care for their names at all.
target: Nay , I care not for their names .

input: I'll thank you if ever I ever do.
target: Well then , if ever I thank any man , I'll thank you .

input: "compliment" is like an encounter of two dogs and apes.
target: But that they call "compliment" is like th ' encounter of two dog- apes .

input: It will be dinner time within this hour.
target: Within this hour it will be dinnertime .

input: I will view the manners of the town, Peruse the traders, gaze upon the buildings, and then return and sleep within my inn.
target: Till that , I'll view the manners of the town , Peruse the traders , gaze upon the buildings , And then return and sleep within mine inn , For with long travel I am stiff and weary .

input: Get thee out of the way.
target: Get thee away .

input: Many a man would take you at your word, and have so good a mean that you would.
target: Many a man would take you at your word And go indeed , having so good a mean .

input: When I am dull with care and melancholy, he lightens my humor with his merry jests.
target: A trusty villain , sir , that very oft , When I am dull with care and melancholy , Lightens my humor with his merry jests .

input: Will you join me for a walk around the town and then go to my inn and eat with me?
target: What , will you walk with me about the town And then go to my inn and dine with me ?

input: I believe I had.
target: I think I had .

input: I didn't deny it at all.
target: I never did deny it .

input: Yes, that you did, sir, and forswore it as well.
target: Yes , that you did , sir , and forswore it too .

input: I don't know who heard me deny it or forswear it.
target: Who heard me to deny it or forswear it ?

input: These ears were mine, and I know that they did hear thee.
target: These ears of mine , thou know'st did hear thee .

input: Fie on thee and wretch.
target: Fie on thee , wretch .

input: It's pity that any honest man would resort to walking where there are prostitutes.
target: Tis pity that thou liv'st To walk where any honest men resort .

input: The villain to impeach me was Thou.
target: Thou art a villain to impeach me thus .

input: I will prove my honor and honesty against thee if you stand up.
target: I'll prove mine honor and mine honesty Against thee presently if thou dar'st stand .

input: I dare and defy thee for a villain.
target: I dare , and do defy thee for a villain .

input: Run, master, run.
target: Run , master , run .

input: Take a house for the sake of God.
target: For God's sake , take a house .

input: Some priory is what this is.
target: This is some priory .

input: Either we are spoiled or we are.
target: In , or we are spoiled .

input: People, be quiet, be quiet.
target: Be quiet , people .

input: Where are you going to hither?
target: Wherefore throng you hither ?

input: My husband distracted me to fetch my poor husband.
target: To fetch my poor distracted husband hence .

input: We can bind him fast and take him home to recover from his injuries.
target: Let us come in , that we may bind him fast And bear him home for his recovery .

input: How long did this possession hold the man?
target: How long hath this possession held the man ?

input: He was heavy, sad, and much different from the man he was this week.
target: This week he hath been heavy , sour , sad , And much different from the man he was .

input: Ne'er was so passionate until this afternoon that he braked into rage.
target: But till this afternoon his passion Ne'er brake into extremity of rage .

input: Young men who give their eyes the liberty of gazing are guilty of a sin that is prevalent in unlawful love.
target: Hath not else his eye Stray'd his affection in unlawful love , A sin prevailing much in youthful men Who give their eyes the liberty of gazing ?

input: Which of these are the things that he is subject to?
target: Which of these sorrows is he subject to ?

input: You should have reprimanded him for that.
target: You should for that have reprehended him .

input: I did so because of that.
target: Why , so I did .

input: Ay, but not rough enough.
target: Ay , but not rough enough .

input: In a private place.
target: Haply in private .

input: And in the assembly as well.
target: And in assemblies too .

input: Not enough, but Ay.
target: Ay , but not enough .

input: It was the subject of my theme, and I often looked at it alone.
target: Alone , it was the subject of my theme ; In company I often glanced it .

input: I told him that it was bad and vile.
target: Still did I tell him it was vile and bad .

input: The man was so angry that he came up with the idea.
target: And thereof came it that the man was mad .

input: The venom of a jealous woman is more deadly than a mad dog's tooth.
target: The venom clamors of a jealous woman Poisons more deadly than a mad dog's tooth .

input: He says his meat was sauced with upbraidings.
target: Thou sayst his meat was sauced with thy upbraidings .

input: His sports were hampered by the brawls.
target: Thou sayest his sports were hinderd by thy brawls .

input: In food, in sport, and life-preserving rest, would be mad or man or beast.
target: In food , in sport , and life-preserving rest To be disturbed , would mad or man or beast .

input: The husband was scared of the use of wits because of his jealous fits.
target: The consequence is , then , thy jealous fits Have scared thy husband from the use of wits .

input: Good people should enter and hold him.
target: Good people , enter and lay hold on him .

input: Allow your servants to bring my husband with them.
target: Then let your servants bring my husband forth .

input: A charitable duty of my order is the branch and parcel of my oath.
target: It is a branch and parcel of mine oath , A charitable duty of my order .

input: Leave him here with me so that I can take care of him.
target: Therefore depart and leave him here with me .

input: You should be quiet and leave.
target: Be quiet and depart .

input: Don't have him, Thou shalt not.
target: Thou shalt not have him .

input: The Duke of this indignity, please complain.
target: Complain unto the Duke of this indignity .

input: Go, come, come.
target: Come , go .

input: I will fall prostrate at his feet, and never rise until my tears and prayers have been fulfilled.
target: I will fall prostrate at his feet And never rise until my tears and prayers Have won his grace to come in person hither And take perforce my husband from the Abbess .

input: I think the dial points at five by this.
target: By this , I think , the dial points at five .

input: To see a reverend who put unluckily into this bay against the laws and statutes of this town and beheaded publicly for his offense.
target: To see a reverend Syracusian merchant , Who put unluckily into this bay Against the laws and statutes of this town , Beheaded publicly for his offense .

input: You can see where they come.
target: See where they come .

input: He will die and we will see it.
target: We will behold his death .

input: Before the duke passes the abbey, he should kneel to the duke.
target: Kneel to the duke before he pass the abbey .

input: If any friend will pay the sum for him, he will not die, so much so that we tender him.
target: Yet once again proclaim it publicly , If any friend will pay the sum for him , He shall not die ; so much we tender him .

input: Justice, the most sacred duke, was against the Abbess.
target: Justice , most sacred duke , against the Abbess .

input: She is both a reverend and a virtue.
target: She is a virtuous and a reverend lady .

input: It is not possible that she did the wrong thing.
target: It can not be that she hath done thee wrong .

input: Let him be brought forth and given help because of the commands of the most gracious duke.
target: Therefore , most gracious duke , with thy command Let him be brought forth and borne hence for help .

input: I to thee engaged a prince's word when I heard that my husband had served me in my wars. To do him all the grace and good I could do.
target: Long since thy husband served me in my wars , And I to thee engaged a prince's word , When thou didst make him master of thy bed , To do him all the grace and good I could .

input: It's peace, it's fool.
target: Peace , fool .

input: It is false to say that the master and his man are here.
target: Thy master and his man are here , And that is false thou dost report to us .

input: I tell you the truth when I am alive.
target: Mistress , upon my life I tell you true .

input: Since I saw it, I have not breathed a word.
target: I have not breathed almost since I did see it .

input: If he can take you, he will burn your face and make you look like a pig.
target: He cries for you , and vows , if he can take you , To scorch your face and to disfigure you .

input: I think it is my husband.
target: Ay me , it is my husband .

input: You can witness that he is invisible.
target: Witness you That he is borne about invisible .

input: We housed him in the abbey, and now he is there, past thought of human reason.
target: Even now we housed him in the abbey here , And now he's there , past thought of human reason .

input: I lost my life for thee, now I have justice.
target: Even for the blood That then I lost for thee , now grant me justice .

input: She this day threw me off balance, beyond imagination is the wrong thing to do.
target: Beyond imagination is the wrong That she this day hath shameless thrown on me .

input: She closed the doors upon me while she feasted in my house.
target: This day , great duke , she shut the doors upon me While she with harlots feasted in my house .

input: Do you think a grievous fault was done?
target: A grievous fault. , Say , woman , didst thou so ?

input: No, my good lord.
target: No , my good lord .

input: My sister and myself did dine together.
target: Myself , he , and my sister Today did dine together .

input: This is false and he burdens me with it.
target: So befall my soul As this is false he burdens me withal .

input: She tells to your Highness that Ne'er may not look on day or night.
target: Ne'er may I look on day , nor sleep on night But she tells to your Highness simple truth .

input: The woman perjured herself.
target: O perjured woman !

input: My liege, I am advised what I say, neither disturbed with the effect of wine, nor heady-rash, provoked with raging ire, but my wrongs might make one smarter mad.
target: My liege , I am advised what I say , Neither disturbed with the effect of wine , Nor heady-rash , provoked with raging ire , Albeit my wrongs might make one wiser mad .

input: The goldsmith was with me when I went to fetch a chain, but he was not packed with her, so he could not witness it.
target: That goldsmith there , were he not packed with her , Could witness it , for he was with me then , Who parted with me to go fetch a chain , Promising to bring it to the Porpentine , Where Balthasar and I did dine together .

input: I went to look for him after dinner because he was not coming.
target: Our dinner done and he not coming thither , I went to seek him .

input: I met him in the street and he was with a gentleman.
target: In the street I met him , And in his company that gentleman .

input: By the way, we met my wife, her sister, and more of the vile confederates.
target: By th ' way we met My wife , her sister , and a rabble more Of vile confederates .

input: They brought a Pinch, a lean-faced villain, a mountebank, a threadbare juggler, and a fortune-teller with them.
target: Along with them They brought one Pinch , a hungry , lean-faced villain , A mere anatomy , a mountebank , A threadbare juggler , and a fortune-teller , A needy , hollow-eyed , sharp-looking wretch , A living dead man .

input: Forsooth took on him as a conjurer, and he looked in my eyes and felt my pulse.
target: This pernicious slave , Forsooth , took on him as a conjurer , And , gazing in mine eyes , feeling my pulse ,

input: Did he have such a chain of thee or not?
target: But had he such a chain of thee or no ?

input: He had, my lord, and when he ran in here, these people saw the chain around his neck.
target: He had , my lord , and when he ran in here , These people saw the chain about his neck .

input: I didn't see the chain, so help me, and this is false, you burden me withal.
target: I never saw the chain , so help me heaven , And this is false you burden me withal .

input: What an intricate impeachment is this?
target: Why , what an intricate impeach is this !

input: I'll meet with you at five o'clock, and then I'll consort with you until the next morning.
target: Soon at five o'clock , Please you , I'll meet with you upon the mart And afterward consort you till bedtime .

input: My current business is calling me from you.
target: My present business calls me from you now .

input: Until then, farewell till then.
target: Farewell till then .

input: I am going to wander up and down to see the city.
target: I will go lose myself And wander up and down to view the city .

input: Sir, I am very pleased with your own content.
target: Sir , I commend you to your own content .

input: He commends me to the thing I can't get, and he also commends me to my own content.
target: He that commends me to mine own content Commends me to the thing I can not get .

input: I to the world is like a drop of water, Who falls there to find his fellow, Unseen, inquisitive, and he confounds himself.
target: I to the world am like a drop of water That in the ocean seeks another drop , Who , falling there to find his fellow forth , Unseen , inquisitive , confounds himself .

input: I wanted to find a mother and a brother, but I lost myself in the process.
target: So I , to find a mother and a brother , In quest of them , unhappy , lose myself .

input: How much chance do you have that art will come back soon?
target: How chance thou art returned so soon ?

input: Returned in a few days?
target: Returned so soon ?

input: Rather approach was too late.
target: Rather approach'd too late !

input: The pig falls from the spit, the capon burns, the clock strikes twelve upon the bell, and my mistress made it one upon my cheek.
target: The capon burns ; the pig falls from the spit ; The clock hath strucken twelve upon the bell ; My mistress made it one upon my cheek .

input: You say he ate at home, but the goldsmith says otherwise.
target: You say he dined at home ; the goldsmith here Denies that saying .

input: Sir, he had dinner with her at the Porpentine.
target: Sir , he dined with her there , at the Porpentine .

input: He snatched that ring from my finger.
target: He did , and from my finger snatched that ring .

input: This ring I had of her is true, my liege.
target: Tis true , my liege ; this ring I had of her .

input: Did you see him enter at the abbey?
target: Saw'st thou him enter at the abbey here ?

input: As I see your Grace, my liege is as sure.
target: As sure , my liege , as I do see your Grace .

input: I think that you are all mad.
target: I think you are all mated or stark mad .

input: vouchsafe me speak a word, the most mighty duke.
target: Most mighty duke , vouchsafe me speak a word .

input: I see that a friend will save my life and pay the sum that will deliver me.
target: Haply I see a friend will save my life And pay the sum that may deliver me .

input: Within this hour, I was his bondman, but he gnawed on two of my cords.
target: Within this hour I was his bondman sir , But he , I thank him , gnawed in two my cords .

input: I Dromio, and his man, are unbound.
target: Now am I Dromio , and his man , unbound .

input: I am sure you both remember me, I am sure.
target: I am sure you both of you remember me .

input: You are not a patient of Pinch, are you?
target: You are not Pinch's patient , are you , sir ?

input: Why don't you look normal on me.
target: Why look you strange on me ?

input: You know I'm well known to you.
target: you know me well .

input: I haven't seen you in a long time.
target: I never saw you in my life till now .

input: Since you saw me last, grief has changed me, and time has written strange de features in my face.
target: O , grief hath changed me since you saw me last , And careful hours with time's deformed hand Have written strange defeatures in my face .

input: Do you not know what my voice is?
target: But tell me yet , dost thou not know my voice ?

input: Neither is that correct.
target: Neither .

input: Is Dromio or Thou the same?
target: Dromio , nor thou ?

input: Trust me, sir, and I. I am sure of it.
target: No , trust me , sir , nor I. I am sure thou dost .

input: I don't know what my voice is.
target: Not know my voice !

input: In seven short years, my only son knows not my feeble key of untuned cares, as I have cracked and split my poor tongue.
target: O time's extremity , Hast thou so crack'd and splitted my poor tongue In seven short years that here my only son Knows not my feeble key of untuned cares ?

input: I hid my face in the snow because it was so cold, but I didn't have a good night's sleep because my lamps were fading.
target: Though now this grained face of mine be hid In sap-consuming winter's drizzled snow , And all the conduits of my blood froze up , Yet hath my night of life some memory , My wasting lamps some fading glimmer left , My dull deaf ears a little use to hear .

input: My son Antipholus is one of these old witnesses, I can not let him down.
target: All these old witnesses , I can not err , Tell me thou art my son Antipholus .

input: I have never seen my father in my life.
target: I never saw my father in my life .

input: We parted seven years ago, boy, Thou know'st we parted.
target: But seven years since , in Syracusa , boy , Thou know'st we parted .

input: I can see that age and dangers make thee dote.
target: I see thy age and dangers make thee dote .

input: Most mighty duke, see a man that's been wronged.
target: Most mighty duke , behold a man much wronged .

input: My eyes deceive me, I see two husbands or both.
target: I see two husbands , or mine eyes deceive me .

input: My name is Dromio and I am sir.
target: I , sir , am Dromio .

input: He should be commanded away.
target: Command him away .

input: My name is Dromio and I am sir.
target: I , sir , am Dromio .

input: Let me stay and please.
target: Please , let me stay .

input: My old master, who bound him here?
target: O , my old master. , Who hath bound him here ?

input: I will loose my bonds and gain a husband by his liberty if the man is bound.
target: Whoever bound him , I will loose his bonds And gain a husband by his liberty. , Speak , old Egeon , if thou be'st the man That hadst a wife once called Emilia , That bore thee at a burden two fair sons .

input: If you are the same Egeon, speak and speak unto the same Emilia.
target: O , if thou be'st the same Egeon , speak , And speak unto the same Emilia .

input: These two Antipholuses, these two so like, and these two Dromios, one in semblance, besides her urging of her wreck at sea, these are the parents to these children, which accidentally are.
target: Why , here begins his morning story right ; These two Antipholuses , these two so like , And these two Dromios , one in semblance , Besides her urging of her wreck at sea , These are the parents to these children , Which accidentally are met together .

input: If I don't dream about it, you know what I mean.
target: If I dream not , thou art Emilia .

input: I want to know where the son that floated with thee on the fatal raft was.
target: If thou art she , tell me where is that son That floated with thee on the fatal raft ?

input: The first person to be born in Corinth.
target: Corinth first .

input: Stand apart, stay together.
target: Stay , stand apart .

input: I do not know which is which.
target: I know not which is which .

input: My most gracious lord was born from Corinth.
target: I came from Corinth , my most gracious lord .

input: I have him with me.
target: And I with him .

input: Duke Menaphon, your most renowned uncle, brought this town with him.
target: Brought to this town by that most famous warrior Duke Menaphon , your most renowned uncle .

input: Which of you two had a meal with me today?
target: Which of you two did dine with me today ?

input: I was a gentle mistress.
target: I , gentle mistress .

input: And are you my husband, too?
target: And are not you my husband ?

input: That is the chain, sir, which you had of me.
target: That is the chain , sir , which you had of me .

input: I think it will be, sir.
target: I think it be , sir .

input: I don't deny that.
target: I deny it not .

input: I was arrested by this chain, sir.
target: And you , sir , for this chain arrested me .

input: I believe I did, sir.
target: I think I did , sir .

input: I don't deny that.
target: I deny it not .

input: I sent you money to be your bail, but I think Dromio didn't bring it.
target: I sent you money , sir , to be your bail By Dromio , but I think he brought it not .

input: No, none by me.
target: No , none by me .

input: Dromio brought me the purse of ducats that I received from you.
target: This purse of ducats I received from you , And Dromio my man did bring them me .

input: These ducats are used to pawn for my father.
target: These ducats pawn I for my father here .

input: It won't need anything.
target: It shall not need .

input: His life was cut short by his father.
target: Thy father hath his life .

input: I need that diamond from you, Sir.
target: Sir , I must have that diamond from you .

input: Thanks for my good cheer, there, take it.
target: There , take it ; and much thanks for my good cheer .

input: Renowned duke vouchsafe to take the pains to go with us into the abbey here and hear all our fortunes, and all that are assembled in this place that have suffered wrong.
target: Renowned duke , vouchsafe to take the pains To go with us into the abbey here And hear at large discoursed all our fortunes , And all that are assembled in this place That by this sympathized one day's error Have suffered wrong .

input: Thirty-three years have passed, and we shall make full satisfaction. The Duke, my husband, and my sons.
target: Go , keep us company , And we shall make full satisfaction. , Thirty-three years have I but gone in travail Of you , my sons , and till this present hour My heavy burden ne'er delivered. , The Duke , my husband , and my children both , And you , the calendars of their nativity , Go to a gossips ' feast , and go with me .

input: After a long time of grief, such a nativity!
target: After so long grief , such nativity !

input: I'll gossip at this feast, with all my heart.
target: With all my heart I'll gossip at this feast .

input: Dromio, what are the things that you have embarked on?
target: Dromio , what stuff of mine hast thou embarked ?

input: Your goods were located at the host in the Centaur.
target: Your goods that lay at host , sir , in the Centaur .

input: Dromio, I am your master, he speaks to me.
target: He speaks to me. , I am your master , Dromio .

input: There is a fat friend at your master's house, that kitchened me for you today at dinner.
target: There is a fat friend at your master's house That kitchened me for you today at dinner .

input: She will be my sister instead of my wife.
target: She now shall be my sister , not my wife .

input: I see by you I am a sweet-faced youth, and I think you are my glass, and not my brother.
target: Methinks you are my glass , and not my brother : I see by you I am a sweet-faced youth .

input: Will you walk in to see what's happening?
target: Will you walk in to see their gossiping ?

input: I am not, sir.
target: Not I , sir .

input: You are my older sibling.
target: You are my elder .

input: That is a question.
target: That's a question .

input: How will we attempt to use it?
target: How shall we try it ?

input: We will draw the cuts for the signior.
target: We'll draw cuts for the signior .

input: Lead first, until then.
target: Till then , lead thou first .

input: We came into the world like brother and brother, and now let's go hand in hand, not one before another.
target: Nay , then , thus : We came into the world like brother and brother , And now let's go hand in hand , not one before another .

input: Stop in your wind, sir.
target: Stop in your wind , sir .

input: I want to know where the money that I gave you has gone.
target: Tell me this , I pray : Where have you left the money that I gave you ?

input: I had sixpence on Wednesday last to pay the saddler for my mistress.
target: O , sixpence , that I had o ' Wednesday last To pay the saddler for my mistress ' crupper ?

input: The saddler had it, but I kept it away from him.
target: The saddler had it , sir ; I kept it not .

input: I am no longer in a sportive humor now.
target: I am not in a sportive humor now .

input: Tell me where the money is, and don't tell me.
target: Tell me , and dally not : where is the money ?

input: How do you trust a charge from your own custody, we are strangers here?
target: We being strangers here , how dar'st thou trust So great a charge from thine own custody ?

input: I am praying for you as you sit down for dinner.
target: I pray you , jest , sir , as you sit at dinner .

input: Me thinks that your maw should be your clock, and strike you home without a messenger.
target: Methinks your maw , like mine , should be your clock , And strike you home without a messenger .

input: Come, Dromio, these jests are out of season.
target: Come , Dromio , come , these jests are out of season .

input: Reserve them until an hour is more than this.
target: Reserve them till a merrier hour than this .

input: Where is the gold I gave to the person?
target: Where is the gold I gave in charge to thee ?

input: To me, sir, what do you think?
target: To me , sir ?

input: Why did you not give me any gold?
target: Why , you gave no gold to me !

input: Come on, sir knave, have done your foolishness, and tell me how you have dealt with the charge.
target: Come on , sir knave , have done your foolishness , And tell me how thou hast disposed thy charge .

input: My charge was to get you from the home to the Phoenix for dinner.
target: My charge was but to fetch you from the mart Home to your house , the Phoenix , sir , to dinner .

input: My mistress and her sister are staying with you.
target: My mistress and her sister stays for you .

input: As I am a Christian, I want to know what safe place you have given me my money in, or I will break that merry sconce of yours.
target: Now , as I am a Christian , answer me In what safe place you have bestowed my money , Or I shall break that merry sconce of yours That stands on tricks when I am undisposed .

input: Where are the thousand marks that I had?
target: Where is the thousand marks thou hadst of me ?

input: Is the mistress marks something?
target: Thy mistress ' marks ?

input: What is the relationship between the mistress and the slave.
target: what mistress , slave , hast thou ?

input: What do you think about it, being forbid, and flouting me thus unto my face?
target: What , wilt thou flout me thus unto my face , Being forbid ?

input: Take you that, sir, there.
target: There , take you that , sir knave .

input: What does it mean to you, sir?
target: What mean you , sir ?

input: Hold your hands for the sake of God.
target: For God's sake , hold your hands .

input: I'll take my heels, an you will not.
target: Nay , an you will not , sir , I'll take my heels .

input: All my money is taken away by the villain when I'm in my life.
target: Upon my life , by some device or other The villain is o'erraught of all my money .

input: They say that this town is full of jugglers that deceive the eye, dark-working sorcerers that change the mind, and many other things.
target: They say this town is full of cozenage , As nimble jugglers that deceive the eye , Dark-working sorcerers that change the mind , Soul-killing witches that deform the body , Disguised cheaters , prating mountebanks , And many suchlike liberties of sin .

input: I sent to seek his master, but neither my husband nor the slave came back.
target: Neither my husband nor the slave returned That in such haste I sent to seek his master ?

input: It is two o'clock, Luciana.
target: Sure , Luciana , it is two o'clock .

input: Maybe some merchant invited him, and from the mart he's somewhere to dinner.
target: Perhaps some merchant hath invited him , And from the mart he's somewhere gone to dinner .

input: Good sister, let us eat and not worry.
target: Good sister , let us dine and never fret .

input: When they see time, they'll either go or come, because a man is master of his liberty.
target: A man is master of his liberty ; Time is their master , and when they see time They'll go or come .

input: Sister, be patient if that is the case.
target: If so , be patient , sister .

input: Why should they have more freedom than we do?
target: Why should their liberty than ours be more ?

input: Because their business is still located out of the door.
target: Because their business still lies out o ' door .

input: Why does headstrong liberty get lashed with woe?
target: Why , headstrong liberty is lashed with woe .

input: Allow your will to attend on their accords.
target: Then let your will attend on their accords .

input: You have to keep unwed because of this servitude.
target: This servitude makes you to keep unwed .

input: The troubles of the marriage bed were not this.
target: Not this , but troubles of the marriage bed .

input: But if you were married, you would have some influence.
target: But , were you wedded , you would bear some sway .

input: I will practice to obey as I learn love.
target: Ere I learn love , I'll practice to obey .

input: How do you know if your husband is going to start somewhere else?
target: How if your husband start some otherwhere ?

input: I would not be happy if he came home again.
target: Till he come home again , I would forbear .

input: It was unmoved by patience.
target: Patience unmoved !

input: They can be meek because they have no other cause.
target: No marvel though she pause ; They can be meek that have no other cause .

input: We try to be quiet when we hear it cry, but we should complain as much as we can because of the weight of pain on us.
target: A wretched soul , bruised with adversity We bid be quiet when we hear it cry , But were we burdened with like weight of pain , As much or more we should ourselves complain .

input: If that hast no unkind mate to grieve thee, with urging helpless patience would relieve me, but this foolish patience in thee will be left behind.
target: So thou , that hast no unkind mate to grieve thee , With urging helpless patience would relieve me ; But , if thou live to see like right bereft , This fool-begged patience in thee will be left .

input: I will marry one day, but I need to try.
target: Well , I will marry one day , but to try .

input: Do you know if your tardy master is at hand?
target: Say , is your tardy master now at hand ?

input: Do you know his mind?
target: Know'st thou his mind ?

input: I want to know if he is coming home.
target: But say , I prithee , is he coming home ?

input: He seems to care a lot about pleasing his wife.
target: It seems he hath great care to please his wife .

input: My master is horn mad, mistress.
target: Why , mistress , sure my master is horn mad .

input: Horn mad and the villain.
target: Horn mad , thou villain !

input: He is stark mad, I mean not cuckold mad, but sure.
target: I mean not cuckold mad , But sure he is stark mad .

input: My mistress, sir, " quoth I."
target: My mistress , sir , " quoth I .

input: Don't let your mistress hang up you.
target: Hang up thy mistress !

input: My master is Quoth me.
target: Quoth my master .

input: "No house, no wife, no mistress, I bare home upon my shoulders, for he did beat me there." So that my errand, due unto my tongue, I thank him.
target: I know , " quoth he , "no house , no wife , no mistress." So that my errand , due unto my tongue , I thank him , I bare home upon my shoulders , For , in conclusion , he did beat me there .

input: Go back again, and get him home.
target: Go back again , thou slave , and fetch him home .

input: Is it possible to go back again and be a new beaten home?
target: Go back again and be new beaten home ?

input: For God's sake, send another messenger.
target: For God's sake , send some other messenger .

input: I will break the pate across the back of the slave.
target: Back , slave , or I will break thy pate across .

input: Prating peasant is what it was.
target: Hence , prating peasant !

input: Don't let your master home go to waste.
target: Fetch thy master home .

input: He will spurn me hither because you spurn me.
target: You spurn me hence , and he will spurn me hither .

input: If I last in this service, you have to put me in leather.
target: If I last in this service , you must case me in leather .

input: How impatient you are in your face, Fie.
target: Fie , how impatience loureth in your face .

input: I must starve at home for a merry look while his company does his grace.
target: His company must do his minions grace , Whilst I at home starve for a merry look .

input: From my poor cheek, the attractive beauty took from my age.
target: Hath homely age th ' alluring beauty took From my poor cheek ?

input: Is it possible to barren my wit.
target: Barren my wit ?

input: A sunny look of his decayed body would soon be fixed.
target: My decayed fair A sunny look of his would soon repair .

input: He feeds from home because he is too unruly a deer.
target: But , too unruly deer , he breaks the pale And feeds from home .

input: I am poor, but he is still young.
target: Poor I am but his stale .

input: Beat it because of self-harming jealousy, fie.
target: Self-harming jealousy , fie , beat it hence .

input: I know his eye doth homage, but what if he would not be here?
target: I know his eye doth homage otherwhere , Or else what lets it but he would be here ?

input: You know he promised me a chain.
target: Sister , you know he promised me a chain .

input: He would keep fair quarter with his bed if that was what he wanted.
target: Would that alone o ' love he would detain , So he would keep fair quarter with his bed .

input: Will will lose his beauty if I see the jewel best enameled.
target: I see the jewel best enameled Will lose his beauty .

input: The gold is still being bid, even though others touch, and often touching, will Wear gold.
target: Yet the gold bides still That others touch , and often touching will Wear gold ; yet no man that hath a name By falsehood and corruption doth it shame .

input: Since that my beauty can't please him, I'll weep and die.
target: Since that my beauty can not please his eye , I'll weep what's left away , and weeping die .

input: How many people serve jealousy.
target: How many fond fools serve mad jealousy !

input: Proceed, Solinus, to procure my fall, and by the doom of death end troubles.
target: Proceed , Solinus , to procure my fall , And by the doom of death end woes and all .

input: To admit no traffic to our adverse towns has been ordered by the seditious countrymen and ourselves.
target: For , since the mortal and intestine jars 'Twixt thy seditious countrymen and us , It hath in solemn synods been decreed Both by the Syracusians and ourselves , To admit no traffic to our adverse towns .

input: He dies if he comes to the bay of Ephesus, his goods will be taken by the Duke's dispose.
target: Nay , more , if any born at Ephesus Be seen at any Syracusian marts and fairs ; Again , if any Syracusian born Come to the bay of Ephesus , he dies , His goods confiscate to the Duke's dispose , Unless a thousand marks be levied To quit the penalty and to ransom him .

input: It is against the law for a substance to be valued at the highest rate and not to be worth a hundred marks.
target: Thy substance , valued at the highest rate , Can not amount unto a hundred marks ; Therefore by law thou art condemned to die .

input: The gold I gave to Dromio is in a safe at the Centaur, and the slave is trying to find me.
target: The gold I gave to Dromio is laid up Safe at the Centaur , and the heedful slave Is wandered forth , in care to seek me out .

input: I was unable to speak with Dromio since I sent him from the mart.
target: By computation and mine host's report , I could not speak with Dromio since at first I sent him from the mart .

input: See, here he arrives.
target: See , here he comes .

input: How are you now, sir?
target: How now , sir ?

input: Is your humor still merry?
target: is your merry humor altered ?

input: You don't know about the Centaur?
target: You know no Centaur ?

input: You did not receive any gold.
target: You received no gold ?

input: Your mistress was supposed to have me home to dinner.
target: Your mistress sent to have me home to dinner ?

input: The house was in the Phoenix.
target: My house was at the Phoenix ?

input: Was it because he was so mad that he answered me so madly?
target: Wast thou mad , That thus so madly thou didst answer me ?

input: What is the answer, sir?
target: What answer , sir ?

input: When spake I am such a word.
target: When spake I such a word ?

input: Since you sent me to the Centaur with the gold you gave me, I did not see you again.
target: I did not see you since you sent me hence , Home to the Centaur with the gold you gave me .

input: I was displeased when I was told of a mistress and a dinner, but I did not deny the gold's receipt.
target: Villain , thou didst deny the gold's receipt And told'st me of a mistress and a dinner , For which , I hope , thou felt'st I was displeased .

input: You are in this merry vein, I am happy to see you.
target: I am glad to see you in this merry vein .

input: This is a jest, what does it mean?
target: What means this jest ?

input: I am praying for you, master, to let me know.
target: I pray you , master , tell me ?

input: Do you think it would be a good idea to violate me in the teeth.
target: Yea , dost thou jeer and flout me in the teeth ?

input: Think of the first thing I said.
target: Think'st thou I jest ?

input: Take that and that, hold it.
target: Hold , take thou that and that .

input: For God's sake, hold, sir.
target: Hold , sir , for God's sake !

input: Your jest is serious now.
target: Now your jest is earnest .

input: What bargain do you offer me?
target: Upon what bargain do you give it me ?

input: You will make a common of my serious hours if you use me for my fool and chat with you.
target: Because that I familiarly sometimes Do use you for my fool and chat with you , Your sauciness will jest upon my love And make a common of my serious hours .

input: Do you want to call it "Scon"?
target: Sconce" call you it ?

input: Shall I tell you what happened?
target: Shall I tell you why ?

input: I would like to thank you.
target: Well , sir , I thank you .

input: For this thing that you gave me for nothing, sir, I'm going to marry you.
target: Marry , sir , for this something that you gave me for nothing .

input: To give you nothing for something, I'll make you apologize next.
target: I'll make you amends next , to give you nothing for something .

input: But say, sir, is it dinnertime?
target: But say , sir , is it dinnertime ?

input: In good time, sir, what is that?
target: In good time , sir , what's that ?

input: Basting is a crime.
target: Basting .

input: Well, sir, then it will be dry.
target: Well , sir , then 'twill be dry .

input: If it is, I want you to eat nothing of it.
target: If it be , sir , I pray you , eat none of it .

input: Are you the one with your reason?
target: Your reason ?

input: Purchase me another dry basting and I will make you choleric.
target: Lest it make you choleric and purchase me another dry basting .

input: Well, sir, learn to laugh in good time.
target: Well , sir , learn to jest in good time .

input: There is a time for everything.
target: There's a time for all things .

input: I denied that before you were so choleric.
target: I durst have denied that before you were so choleric .

input: By what rule, sir?
target: By what rule , sir ?

input: Marry, sir, by a rule as simple as the bald pate of Father Time himself.
target: Marry , sir , by a rule as plain as the plain bald pate of Father Time himself .

input: Let's talk about it.
target: Let's hear it .

input: There isn't time for a man to recover his hair that is bald by nature.
target: There's no time for a man to recover his hair that grows bald by nature .

input: Time is a niggard of hair, as it is, so plentiful an excrement.
target: Why is Time such a niggard of hair , being , as it is , so plentiful an excrement ?

input: There's a lot of a man with more hair than wit.
target: Why , but there's many a man hath more hair than wit .

input: Why do you conclude hairy men plain dealers without wit?
target: Why , thou didst conclude hairy men plain dealers without wit .

input: What is the reason for it?
target: For what reason ?

input: It's for two and sound ones too.
target: For two , and sound ones too .

input: I pray you don't sound like that.
target: Nay , not sound , I pray you .

input: Sure ones, then.
target: Sure ones , then .

input: Not sure, in a thing that is not true.
target: Nay , not sure , in a thing falsing .

input: Then there are certain ones.
target: Certain ones , then .

input: They should be named.
target: Name them .

input: To save the money that he spends in tiring, and the other, that they should not eat his breakfast at dinner.
target: The one , to save the money that he spends in tiring ; the other , that at dinner they should not drop in his porridge .

input: You would have proved that there is no time for everything.
target: You would all this time have proved there is no time for all things .

input: To the world's end, Time will have bald followers, because he is bald.
target: Thus I mend it : Time himself is bald and therefore , to the world's end , will have bald followers .

input: The time was once when you could never say anything that wasn't music to your ear, that you couldn't touch anything that wasn't pleasing to the eye, and that you couldn't eat anything that wasn't sweet-savored in your taste.
target: The time was once when thou unurged wouldst vow That never words were music to thine ear , That never object pleasing in thine eye , That never touch well welcome to thy hand , That never meat sweet-savored in thy taste , Unless I spake , or looked , or touched , or carved to thee .

input: How comes it now, my husband, how comes it that he doesn't know anything about it?
target: How comes it now , my husband , O , how comes it That thou art thus estranged from thyself ?

input: Do not let yourself be taken away from me!
target: Ah , do not tear away thyself from me !

input: I know that you don't.
target: I know you not .

input: When was the last time you used my sister?
target: When were you wont to use my sister thus ?

input: Dromio sent her for you to dinner.
target: She sent for you by Dromio home to dinner .

input: By Dromio.
target: By Dromio ?

input: He denied my house for his wife and buffeted thee in his blows, and returned from him.
target: By thee ; and this thou didst return from him : That he did buffet thee and , in his blows , Denied my house for his , me for his wife .

input: Did you speak with this gentlewoman?
target: Did you converse , sir , with this gentlewoman ?

input: What is the course and drift of your compact?
target: What is the course and drift of your compact ?

input: I, sir, what are you talking about?
target: I , sir ?

input: I have never seen her before this time.
target: I never saw her till this time .

input: For even her very words Didst Thou deliver to me on the mart, the Villain.
target: Villain , thou liest ; for even her very words Didst thou deliver to me on the mart .

input: I have never had a relationship with her in my life.
target: I never spake with her in all my life .

input: I wondered if I married her in my dream.
target: What , was I married to her in my dream ?

input: I think I hear all this, so I might as well sleep now.
target: Or sleep I now and think I hear all this ?

input: What is the cause of our eyes and ears not hearing something?
target: What error drives our eyes and ears amiss ?

input: I'll entertain the offered fallacy until I know this is sure uncertainty.
target: Until I know this sure uncertainty I'll entertain the offered fallacy .

input: Dromio, go for the servants spread for dinner.
target: Dromio , go bid the servants spread for dinner .

input: For my beads, for sure!
target: O , for my beads !

input: I cross myself for a bad person.
target: I cross me for a sinner .

input: This is the land of the fairies.
target: This is the fairy land .

input: O spite of things that are not good.
target: O spite of spites !

input: They'll suck our breath if we don't obey them, or they'll pinch us black and blue.
target: We talk with goblins , owls , and sprites : If we obey them not , this will ensue : They'll suck our breath , or pinch us black and blue .

input: Why did you not answer to yourself and why did you not do so?
target: Why prat'st thou to thyself and answer'st not ?

input: Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Dromio, Drom
target: Dromio , thou , Dromio , thou snail , thou slug , thou sot .

input: I am transformed, master, but am I not?
target: I am transformed , master , am I not ?

input: I think I am both in mind and in my shape.
target: I think thou art in mind , and so am I. Nay , master , both in mind and in my shape .

input: It is true.
target: Tis true .

input: I should know her as well as she knows me because I am an ass.
target: I am an ass ; else it could never be But I should know her as well as she knows me .

input: No longer will I be a fool, I will put the finger in the eye and weep, man and laugh my troubles to repentance.
target: Come , come , no longer will I be a fool , To put the finger in the eye and weep Whilst man and master laugh my woes to scorn .

input: Sir, come to dinner. Dromio, keep the gate.
target: Come , sir , to dinner. , Dromio , keep the gate .

input: I'll dine above with you today, and give you a thousand prank ideas.
target: Husband , I'll dine above with you today , And shrive you of a thousand idle pranks .

input: I don't know if I am in heaven or in hell.
target: Am I in earth , in heaven , or in hell ?

input: To myself, known unto these and to myself hiding.
target: Known unto these , and to myself disguised !

input: Is it possible that I will be a porter at the gate.
target: Master , shall I be porter at the gate ?

input: I will break your pate if you don't let none enter.
target: Ay ; and let none enter , lest I break your pate .

input: Why did you come to Ephesus from your native home, and what is the reason?
target: Well , Syracusian , say in brief the cause Why thou dep-artedst from thy native home And for what cause thou camest to Ephesus .

input: I was born in Syracusa and married Unto a woman who was happy, but for me.
target: In Syracusa was I born , and wed Unto a woman happy but for me , And by me , had not our hap been bad .

input: In the selfsame inn, a meaner woman was delivered Of such a burden, male twins, both alike.
target: That very hour , and in the selfsame inn , A meaner woman was delivered Of such a burden , male twins , both alike .

input: I agreed, but not without resistance.
target: Unwilling , I agreed .

input: Too soon, we came aboard.
target: Alas , too soon We came aboard .

input: Good signior, you must excuse us all, my wife is not happy when I am not working.
target: Good Signior Angelo , you must excuse us all ; My wife is shrewish when I keep not hours .

input: You will bring her carcanet home tomorrow, because I lingered with you at your shop to see the making of her carcanet.
target: Say that I lingered with you at your shop To see the making of her carcanet , And that tomorrow you will bring it home .

input: He met me on the mart, and that I beat him, and charged him with a thousand marks in gold, and that I did not allow my wife and house.
target: But here's a villain that would face me down He met me on the mart , and that I beat him And charged him with a thousand marks in gold , And that I did deny my wife and house. , Thou drunkard , thou , what didst thou mean by this ?

input: Say what you will, sir, but I know what you're saying.
target: Say what you will , sir , but I know what I know .

input: I think he is an artist.
target: I think thou art an ass .

input: You are sad, Signior Balthasar.
target: You're sad , Signior Balthasar .

input: I hold your dainties cheap, sir, and your welcome dear.
target: I hold your dainties cheap , sir , and your welcome dear .

input: Good meat is common, sir, that every churl affords.
target: Good meat , sir , is common ; that every churl affords .

input: For that's nothing but words, and welcome more common.
target: And welcome more common , for that's nothing but words .

input: A merry feast is made when small cheer and great welcome are present.
target: Small cheer and great welcome makes a merry feast .

input: To a niggardly host and a more sparing guest.
target: Ay , to a niggardly host and more sparing guest .

input: Take my cats in good part, even though they are mean.
target: But though my cates be mean , take them in good part .

input: Better cheer may be good, but not with a better heart.
target: Better cheer may you have , but not with better heart .

input: But soft, but!
target: But soft !

input: I have a door that is lock'd.
target: My door is lock'd .

input: Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian, Marian.
target: Maud , Bridget , Marian , Ciceley , Gillian , Ginn !

input: My master is not in the house.
target: My master stays in the street .

input: Who is talking within there?
target: Who talks within there ?

input: The door should be open.
target: Ho , open the door .

input: Wherefore, wherefore?
target: Wherefore ?

input: For my supper.
target: For my dinner .

input: I have not eaten today.
target: I have not dined today .

input: What art keeps me out of the house that I owe?
target: What art thou that keep'st me out from the house I owe ?

input: My office and my name have been stolen by the villain.
target: O villain , thou hast stolen both mine office and my name !

input: O Lord, I have to laugh.
target: O Lord , I must laugh .

input: Do you have a proverb that says, "Shall I set in my staff"?
target: Have at you with a proverb : shall I set in my staff ?

input: You minion, do you hear anything?
target: Do you hear , you minion ?

input: You'll let us in, I hope so.
target: You'll let us in , I hope ?

input: So, come and help.
target: So , come , help .

input: Well struck, well struck!
target: Well struck !

input: There was a blow for blow.
target: There was blow for blow .

input: Let me in with your baggage.
target: Thou baggage , let me in .

input: Master, knock the door down hard.
target: Master , knock the door hard .

input: If I beat the door down, you will cry for this.
target: You'll cry for this , minion , if I beat the door down .

input: Are you there with your spouse?
target: Are you there , wife ?

input: You might have arrived before that.
target: You might have come before .

input: This knave would go sore if you went in pain, master.
target: If you went in pain , master , this knave would go sore .

input: We will part with either or both in debating which was the best.
target: In debating which was best , we shall part with neither .

input: Master, if your garments were thin, you would say so.
target: You would say so , master , if your garments were thin .

input: You stand here in the cold, but your cake is warm within.
target: Your cake there is warm within ; you stand here in the cold .

input: It would make a man angry that he was being bought and sold.
target: It would make a man mad as a buck to be so bought and sold .

input: I will break the gate if you fetch me something.
target: Go , fetch me something : I'll break ope the gate .

input: Here's too much "out upon thee", let me in.
target: Here's too much "out upon thee ! " I pray thee , let me in .

input: Well, I will break in.
target: Well , I'll break in .

input: Go and borrow a crow.
target: Go , borrow me a crow .

input: A bird without a feather.
target: A crow without feather ?

input: Do you mean you are a master?
target: Master , mean you so ?

input: There is a fowl without a feather for a fish.
target: For a fish without a fin , there's a fowl without a feather. , Go , get thee gone .

input: I'm going to get an iron crow.
target: Fetch me an iron crow .

input: Don't be impatient, sir.
target: Have patience , sir .

input: Let it not be that way.
target: O , let it not be so .

input: She will excuse why the doors are made against you at this time.
target: And doubt not , sir , but she will well excuse Why at this time the doors are made against you .

input: To know the reason of this strange restraint, leave in patience, and let us to the tiger all to dinner, and about evening come yourself alone.
target: Be ruled by me ; depart in patience , And let us to the Tiger all to dinner , And about evening come yourself alone To know the reason of this strange restraint .

input: You have triumphed.
target: You have prevailed .

input: I will leave in a quiet manner, and be merry.
target: I will depart in quiet And , in despite of mirth , mean to be merry .

input: I know a wench of excellent discourse that is pretty and witty, wild and yet gentle.
target: I know a wench of excellent discourse , Pretty and witty , wild and yet , too , gentle .

input: There will be a meal there.
target: There will we dine .

input: I will give that chain to spite my wife and my hostess there.
target: That chain will I bestow , Be it for nothing but to spite my wife , Upon mine hostess there .

input: I'll meet you at that place sometime in the afternoon.
target: I'll meet you at that place some hour hence .

input: Do this.
target: Do so .

input: This jest will cost me some money.
target: This jest shall cost me some expense .

input: Even in the spring of love, shall the love-springs rot?
target: Shall , Antipholus , Even in the spring of love thy love-springs rot ?

input: If you married my sister for her wealth, then use her with more kindness.
target: If you did wed my sister for her wealth , Then for her wealth's sake use her with more kindness .

input: What simple thief brags about his own accomplishments?
target: What simple thief brags of his own attaint ?

input: Let her read it in your bed, because it's double wrong.
target: Tis double wrong to truant with your bed And let her read it in thy looks at board .

input: You may move us if you show us the sleeve and you motion turn.
target: Though others have the arm , show us the sleeve ; We in your motion turn , and you may move us .

input: Get him in again, gentle brother.
target: Then , gentle brother , get you in again .

input: I don't know what your name is, nor do I know what you do hit me with.
target: Sweet mistress , what your name is else I know not , Nor by what wonder you do hit of mine , ,

input: Less in your knowledge and more in your grace, you show more than our earth's Wonder.
target: Less in your knowledge and your grace you show not Than our earth's wonder , more than earth divine .

input: How to think and speak is something I need to be taught.
target: Teach me , dear creature , how to think and speak .

input: Why labour to make it wander in an unknown field, against my soul's pure truth?
target: Against my soul's pure truth why labour you To make it wander in an unknown field ?

input: Do you think you are a god?
target: Are you a god ?

input: Is it possible that you would create me a new thing.
target: would you create me new ?

input: I will yield to your power if you transform me.
target: Transform me , then , and to your power I'll yield .

input: If that is me, I know that your sister is not my wife, nor is her bed a tribute to me.
target: But if that I am I , then well I know Your weeping sister is no wife of mine , Nor to her bed no homage do I owe .

input: I decline more than you do.
target: Far more , far more , to you do I decline .

input: To drown me in her sister's flood of tears, train me not, sweet mermaid.
target: O , train me not , sweet mermaid , with thy note To drown me in thy sister's flood of tears .

input: Are you angry that you do reason so?
target: What , are you mad that you do reason so ?

input: It's a fault that comes out of your eye.
target: It is a fault that springeth from your eye .

input: Being by the fair sun is for gazing on your beams.
target: For gazing on your beams , fair sun , being by .

input: Why do you call me "love"?
target: Why call you me "love" ?

input: My sister should be called so.
target: Call my sister so .

input: The sister of the sister.
target: Thy sister's sister .

input: My sister is that one.
