target: It is gone .

input: If you knew who I gave the ring to, you would conceive for what I gave it. I left the ring when naught would be accepted but the ring.
target: Sweet Portia , If you did know to whom I gave the ring , If you did know for whom I gave the ring , And would conceive for what I gave the ring , And how unwillingly I left the ring When naught would be accepted but the ring , You would abate the strength of your displeasure .

input: You wouldn't have parted with the ring if you had known the virtue of the ring, half her worthiness, or your own honor.
target: If you had known the virtue of the ring , Or half her worthiness that gave the ring , Or your own honor to contain the ring , You would not then have parted with the ring .

input: What to believe is taught to me by Nerissa.
target: Nerissa teaches me what to believe .

input: I'll die for that ring, but some woman had it.
target: I'll die for 't but some woman had the ring .

input: I don't know what to say to the sweet lady.
target: What should I say , sweet lady ?

input: I was told to send it after him.
target: I was enforced to send it after him .

input: I don't want that doctor to come near my house.
target: Let not that doctor e'er come near my house !

input: Since he got the jewel that I loved, and that you swore to keep for me, I will become liberal as well.
target: Since he hath got the jewel that I loved , And that which you did swear to keep for me , I will become as liberal as you .

input: I will not deny him anything I have, not my body, nor my husband's bed.
target: I'll not deny him anything I have , No , not my body , nor my husband's bed .

input: I am sure that he is, and I will know him.
target: Know him I shall , I am well sure of it .

input: It's not a night from home if you lie.
target: Lie not a night from home .

input: You can watch me like an animal.
target: Watch me like Argus .

input: If you don't, I'll have my own doctor for my bedfellow, which is yet my own.
target: If you do not , if I be left alone , Now , by mine honor , which is yet mine own , I'll have that doctor for my bedfellow .

input: I am unhappy about these quarrels.
target: I am th ' unhappy subject of these quarrels .

input: Sir, do not grieve.
target: Sir , grieve not you .

input: In the hearing of these many friends, I swear to thee, even by my own fair eyes, Mark you but that!
target: Portia , forgive me this enforced wrong , And in the hearing of these many friends I swear to thee , even by thine own fair eyes Wherein I see myself , Mark you but that !

input: He sees himself in both of my eyes, one in each eye.
target: In both my eyes he doubly sees himself , In each eye , one .

input: There's an oath of credit, and you're wearing by your double self.
target: Swear by your double self , And there's an oath of credit !

input: But hear me, that's okay.
target: Nay , but hear me .

input: I swear by my soul that I never will break an oath with thee again.
target: Pardon this fault , and by my soul I swear I never more will break an oath with thee .

input: I once lent my body for his wealth, but for your husband's ring, which had quite miscarried, I did it once.
target: I once did lend my body for his wealth , Which but for him that had your husband's ring Had quite miscarried .

input: I gave the doctor the same thing, by heaven.
target: By heaven , it is the same I gave the doctor !

input: I had it in my possession.
target: I had it of him .

input: We have deserved it, but what about us?
target: What , are we cuckolds ere we have deserved it ?

input: You are all amazed, speak not so grossly.
target: Speak not so grossly. , You are all amazed .

input: I don't know anything.
target: I am dumb .

input: Unless he live until he be a man, the clerk doesn't mean to do it.
target: Ay , but the clerk that never means to do it Unless he live until he be a man .

input: You have given me life and I appreciate that.
target: Sweet lady , you have given me life and living .

input: The Duke of Saxony's nephew, the young German, how like you?
target: How like you the young German , the Duke of Saxony's nephew ?

input: He is very vile in the morning when he is sober and very vile in the afternoon when he is drunk.
target: Very vilely in the morning , when he is sober , and most vilely in the afternoon , when he is drunk .

input: He is a little worse than a man when he is the best, and a little better than a beast when he is the worst.
target: When he is best he is a little worse than a man , and when he is worst he is little better than a beast .

input: I'll be married to a sponge, and I will do anything.
target: I will do any thing , Nerissa , ere I'll be married to a sponge .

input: You don't need to be afraid, lady, you have any of these lords.
target: You need not fear , lady , the having any of these lords .

input: I am praying that God will grant them a fair departure.
target: And I pray God grant them a fair departure .

input: In your father's time, a Venetian, a scholar and a soldier, came hither in company of the Montferrats, do you remember?
target: Do you not remember , lady , in your father's time a Venetian , a scholar and a soldier , that came hither in company of the Marquess of Montferrat ?

input: How are you now, Lorenzo?
target: How now , Lorenzo ?

input: My clerk has some good comforts for you as well.
target: My clerk hath some good comforts too for you .

input: I'll give them him without charge.
target: Ay , and I'll give them him without a fee .

input: Fair ladies, you drop manna in the way of people who are starving.
target: Fair ladies , you drop manna in the way Of starved people .

input: I am sure that you are not satisfied with the events that have taken place.
target: It is almost morning , And yet I am sure you are not satisfied Of these events at full .

input: We will answer all the questions faithfully, if we go in and charge us there.
target: Let us go in , And charge us there upon interr'gatories , And we will answer all things faithfully .

input: Let it be that way.
target: Let it be so .

input: The first interr'gatory that my Nerissa will have to answer is whether or not to stay till the next night or go to bed now.
target: The first interr'gatory That my Nerissa shall be sworn on is Whether till the next night she had rather stay , Or go to bed now , being two hours to day .

input: I should have wished it was dark because I was couching with the doctor's clerk.
target: But were the day come , I should wish it dark , That I were couching with the doctor's clerk .

input: It is true, madam.
target: True , madam .

input: He was the best deserving of a fair lady and my foolish eyes looked upon him.
target: He , of all the men that ever my foolish eyes looked upon , was the best deserving a fair lady .

input: I remember him well, and I think he is worthy of praise.
target: I remember him well , and I remember him worthy of thy praise .

input: What news is happening now?
target: How now , what news ?

input: The four strangers are looking for you, madam, to take their leave.
target: The four strangers seek for you , madam , to take their leave .

input: The prince his master will be here tonight, comes from a fifth prince, the Prince of Morocco.
target: And there is a forerunner come from a fifth , the Prince of Morocco , who brings word the prince his master will be here tonight .

input: If I could bid the fifth welcome with a good heart as I can bid the other four farewells, then I should be happy with his approach.
target: If I could bid the fifth welcome with so good a heart as I can bid the other four farewell , I should be glad of his approach .

input: If he have the condition of a saint and the complexion of a devil, I would rather have him kill me than not.
target: If he have the condition of a saint and the complexion of a devil , I had rather he should shrive me than wive me .

input: Come to us, Nerissa.
target: Come , Nerissa. ,

input: Three thousand ducats, well that's right.
target: Three thousand ducats , well .

input: For three months, sir.
target: Ay , sir , for three months .

input: Three months is a long time.
target: For three months , well .

input: I told you that Antonio would be bound.
target: For the which , as I told you , Antonio shall be bound .

input: Antonio is going to become bound.
target: Antonio shall become bound , well .

input: Is it possible that you will stead me?
target: May you stead me ?

input: Will you be happy with me?
target: Will you pleasure me ?

input: Is it possible that I will know your answer.
target: Shall I know your answer ?

input: Antonio bound for three months with three thousand ducats.
target: Three thousand ducats for three months , and Antonio bound .

input: Do you have an answer for that?
target: Your answer to that ?

input: Antonio is a good person.
target: Antonio is a good man .

input: Is there any imputation that you have not heard?
target: Have you heard any imputation to the contrary ?

input: His means are in a state of supposition.
target: Yet his means are in supposition .

input: He has an argosy bound to Libya and the Indies.
target: He hath an argosy bound to Tripolis , another to the Indies .

input: I understand that he had a third at Mexico, a fourth for England, and other ventures abroad.
target: I understand moreover , upon the Rialto , he hath a third at Mexico , a fourth for England , and other ventures he hath squandered abroad .

input: Sailors and men are not on ships.
target: But ships are but boards , sailors but men .

input: There are land rats and water rats, water thieves and land thieves, and then there is the danger of waters, winds, and rocks.
target: There be land rats and water rats , water thieves and land thieves , I mean pirates , and then there is the peril of waters , winds , and rocks .

input: The man is still sufficient.
target: The man is notwithstanding sufficient .

input: You will be assured that you will.
target: Be assured you may .

input: Signor Antonio is here.
target: This is Signor Antonio .

input: I do not know why I am sad.
target: In sooth , I know not why I am so sad .

input: You say it wearies me, I say it wearies you.
target: It wearies me ; you say it wearies you .

input: The better part of my affections would be if I had ventured abroad.
target: Believe me , sir , had I such venture forth , The better part of my affections would Be with my hopes abroad .

input: I would be sad if every object made me fear misfortune to my ventures out of doubt.
target: And every object that might make me fear Misfortune to my ventures out of doubt Would make me sad .

input: Do you know what I'm talking about?
target: Shylock , do you hear ?

input: I can't raise the gross of full three thousand ducats instantly because I am debating my present store.
target: I am debating of my present store , And by the near guess of my memory I can not instantly raise up the gross Of full three thousand ducats .

input: What about this?
target: What of that ?

input: Tubal, a wealthy Hebrew of my tribe, will give me something.
target: Tubal , a wealthy Hebrew of my tribe , Will furnish me .

input: But soft, but!
target: But soft !

input: How many months do you want to have?
target: How many months Do you desire ?

input: I don't lend nor borrow, but I will break a custom if I can give my friend the ripe wants of my friend.
target: Shylock , albeit I neither lend nor borrow By taking nor by giving of excess , Yet to supply the ripe wants of my friend , I'll break a custom .

input: There are three thousand ducats.
target: Ay , ay , three thousand ducats .

input: And for three months.
target: And for three months .

input: Three months had passed and I had forgotten.
target: I had forgot , three months .

input: You said that to me.
target: You told me so .

input: I don't use it at all.
target: I do never use it .

input: When Jacob grazed his uncle Laban's sheep, this Jacob from our holy Abram was, as his wise mother wrought in his behalf, the third possessor, and what of him?
target: When Jacob grazed his uncle Laban's sheep , This Jacob from our holy Abram was , As his wise mother wrought in his behalf , The third possessor , ay , he was the third , And what of him ?

input: Is he interested in the matter?
target: Did he take interest ?

input: This was a thing not in Jacob's power to bring to pass, but swayed and fashioned by the hand of heaven.
target: This was a venture , sir , that Jacob served for , A thing not in his power to bring to pass But swayed and fashioned by the hand of heaven .

input: Is your gold and silver sheep and rams?
target: Or is your gold and silver ewes and rams ?

input: But signor, but note me.
target: But note me , signor ,

input: An evil soul producing a holy witness is like a villain with a smiling cheek and rotten at the heart.
target: An evil soul producing holy witness Is like a villain with a smiling cheek , A goodly apple rotten at the heart .

input: Oh, what a goodly outside lie!
target: Oh , what a goodly outside falsehood hath !

input: Three months from the day before.
target: Three months from twelve , then .

input: Let me see what I can see.
target: Let me see .

input: Is the rate beholding to you, Shylock?
target: The rate , Well , Shylock , shall we be beholding to you ?

input: You have rated me about my moneys and my usances, Antonio, many a time.
target: Signor Antonio , many a time and oft In the Rialto you have rated me About my moneys and my usances .

input: You call me a misbeliever, cutthroat dog, and all for use of my Jewish gaberdine.
target: You call me misbeliever , cutthroat dog , And spet upon my Jewish gaberdine , And all for use of that which is mine own .

input: It now appears you need my assistance.
target: Well then , it now appears you need my help .

input: Go to that point.
target: Go to , then !

input: "Shylock, we would have moneys", you say, as you walk me over your threshold.
target: You come to me and you say , "Shylock , we would have moneys." You say so ! , You , that did void your rheum upon my beard And foot me as you spurn a stranger cur Over your threshold !

input: Moneys is the suit of your choice.
target: Moneys is your suit .

input: What do you want me to say to you?
target: What should I say to you ?

input: "Hath a dog money?" Should I not say that?
target: Should I not say , "Hath a dog money ?

input: Is it possible that a person can lend three thousand ducats?
target: Is it possible A cur can lend three thousand ducats ? " Or Shall I bend low and in a bondman's key With bated breath and whispering humbleness Say this :

input: When did friendship take a breed for barren metal of his friend, if he was to lend this money?
target: If thou wilt lend this money , lend it not As to thy friends , for when did friendship take A breed for barren metal of his friend ?

input: If he breaks it, lend it to his opponent, who will have a better face.
target: But lend it rather to thine enemy , Who , if he break , thou mayst with better face Exact the penalty .

input: Look you how you storm, why?
target: Why , look you how you storm !

input: You will not hear me if you don't supply your present wants and take no doit of usance for my moneys.
target: I would be friends with you and have your love , Forget the shames that you have stained me with , Supply your present wants and take no doit Of usance for my moneys , and you'll not hear me !

input: This is the kind of thing I offer.
target: This is kind I offer .

input: This was kindness.
target: This were kindness .

input: This kindness will be shown by me.
target: This kindness will I show .

input: If you repay me not on such a day, in such a place, such sum or sums as are Expressed in the condition, let the forfeiture be done.
target: Go with me to a notary , seal me there Your single bond , and , in a merry sport , If you repay me not on such a day , In such a place , such sum or sums as are Expressed in the condition , let the forfeit Be nominated for an equal pound Of your fair flesh , to be cut off and taken In what part of your body pleaseth me .

input: In faith, there is content.
target: Content , in faith .

input: I will say that there is a lot of kindness in the Jew.
target: I'll seal to such a bond , And say there is much kindness in the Jew .

input: You will not seal such a bond for me.
target: You shall not seal to such a bond for me !

input: I will rather focus on my necessity.
target: I'll rather dwell in my necessity .

input: I expect return of three times the value of this bond within two months, before this bond expires.
target: Within these two months , that's a month before This bond expires , I do expect return Of thrice three times the value of this bond .

input: A pound of man's flesh taken from a man is not profitable or estimable, as the flesh of sheep, beef, or goats.
target: A pound of man's flesh taken from a man Is not so estimable , profitable neither , As flesh of muttons , beefs , or goats .

input: He will take it if he does.
target: If he will take it , so .

input: It's adieu if not.
target: If not , adieu .

input: I pray that you don't misunderstand me for my love.
target: And for my love I pray you wrong me not .

input: I will seal this bond, Shylock.
target: Yes , Shylock , I will seal unto this bond .

input: Then meet me at the end of the street.
target: Then meet me forthwith at the notary's .

input: Give him direction for this merry bond, and I will go and purse the ducats straight, see to my house left in the fearful guard of an unthrifty knave, and presently I will be with you.
target: Give him direction for this merry bond , And I will go and purse the ducats straight , See to my house left in the fearful guard Of an unthrifty knave , and presently I will be with you .

input: Thank you, gentle Jew.
target: Hie thee , gentle Jew .

input: The ships come home a month before the day.
target: My ships come home a month before the day .

input: I wouldn't change this hue except to steal your thoughts, my gentle queen.
target: I would not change this hue Except to steal your thoughts , my gentle queen .

input: I thank you for that, even for that.
target: Even for that I thank you .

input: I pray that you will lead me to the caskets to try my fortune.
target: Therefore I pray you lead me to the caskets To try my fortune .

input: That slew the Sophy and a Persian prince, that won three fields of Sultan Solyman, and that Outbrave the heart most daring on the earth, Pluck the young sucking cubs from the she.
target: By this scimitar That slew the Sophy and a Persian prince That won three fields of Sultan Solyman , I would o'erstare the sternest eyes that look , Outbrave the heart most daring on the earth , Pluck the young sucking cubs from the she-bear , Yea , mock the lion when he roars for prey , To win the lady .

input: But, alas, the while.
target: But , alas the while !

input: Nor will they.
target: Nor will not .

input: Come and let me take my chance.
target: Come , bring me unto my chance .

input: The first thing to do is to get to the temple.
target: First , forward to the temple .

input: Your hazard will be made after the dinner party.
target: After dinner Your hazard shall be made .

input: My conscience will allow me to run away from my master.
target: Certainly my conscience will serve me to run from this Jew , my master .

input: My conscience is hanging about the neck of my heart and it says very wisely to me that my honest friend Launcelot is being an honest man.
target: For the heavens , rouse up a brave mind , " says the fiend , "and run." Well , my conscience , hanging about the neck of my heart , says very wisely to me , "My honest friend Launcelot , being an honest man's son" , or rather an honest woman's son , for indeed my father did something smack , something grow to .

input: My conscience says, "Launcelot, budge not." The fiend says, "Budge!"
target: He had a kind of taste. , Well , my conscience says , "Launcelot , budge not." "Budge ! " says the fiend .

input: "Budge not," says my conscience.
target: Budge not , " says my conscience .

input: To be ruled by my conscience, I should stay with the Jew my master, who is a kind of devil.
target: Conscience , " say I , "you counsel well." "Fiend , " say I , "you counsel well." To be ruled by my conscience I should stay with the Jew my master , who , God bless the mark , is a kind of devil .

input: To escape from the Jew, I should be ruled by the fiend, who is the devil himself.
target: And to run away from the Jew I should be ruled by the fiend , who , saving your reverence , is the devil himself .

input: The fiend is more friendly with the counsel.
target: The fiend gives the more friendly counsel .

input: I will run, fiend.
target: I will run , fiend .

input: I am going to run.
target: I will run .

input: Which is the way to Master Jew's, Master young man, I pray you are okay?
target: Master young man , you , I pray you , which is the way to Master Jew's ?

input: I pray that you find the way to Master Jew's, Master young gentleman.
target: Master young gentleman , I pray you , which is the way to Master Jew's ?

input: Turn up on your right hand at the next turn, but down on your left at the next turning.
target: Turn up on your right hand at the next turning , but at the next turning of all on your left .

input: At the next turn of no hand, turn down to the Jew's house and we will marry.
target: Marry , at the very next turning turn of no hand , but turn down indirectly to the Jew's house .

input: By God's sonties, it will be a hard way to hit.
target: By God's sonties , 'twill be a hard way to hit .

input: Can you tell me if one Launcelot dwells with him or not.
target: Can you tell me whether one Launcelot that dwells with him , dwell with him or no ?

input: Talk to Master Launcelot, he is young.
target: Talk you of young Master Launcelot ?

input: A poor man's son, but no "master", sir.
target: No "master , " sir , but a poor man's son .

input: I say that his father is an honest exceeding poor man and that God be thanked for that.
target: His father , though I say 't , is an honest exceeding poor man and , God be thanked , well to live .

input: Sir, your worship's friend and Launcelot, sir.
target: Your worship's friend and Launcelot , sir .

input: I don't know if it would make me sad, but will I have the thought to think about this?
target: Shall I have the thought To think on this , and shall I lack the thought That such a thing bechanced would make me sad ?

input: But don't tell me.
target: But tell not me .

input: No, believe me, I do.
target: Believe me , no .

input: My merchandise makes me feel better.
target: Therefore my merchandise makes me not sad .

input: Why are you in love with each other?
target: Why then , you are in love .

input: Not in love, neither?
target: Not in love neither ?

input: I pray that you talk to the young Master Launcelot, I implore you.
target: But I pray you , ergo , old man , ergo , I beseech you , talk you of young Master Launcelot ?

input: Master Launcelot is called that.
target: Ergo , Master Launcelot .

input: Don't marry, God forbid.
target: Marry , God forbid !

input: The boy was my prop when I was younger.
target: The boy was the very staff of my age , my very prop .

input: I don't know if I look like a cudgel, a hovel-post, a staff, or a prop.
target: Do I look like a cudgel or a hovel-post , a staff or a prop ?

input: Do you know anything about me?
target: Do you know me , Father ?

input: I know you don't, but alack the day.
target: Alack the day , I know you not , young gentleman .

input: Please tell me if my boy is alive or dead, I want to know.
target: But I pray you , tell me , is my boy , God rest his soul , alive or dead ?

input: Father, do you not know who I am?
target: Do you not know me , Father ?

input: I am sand-blind, Alack.
target: Alack , sir , I am sand-blind .

input: I know that you don't.
target: I know you not .

input: If you didn't have your eyes, you would fail to know me.
target: Nay , indeed if you had your eyes , you might fail of the knowing me .

input: It is a wise father that knows his child.
target: It is a wise father that knows his own child .

input: I will tell you about your son, old man.
target: Well , old man , I will tell you news of your son .

input: You should give me your blessings.
target: Give me your blessing .

input: Stand up, sir, please pray for you.
target: Pray you , sir , stand up .

input: I am certain that you are not Launcelot, my boy.
target: I am sure you are not Launcelot , my boy .

input: Let's have no more fooling about it, but please give me your blessings.
target: Pray you , let's have no more fooling about it , but give me your blessing .

input: I am Launcelot, your boy that was, your son that was, and your child that will be.
target: I am Launcelot , your boy that was , your son that is , your child that shall be .

input: I don't think you are my son, I can't believe it.
target: I can not think you are my son .

input: Her name is Margery, indeed.
target: Her name is Margery , indeed .

input: I'll be sworn in if I'm Launcelot, I have my own flesh and blood.
target: I'll be sworn , if thou be Launcelot , thou art mine own flesh and blood .

input: It seems like Dobbin's tail grows backwards.
target: It should seem then that Dobbin's tail grows backward .

input: I'm pretty sure he had more hair on his tail than I did.
target: I am sure he had more hair of his tail than I have of my face when I last saw him .

input: How art has changed!
target: Lord , how art thou changed !

input: How do you agree with your master?
target: How dost thou and thy master agree ?

input: I have given him a present.
target: I have brought him a present .

input: How much do you want now?
target: How 'gree you now ?

input: My master is a very religious person.
target: My master's a very Jew .

input: Give him something to unwrap.
target: Give him a present .

input: He should be given a halter.
target: Give him a halter .

input: I am very sad for him in his service.
target: I am famished in his service .

input: You can tell if I have ribs by my fingers.
target: You may tell every finger I have with my ribs .

input: Father, I'm happy you're here.
target: Father , I am glad you are come .

input: Master Bassanio gives rare new liveries and I want you to give me your present.
target: Give me your present to one Master Bassanio , who indeed gives rare new liveries .

input: Gramercy is what it is.
target: Gramercy !

input: Is it possible that you would aught with me.
target: Wouldst thou aught with me ?

input: What do you think would be the answer?
target: What would you ?

input: You should serve you, sir.
target: Serve you , sir .

input: That is the most serious defect of the matter, sir.
target: That is the very defect of the matter , sir .

input: I know what I'm talking about.
target: I know thee well .

input: The suit has been obtained by Thou.
target: Thou hast obtained thy suit .

input: Father is in the picture.
target: Father , in .

input: My best efforts will be accomplished here.
target: My best endeavours shall be done herein .

input: He walks. Yonder, sir, he walks.
target: Yonder , sir , he walks .

input: Bassanio is a signor.
target: Signor Bassanio !

input: It's Gratiano!
target: Gratiano !

input: I have a suit that you can wear.
target: I have a suit to you .

input: You have obtained something.
target: You have obtained it .

input: You have to allow me to.
target: You must not deny me .

input: I need you with me to go to Belmont.
target: I must go with you to Belmont .

input: Then you must explain why.
target: Why , then you must .

input: Listen to thee, Gratiano.
target: But hear thee , Gratiano .

input: Ours appear not to be faults because of our wild, rude, and bold voice, and parts that become thee happily enough.
target: Thou art too wild , too rude and bold of voice , Parts that become thee happily enough And in such eyes as ours appear not faults .

input: To allay with some cold drops of modesty, I will be misconst'red in the place that I go, and lose my hopes.
target: Pray thee , take pain To allay with some cold drops of modesty Thy skipping spirit , lest through thy wild behavior I be misconst'red in the place I go to , And lose my hopes .

input: Signor Bassanio, please hear me.
target: Signor Bassanio , hear me .

input: If I don't put on a sober habit, talk with respect and swear but also wear prayer books in my pocket and look demurely.
target: If I do not put on a sober habit , Talk with respect and swear but now and then , Wear prayer books in my pocket , look demurely , Nay more .

input: While grace is saying, hood mine eyes, and sigh and say "Amen", Use all the observance of civility, like one well studied in a sad ostent, to please his grandam.

input: Allow my counsel to sway you in this case for a while.
target: Pause awhile , And let my counsel sway you in this case .

target: Let her awhile be secretly kept in And publish it that she is dead indeed .

target: And though you know my inwardness and love Is very much unto the Prince and Claudio , Yet , by mine honor , I will deal in this As secretly and justly as your soul Should with your body .

input: Is this something you've been looking for?

target: My brother hath a daughter , Almost the copy of my child that's dead , And she alone is heir to both of us .

input: I will die my revenge because you should have given her cousin the right.
target: Give her the right you should have given her cousin , And so dies my revenge .

input: I feel that I adore her.
target: That I love her , I feel .

input: I am aware that she is worthy.
target: That she is worthy , I know .

input: He was never able to maintain his part but in the force of his will.
target: And never could maintain his part but in the force of his will .

input: I would like to thank the woman that conceived me.
target: That a woman conceived me , I thank her .

input: I gave her the most humble thanks, that she brought me up.
target: That she brought me up , I likewise give her most humble thanks .

input: I will see thee, and I will look pale with love.
target: I shall see thee , ere I die , look pale with love .

input: My lord, not with love, but with anger, with sickness, or with hunger.
target: With anger , with sickness , or with hunger , my lord , not with love .

input: Pick out my eyes with a pen and hang me up at the door of a brothel house if I can prove that I lose more blood with love than I will get again with drinking.
target: Prove that ever I lose more blood with love than I will get again with drinking , pick out mine eyes with a ballad-maker's pen and hang me up at the door of a brothel house for the sign of blind Cupid .

input: Sir, O noble sir!
target: O noble sir !

input: Your kindness wrings tears out of me.
target: Your overkindness doth wring tears from me .

input: I accept your offer and dispose of the poor Claudio.
target: I do embrace your offer ; and dispose For henceforth of poor Claudio .

input: Tomorrow is when I will expect you to arrive.
target: Tomorrow then I will expect your coming .

input: I will take my leave tonight.
target: Tonight I take my leave .

input: The naughty man will be brought to Margaret by your brother, who I believe was packed in all the wrong places.
target: This naughty man Shall face to face be brought to Margaret , Who I believe was packed in all this wrong , Hired to it by your brother .

input: I would like to thank thee for your care and honest pains.
target: I thank thee for thy care and honest pains .

input: I praise God for you, because your worship speaks like a most thankful and reverent youth.
target: Your worship speaks like a most thankful and reverent youth , and I praise God for you .

input: The foundation is saved by the Almighty.
target: God save the foundation !

input: For the example of others, I leave an arrant knave with your Worship, which I implore you to correct yourself.
target: I leave an arrant knave with your Worship , which I beseech your Worship to correct yourself , for the example of others .

input: God, keep your worship!
target: God keep your Worship !

input: I wish you good luck with your worship.
target: I wish your Worship well .

input: You will be restored to health by the Almighty!
target: God restore you to health !

input: Thank you, my lords.
target: Farewell , my lords .

input: We will be looking for you tomorrow.
target: We look for you tomorrow .

input: We are going to succeed.
target: We will not fail .

input: Tonight I will mourn with Hero.
target: Tonight I'll mourn with Hero .

input: Margaret, please help me to the speech of Beatrice, I need your assistance.
target: Pray thee , sweet Mistress Margaret , deserve well at my hands by helping me to the speech of Beatrice .

input: To not have a man come over me.
target: To have no man come over me !

input: Margaret is a most manly wit and it will not hurt a woman.
target: A most manly wit , Margaret , it will not hurt a woman .

input: I pray thee to call thee, Beatrice.
target: And so , I pray thee , call Beatrice .
Well , I will call Beatrice to you , who I think hath legs .

input: And therefore will happen.
target: And therefore will come .

input: I am talking about singing.
target: I mean in singing .

input: Is it possible that you would come when I called thee?
target: Sweet Beatrice , wouldst thou come when I called thee ?

input: Signior, leave me when you bid me.
target: Yea , Signior , and depart when you bid me .

input: Stay, but till then.
target: Oh , stay but till then !

input: I will kiss thee if there are only foul words left.
target: Only foul words , and thereupon I will kiss thee .

input: Foul words and foul wind are not the same, and foul breath is not the same.
target: Foul words is but foul wind , and foul wind is but foul breath , and foul breath is noisome .

input: I will leave without being kissed.
target: Therefore I will depart unkissed .

input: He has frighted the word out of his right sense, so forcible is his wit.
target: Thou hast frighted the word out of his right sense , so forcible is thy wit .

input: If I don't hear from him soon, I'm going to subscribe him a cowardice.
target: But I must tell thee plainly , Claudio undergoes my challenge , and either I must shortly hear from him , or I will subscribe him a coward .

input: I would like to know which of my bad parts first fell in love with me.
target: And I pray thee now tell me , for which of my bad parts didst thou first fall in love with me ?

input: For them all together, they maintained a state of evil that they will not admit any good part to.
target: For them all together , which maintained so politic a state of evil that they will not admit any good part to intermingle with them .

input: For which of my good parts did you first fall in love with me?
target: But for which of my good parts did you first suffer love for me ?

input: I will suffer love.
target: Suffer love !

input: A good way to describe yourself.
target: A good epithet !

input: For I love thee against my will, and I suffer love.
target: I do suffer love indeed , for I love thee against my will .

input: I think that in spite of your heart, I think.
target: In spite of your heart , I think .

input: If a man doesn't put his own tomb in this age, he will live no longer in a monument than the bell rings and the widow will weep.
target: If a man do not erect in this age his own tomb ere he dies , he shall live no longer in monument than the bell rings and the widow weeps .

input: Do you know how long that is?
target: And how long is that , think you ?

input: Why is it that there is an hour in clamor and a quarter in rheum?
target: Question : why , an hour in clamor and a quarter in rheum .

input: If Don Worm finds no impediment to the contrary, is it most expedient for the wise to trumpet his own virtues?
target: Therefore is it most expedient for the wise , if Don Worm , his conscience , find no impediment to the contrary , to be the trumpet of his own virtues , as I am to myself .

input: I myself will bear witness, which is praiseworthy, but so much for praising myself.
target: So much for praising myself , who , I myself will bear witness , is praiseworthy .

input: How do you know your cousin is doing?
target: An now tell me , how doth your cousin ?

input: It's very ill as well.
target: Very ill , too .

input: Help God, love me, and mend.
target: Serve God , love me , and mend .

input: You need to come to your uncle.
target: Madam , you must come to your uncle .

input: Don John is the author of all, who is fled and gone, after it was proven my Lady Hero was wrongly accused, the Prince and Claudio abused, and Don John is the author.
target: It is proved my Lady Hero hath been falsely accused , the Prince and Claudio mightily abused , and Don John is the author of all , who is fled and gone .

input: Will you come right now?
target: Will you come presently ?

input: Signior, will you listen to this news?
target: Will you go hear this news , Signior ?

input: I will die in your lap, and be buried in your eyes, and I will accompany you to your uncle's house.
target: I will live in thy heart , die in thy lap , and be buried in thy eyes , and moreover , I will go with thee to thy uncle's .

input: Is this the monument of a person?
target: Is this the monument of Leonato ?

input: My lord, it is, my lord.
target: It is , my lord .

input: The Hero that here lies was Done to Death by slanderous tongues.
target: Done to death by slanderous tongues Was the Hero that here lies .

input: She gives her fame which never dies, because of her wrongs.
target: Death , in guerdon of her wrongs , Gives her fame which never dies .

input: The life that died with shame Lives in death with glorious fame.
target: So the life that died with shame Lives in death with glorious fame .

input: Praising her when I am dumb, hang there upon the tomb.
target: Hang thou there upon the tomb , Praising her when I am dumb .

input: Music, sound, and sing your solemn hymn now.
target: Now , music , sound , and sing your solemn hymn .

input: Good night, now, unto the bones!
target: Now , unto thy bones good night !

input: Will I do this ritual yearly?
target: Yearly will I do this rite .

input: Tomorrow is good, masters.
target: Good morrow , masters .

input: You should put your torches out.
target: Put your torches out .

input: The wolves have preyed, and looked, the gentle day, before the wheels of Phoebus, round about Dapples the drowsy east with spots of grey.
target: The wolves have preyed , and look , the gentle day , Before the wheels of Phoebus , round about Dapples the drowsy east with spots of grey .

input: Tomorrow is good, masters.
target: Good morrow , masters .

input: I don't know if I told you that she was innocent.
target: Did I not tell you she was innocent ?

input: The Prince and Claudio accused her of making an error that they heard debate.
target: So are the Prince and Claudio , who accused her Upon the error that you heard debated .

input: I am happy that all things are going well.
target: Well , I am glad that all things sort so well .

input: Being by faith enforced, I am also calling young Claudio to a reckoning for it.
target: And so am I , being else by faith enforced To call young Claudio to a reckoning for it .

input: When I send for you, come hither masked, and withdraw into a chamber by yourselves, daughter and you gentle women.
target: Well , daughter , and you gentlewomen all , Withdraw into a chamber by yourselves , And when I send for you , come hither masked .

input: The Prince and his brother will visit me by this hour.
target: The Prince and Claudio promised by this hour To visit me. , You know your office , brother .

input: You have to be the father of your brother's daughter to young Claudio.
target: You must be father to your brother's daughter , And give her to young Claudio .

input: Is it possible to do what Signior asks?
target: To do what , Signior ?

input: That eye my daughter lent her was most true.
target: That eye my daughter lent her ; 'tis most true .

input: I do with an eye of love requite her.
target: And I do with an eye of love requite her .

input: I think you had from me the sight where you had from the princes.
target: The sight whereof I think you had from me , From Claudio and the Prince .

input: But what will you do?
target: But what's your will ?

input: Sir, your answer is enigmatical.
target: Your answer , sir , is enigmatical .

input: And my help as well.
target: And my help .

input: There is the Prince and the Claudio.
target: Here comes the Prince and Claudio .

input: Tomorrow is a good day to attend this fair assembly.
target: Good morrow to this fair assembly .

input: Good tomorrow, Prince, and good tomorrow, Claudio.
target: Good morrow , Prince ; good morrow , Claudio .

input: We are here to support you.
target: We here attend you .

input: Are you still determined to marry my brother's daughter?
target: Are you yet determined Today to marry with my brother's daughter ?

input: I'll think about her if she was an Ethiope.
target: I'll hold my mind were she an Ethiope .

input: As time goes by, we shall try.
target: Well , as time shall try .

input: The hours are what you temporize with.
target: Well , you temporize with the hours .

input: Inform him that I will not fail him at supper, for he has made great preparation.
target: Commend me to him and tell him I will not fail him at supper , for indeed he hath made great preparation .

input: Please call her forth, brother.
target: Call her forth , brother .

input: There's the friar ready.
target: Here's the friar ready .

input: Good morning, Benedick.
target: Good morrow , Benedick .

input: I believe he thinks of the savage bull.
target: I think he thinks upon the savage bull .

input: Man, don't worry, fear not.
target: Tush , fear not , man .

input: There are other reck's here.
target: Here comes other reck'nings .

input: Which is the lady that I have to seize upon?
target: Which is the lady I must seize upon ?

input: I give you the same thing, she is the same.
target: This same is she , and I do give you her .

input: You will not marry her until you take her hand and swear to marry her.
target: No , that you shall not till you take her hand Before this friar and swear to marry her .

input: Another Hero!
target: Another Hero !

input: Nothing is certain.
target: Nothing certainer .

input: One Hero died, but I live, and surely as I live, I am a maid.
target: One Hero died defiled , but I do live , And surely as I live , I am a maid .

input: The former hero!
target: The former Hero !

input: That is a hero that is no longer alive.
target: Hero that is dead !

input: She died, my lord, but her words were still being spoken.
target: She died , my lord , but whiles her slander lived .

input: I will tell you mostly of Hero's death after the holy rites are ended.
target: All this amazement can I qualify When after that the holy rites are ended I'll tell you largely of fair Hero's death .

input: Soft and fair, Friar. Which is Beatrice?
target: Soft and fair , Friar. , Which is Beatrice ?

input: You love me, do not you?
target: Do not you love me ?

input: Why not, no more than reason.
target: Why no , no more than reason .

input: Your uncle and the Prince have been deceived, why?
target: Why then , your uncle and the Prince and Claudio Have been deceived .

input: They said that you did.
target: They swore you did .

input: You love me, do not you?
target: Do not you love me ?

input: Troth, no, no more than reason.
target: Troth , no , no more than reason .

input: Margaret and Ursula were deceived by the fact that they did swear you did.
target: Why then , my cousin , Margaret , and Ursula Are much deceived , for they did swear you did .

input: They said that you were close to being sick for me.
target: They swore that you were almost sick for me .

input: They swore that you were dead for me.
target: They swore that you were well-nigh dead for me .

input: It's not such a matter.
target: Tis no such matter .

input: Do you not love me?
target: Then you do not love me ?

input: No, truly, but in friendly compensation.
target: No , truly , but in friendly recompense .

input: I am sure you love the gentleman, cousin.
target: Come , cousin , I am sure you love the gentleman .

input: There's another one in my cousin's hand, stol'n from her pocket, and it contains her affection for Benedick.
target: And here's another , Writ in my cousin's hand , stol'n from her pocket , Containing her affection unto Benedick .

input: It is a miracle!
target: A miracle !

input: We have our own hands against our hearts.
target: Here's our own hands against our hearts .

input: By this light, I take thee for pity, but I will have thee.
target: Come , I will have thee , but , by this light , I take thee for pity .

input: I was told that you were in a consumption state, so I relented and saved your life, but I would not deny you.
target: I would not deny you , but , by this good day , I yield upon great persuasion , and partly to save your life , for I was told you were in a consumption .

input: There is peace.
target: Peace !

input: I will stop you from speaking.
target: I will stop your mouth .

input: What do you think about Benedick, the married man?
target: How dost thou , Benedick , the married man ?

input: I will tell Prince that a college of wit-crackers can't make me laugh out of my humor.
target: I'll tell thee what , Prince : a college of wit-crackers can not flout me out of my humor .

input: Do you think I care about satire or an Epigram?
target: Dost thou think I care for a satire or an epigram ?

input: No, that's not true.
target: No .

input: My word first, of course.
target: First , of my word !

input: Prince, please play music and be sad.
target: Therefore play , music. , Prince , thou art sad .

input: Get thee a wife, get thee a wife.
target: Get thee a wife , get thee a wife .

input: To the tuition of the Almighty.
target: To the tuition of God .

input: If I had it on the sixth of July, it was from my house.
target: From my house , if I had it , The sixth of July .

input: Your highness may do me good, my liege.
target: My liege , your highness now may do me good .

input: My love is for teaching.
target: My love is thine to teach .

input: Thou shalt see how apt it is to learn a hard lesson, if you teach it but how.
target: Teach it but how , And thou shalt see how apt it is to learn Any hard lesson that may do thee good .

input: My lord, how about any son, my lord?
target: Hath Leonato any son , my lord ?

input: Hero is his only child and his heir.
target: No child but Hero ; she's his only heir .

input: Is it possible that she will affect her, Claudio?
target: Dost thou affect her , Claudio ?

input: If you love fair Hero, I will break with her and with her father, and you will have her.
target: If thou dost love fair Hero , cherish it , And I will break with her and with her father , And thou shalt have her .

input: Was it not to this end that he began to twist so fine a story?
target: Was 't not to this end That thou began'st to twist so fine a story ?

input: I would have taken care of it with a longer piece of writing.
target: But lest my liking might too sudden seem , I would have salved it with a longer treatise .

input: The bridge needs to be broader than the floods.
target: What need the bridge much broader than the flood ?

input: I will pretend to be Hero and take her prisoner with the force of my amorous tale, and in her bosom, I will unclasp my heart.
target: I will assume thy part in some disguise And tell fair Hero I am Claudio , And in her bosom I'll unclasp my heart And take her hearing prisoner with the force And strong encounter of my amorous tale .

input: Let us put it in practice now.
target: In practice let us put it presently .

input: This music was provided by him.
target: Hath he provided this music ?

input: He is working very hard on it.
target: He is very busy about it .

input: I can tell you that you haven't dreamt in a long time.
target: But , brother , I can tell you strange news that you yet dreamt not of .

input: Is they a good thing?
target: Are they good ?

input: Is the fellow a wit that told you that?
target: Hath the fellow any wit that told you this ?

input: A sharp fellow.
target: A good sharp fellow .

input: I'll send for him and ask him some questions.
target: I will send for him , and question him yourself .

input: He is very close to this.
target: He is very near by this .

input: When I left him, he was not three leagues off.
target: He was not three leagues off when I left him .

input: How many gentlemen have you lost in this action?
target: How many gentlemen have you lost in this action ?

input: There are few of any sort and no name.
target: But few of any sort , and none of name .

input: When the achiever brings home full numbers, there is a victory twice itself.
target: A victory is twice itself when the achiever brings home full numbers .

input: Don Pedro gave a lot of honor to a young Florentine, called Claudio.
target: I find here that Don Pedro hath bestowed much honor on a young Florentine called Claudio .

input: An uncle in Messina will be very pleased with it.
target: He hath an uncle here in Messina will be very much glad of it .

input: We will hold on to it as a dream until it becomes reality.
target: No , no , we will hold it as a dream till it appear itself .

input: I will tell my daughter that she may be better prepared for an answer if this are true.
target: But I will acquaint my daughter withal , that she may be the better prepared for an answer if peradventure this be true .

input: You should tell her about it.
target: Go you and tell her of it .

input: You know what you have to do. I cry for you friend.
target: Cousins , you know what you have to do. , O , I cry you mercy , friend .

input: I will use your skills if you go with me.
target: Go you with me and I will use your skill. , Good cousin , have a care this busy time .

input: Why are you so sad, my lord, what a wonderful year?
target: What the goodyear , my lord , why are you thus out of measure sad ?

input: There is no limit to the sadness.
target: Therefore the sadness is without limit .

input: You should be aware of why.
target: You should hear reason .

input: I don't have to hide what I am.
target: I can not hide what I am .

input: You must not make the full show of this until you can do it without controlment.
target: Yea , but you must not make the full show of this till you may do it without controlment .

input: You have stood out against your brother, where it is impossible for you to take root, but by the fair weather that you make yourself.
target: You have of late stood out against your brother , and he hath ta'en you newly into his grace , where it is impossible you should take true root but by the fair weather that you make yourself .

input: It is necessary that you frame the season for your own harvest.
target: It is needful that you frame the season for your own harvest .

input: I had rather be a canker in a hedge than a rose in his grace, and it better fits my blood to be disdained of all than to fashion a carriage to rob love from any person.
target: I had rather be a canker in a hedge than a rose in his grace , and it better fits my blood to be disdained of all than to fashion a carriage to rob love from any .

input: Though I can't be said to be a flattering honest man, I am a plain- Dealing villain.
target: In this , though I can not be said to be a flattering honest man , it must not be denied but I am a plain-dealing villain .

input: Let me be who I am and not be changed by this.
target: In the meantime , let me be that I am , and seek not to alter me .

input: Can you not use your unhappiness?
target: Can you make no use of your discontent ?

input: I only use it when I need it, so I make all use of it.
target: I make all use of it , for I use it only .

input: Who arrives here?
target: Who comes here ?

input: What is the current news, Borachio?
target: What news , Borachio ?

input: What is it that he is for a fool that would bet his life on un quietness?
target: What is he for a fool that betroths himself to unquietness ?

input: It is your brother's right hand that you marry.
target: Marry , it is your brother's right hand .

input: Who is this person?
target: Who ?

input: The most beautiful man in the world?
target: The most exquisite Claudio ?

input: Even he, even.
target: Even he .

input: Marry on Hero, the daughter and heir to the throne.
target: Marry , on Hero , the daughter and heir of Leonato .

input: The March-chick is a very forward March.
target: A very forward March-chick !

input: How did you come to this?
target: How came you to this ?

input: Being entertained for a perfumer, as I was smoking a musty room, comes me the Prince and Claudio, hand in hand, in a sad conference,
target: Being entertained for a perfumer , as I was smoking a musty room , comes me the Prince and Claudio , hand in hand , in sad conference .

input: Let us come, come, let us come.
target: Come , come , let us thither .

input: This could prove to be food that I don't like.
target: This may prove food to my displeasure .

input: I bless myself every way if I can cross him.
target: If I can cross him any way , I bless myself every way .

input: Both of you are sure, and will assist me.
target: You are both sure , and will assist me ?

input: To the death of my lord.
target: To the death , my lord .

input: We are going to the great supper.
target: Let us to the great supper .

input: We will wait for your lordship.
target: We'll wait upon your lordship .

input: Did Count John not come here at supper?
target: Was not Count John here at supper ?

input: I couldn't see him.
target: I saw him not .

input: That gentleman looks like he is trying to be funny.
target: How tartly that gentleman looks !

input: I can't see him, but I get indigestion after an hour.
target: I never can see him but I am heartburned an hour after .

input: He has a very sad disposition.
target: He is of a very melancholy disposition .

input: He was an excellent man that was made in the middle of him and Benedick.
target: He were an excellent man that were made just in the midway between him and Benedick .

input: The one says nothing and the other is tattling, it's like an image and a picture.
target: The one is too like an image and says nothing , and the other too like my lady's eldest son , evermore tattling .

input: Signor Benedick's tongue was half in Count John's mouth and half in his face, with a good leg and a good foot.
target: Then half Signor Benedick's tongue in Count John's mouth , and half Count John's melancholy in Signor Benedick's face , With a good leg and a good foot , uncle , and money enough in his purse , such a man would win any woman in the world , if he could get her goodwill .

input: By my troth, niece, you will never get a husband if you are so shrewd of your tongue.
target: By my troth , niece , thou wilt never get thee a husband if thou be so shrewd of thy tongue .

input: She's too hard of a person in faith.
target: In faith , she's too curst .

input: You can light on a husband that doesn't have a beard.
target: You may light on a husband that hath no beard .

input: I don't know what to do with him.
target: What should I do with him ?

input: Do you mean go to hell?
target: Well then , go you into hell ?

input: The devil will meet me at the gate and say, "Get you to heaven, Beatrice, get you to heaven, here's no place for you maids."
target: No , but to the gate , and there will the devil meet me like an old cuckold with horns on his head , and say , "Get you to heaven , Beatrice , get you to heaven ; here's no place for you maids." So deliver I up my apes and away to Saint Peter .

input: For the heavens, he shows me where the men sit, and we live as merry as the day is long.
target: For the heavens , he shows me where the bachelors sit , and there live we as merry as the day is long .

input: God will not make men of metal until he makes earth.
target: Not till God make men of some other metal than earth .

input: Would a woman grieve to be overmastered with a piece of dust?
target: Would it not grieve a woman to be overmastered with a piece of valiant dust ?

input: She wanted to make an account of her life to the marl.
target: To make an account of her life to a clod of wayward marl ?

input: No, uncle, I will not.
target: No , uncle , I'll none .

input: If the Prince is too important, tell him that there is measure in everything and then dance out the answer.
target: If the Prince be too important , tell him there is measure in everything , and so dance out the answer .

input: To hear me, Hero, wooing, wedding, and repentance is as a Scotch jig, a measure, and a cinquepace.
target: For hear me , Hero , wooing , wedding , and repenting is as a Scotch jig , a measure , and a cinquepace .

input: You are passing shrewdly, Cousin.
target: Cousin , you apprehend passing shrewdly .

input: I have a good eye, my uncle.
target: I have a good eye , uncle .

input: I can see the church in the morning.
target: I can see a church by daylight .

input: The revelers are getting ready to enter.
target: The revelers are entering , brother .

input: It's a good idea to make a good room.
target: Make good room .

input: Lady, will you fight with your friend.
target: Lady , will you walk a bout with your friend ?

input: I am yours for the walk, and especially when I walk away, so you walk softly, and look sweetly, and say nothing.
target: So you walk softly , and look sweetly , and say nothing , I am yours for the walk , and especially when I walk away .

input: When do you want to say it?
target: And when please you to say so ?

input: For God to defend the lute should be like the case when I like your favor.
target: When I like your favor , for God defend the lute should be like the case !

input: My visor is on Philemon's roof and within the house is Jove.
target: My visor is Philemon's roof ; within the house is Jove .

input: If you speak love, speak softly.
target: Speak low if you speak love .

input: I would love to have you as a friend.

target: Shall we go seek Benedick and tell him of her love ?

target: Against my will I am sent to bid you come in to dinner." There's a double meaning in that .

target: If I do not love her , I am a Jew .

target: There shalt thou find my cousin Beatrice Proposing with the Prince and Claudio .

target: Whisper her ear and tell her I and Ursula Walk in the orchard , and our whole discourse Is all of her .

target: Say that thou overheardst us , And bid her steal into the pleached bower Where honeysuckles ripened by the sun Forbid the sun to enter , like favorites Made proud by princes , that advance their pride Against that power that bred it .

target: There will she hide her To listen our propose .

target: Bear thee well in it and leave us alone .

target: I'll make her come , I warrant you , presently .

target: Now , Ursula , when Beatrice doth come , As we do trace this alley up and down , Our talk must only be of Benedick .

target: When I do name him , let it be thy part To praise him more than ever man did merit .

target: My talk to thee must be how Benedick Is sick in love with Beatrice .

target: But are you sure That Benedick loves Beatrice so entirely ?

target: So says the Prince and my new-trothed lord .

target: And did they bid you tell her of it , madam ?

target: They did entreat me to acquaint her of it , But I persuaded them , if they loved Benedick , To wish him wrestle with affection And never to let Beatrice know of it .

input: Why did you decide to do that?
target: Why did you so ?

target: Doth not the gentleman Deserve as full as fortunate a bed As ever Beatrice shall couch upon ?

target: What's the matter , lieutenant ?

target: I'll beat the knave into a twiggen bottle .

target: Beat me ?

target: Dost thou prate , rogue ?

target: Nay , good lieutenant !

target: I pray you , sir , hold your hand .

target: Who's that which rings the bell ? , Diablo , ho !

target: The town will rise .

target: Fie , Fie , lieutenant , You'll be ashamed for ever .

target: For Christian shame , put by this barbarous brawl .

target: He that stirs next to carve for his own rage Holds his soul light , he dies upon his motion .

target: Silence that dreadful bell , it frights the isle From her propriety .

target: What is the matter , masters ? , Honest Iago , that looks dead with grieving , Speak , who began this ?

target: On thy love , I charge thee .

target: I do not know .

target: Swords out , and tilting one at other's breasts In opposition bloody .

target: I can not speak Any beginning to this peevish odds , And would in action glorious I had lost Those legs that brought me to a part of it .

target: Worthy Montano , you were wont be civil .

input: You unlace your reputation so you can spend your opinion on the name of a night-brawler.
target: What's the matter That you unlace your reputation thus And spend your rich opinion for the name Of a night-brawler ?

target: Give me answer to it .

input: I am hurt to danger, and Worthy.
target: Worthy Othello , I am hurt to danger .

target: Nor know I aught By me that's said or done amiss this night , Unless self-charity be sometimes a vice , And to defend ourselves it be a sin When violence assails us .

input: By heaven, my blood begins my safer guides to rule, and passion, having my best judgment collied, and assas to lead the way.
target: Now , by heaven , My blood begins my safer guides to rule , And passion , having my best judgment collied , Assays to lead the way .

input: That is monstrous.
target: Tis monstrous .

input: Who started 't? Iago.
target: Iago , who began 't ?

target: Touch me not so near .

target: I had rather have this tongue cut from my mouth Than it should do offence to Michael Cassio .

target: Yet I persuade myself to speak the truth Shall nothing wrong him .

target: When I came back , For this was brief , I found them close together At blow and thrust , even as again they were When you yourself did part them .

input: More of this matter can not be reported.
target: More of this matter can not I report .

input: As men in rage strike those that wish them best, I believe that Cassio received from him that he fled some strange indignity.
target: Though Cassio did some little wrong to him , As men in rage strike those that wish them best , Yet surely Cassio , I believe , received From him that fled some strange indignity Which patience could not pass .

input: An example will be made by me.
target: I'll make thee an example .

input: dear, what is the matter?
target: What's the matter , dear ?

target: What , are you hurt , lieutenant ?

target: Ay , past all surgery .

target: Marry , heaven forbid !

input: To make this bitter to thee, I need to be sure that my place and my spirits have the power to do it.
target: But thou must needs be sure My spirits and my place have in their power To make this bitter to thee .

target: Patience , good sir .

target: What tell'st thou me of robbing ?

target: You'll have your nephews neigh to you .

target: You'll have coursers for cousins and gennets for germans .

target: What profane wretch art thou ?

target: Reputation , reputation , reputation !

target: My reputation , Iago , my reputation !

target: As I am an honest man , I thought you had received some bodily wound .

target: There is more sense in that than in reputation .

target: You have lost no reputation at all unless you repute yourself such a loser .

target: What , man , there are ways to recover the general again .

target: Sue to him again and he's yours .

target: Drunk ?

target: And speak parrot ?

target: Swagger ?

target: And discourse fustian with one's own shadow ?

target: Had I as many mouths as Hydra , such an answer would stop them all .

target: Every inordinate cup is unblessed and the ingredient is a devil .

target: She is of so free , so kind , so apt , so blessed a disposition , she holds it a vice in her goodness not to do more than she is requested .

target: I protest , in the sincerity of love and honest kindness .

target: Good night , lieutenant , I must to the watch .

target: Good night , honest Iago .

input: What is he saying that I play the villain?
target: And what's he then that says I play the villain ?

target: When this advice is free I give and honest , Probal to thinking and indeed the course To win the Moor again ?

input: In any honest suit, inclining Desdemona to subdue is the most easy way to subdue.
target: For 'tis most easy Th ' inclining Desdemona to subdue In any honest suit .

input: As the free elements, she is framed as fruitful.
target: She's framed as fruitful As the free elements .

input: How am I supposed to tell the villain to go to his good?
target: How am I then a villain To counsel Cassio to this parallel course , Directly to his good ?

input: When devils will put the blackest sins on them, they suggest heavenly shows as a start.
target: When devils will the blackest sins put on They do suggest at first with heavenly shows As I do now .

target: And by how much she strives to do him good She shall undo her credit with the Moor .

target: So will I turn her virtue into pitch And out of her own goodness make the net That shall enmesh them all .

target: How now , Roderigo !

target: My money is almost spent , I have been tonight exceedingly well cudgeled , and I think the issue will be I shall have so much experience for my pains .

target: And so , with no money at all and a little more wit , return again to Venice .

input: How poor are they? They don't have patience.

target: Does't not go well ?

input: In the morning, 'tis troth.
target: In troth , 'tis morning .

target: Pleasure and action make the hours seem short .

target: Retire thee , go where thou art billeted .

target: Nay , get thee gone .

target: Two things are to be done : My wife must move for Cassio to her mistress .

input: She'll be set on by me.
target: I'll set her on .

input: That's how it is, Ay.
target: Ay , that's the way .

target: Masters , play here , I will content your pains .

target: Are these , I pray you , wind instruments ?

target: Ay , marry , are they , sir .

target: Oh , thereby hangs a tail .

target: Whereby hangs a tale , sir ?

target: Well , sir , we will not .

target: If you have any music that may not be heard , to 't again .

target: But , as they say , to hear music the general does not greatly care .

input: We do not have such, sir.
target: We have none such , sir .

input: Put your pipes in your bag for me to leave.
target: Then put up your pipes in your bag , for I'll away .

input: Go, disappear into the air, away!
target: Go , vanish into air , away !

input: Dost you hear me, my honest friend?
target: Dost thou hear , my honest friend ?
