target: Prithee , keep up thy quillets .

input: She is making a noise, sir.
target: She is stirring , sir .

input: I will notify her if she will stir hither.
target: If she will stir hither , I shall seem to notify unto her .

input: Iago is happy in happy time.
target: In happy time , Iago .

input: You haven't been abed yet, then?
target: You have not been abed , then ?

input: There is no reason, no.
target: Why , no .

input: Is she going to cure me of Desdemona Procure me some access?
target: My suit to her Is that she will to virtuous Desdemona Procure me some access .

input: I would like to thank you for that.
target: I humbly thank you for't .

input: Good Lieutenant, good day tomorrow.
target: Good morrow , good Lieutenant .

input: I apologize for your displeasure, but all will be fine.
target: I am sorry For your displeasure , but all will sure be well .

input: The general and his wife are talking about it, and she speaks for you.
target: The general and his wife are talking of it , And she speaks for you stoutly .

input: The Moor said that he was of great fame in Cyprus and that he might refuse to let you go.
target: The Moor replies That he you hurt is of great fame in Cyprus And great affinity , and that in wholesome wisdom He might not but refuse you .

input: He loves you so much that he needs no other suitor but his likings to bring you in again.
target: But he protests he loves you And needs no other suitor but his likings To take the safest occasion by the front To bring you in again .

input: If you think fit, or that it may be done, give me some brief discussion with Desdemona alone.
target: Yet I beseech you , If you think fit , or that it may be done , Give me advantage of some brief discourse With Desdemona alone .

input: You should come in.
target: Pray you come in .

input: I will give you a place to speak your bosom freely.
target: I will bestow you where you shall have time To speak your bosom freely .

input: I am very much bound to you.
target: I am much bound to you .

input: Iago is given to the pilot by these letters, so that he can do my duties in the senate.
target: These letters give , Iago , to the pilot , And by him do my duties to the senate .

input: I will be walking on the works to fix it for myself.
target: That done , I will be walking on the works , Repair there to me .

input: Well, my good lord, I will do it.
target: Well , my good lord , I'll do 't .

input: Gentlemen, shall we see this fortification?
target: This fortification , gentlemen , shall we see 't ?

input: We will wait for your lordship.
target: We'll wait upon your lordship .

input: I will do all my abilities in your behalf, be assured.
target: Be thou assured , good Cassio , I will do All my abilities in thy behalf .

input: Good madam, do.
target: Good madam , do .

input: I will have my lord and you again, as friendly as you were, but do not doubt.
target: Do not doubt , Cassio , But I will have my lord and you again As friendly as you were .

input: You love my lord, you do.
target: You do love my lord .

input: My general will forget my love and service, if that policy lasts so long, or feed upon such nice and waterish diet, or breed itself so out of circumstances.
target: Ay , but , lady , That policy may either last so long , Or feed upon such nice and waterish diet , Or breed itself so out of circumstances , That , I being absent and my place supplied , My general will forget my love and service .

input: My lord will never rest, I will talk him out of his patience.
target: My lord shall never rest , I'll watch him tame and talk him out of patience .

input: But if you don't know, I will tell you that we have your wrong rebuke.
target: But if you know not this my manners tell me We have your wrong rebuke .

input: From the sense of all civility, I would play and trifle with your reverence.
target: Do not believe That , from the sense of all civility , I thus would play and trifle with your reverence .

input: If she is in your house, let's loose on the justice of the state for deluding you.
target: If she be in her chamber or your house , Let loose on me the justice of the state For thus deluding you .

input: It's time to strike on the tinder!
target: Strike on the tinder , ho !

input: Give me a break, call up all my people.
target: Give me a taper , call up all my people !

input: Belief of this accident oppresses me already, it is not unlike my dream.
target: This accident is not unlike my dream , Belief of it oppresses me already .

input: Light, I say, light.
target: Light , I say , light !

input: I must leave you for now.
target: Farewell , for I must leave you .

input: It seems not to be wholesome to my place and to be producted against the Moor if I stay.
target: It seems not meet , nor wholesome to my place , To be producted ( as , if I stay , I shall ) Against the Moor .

input: Which is the case.
target: In which regard ,

input: It is said that the solicitor will rather die than give away his cause.
target: Therefore be merry , Cassio , For thy solicitor shall rather die Than give thy cause away .

input: My lord, here comes my lady.
target: Madam , here comes my lord .

input: I'm going to take my leave.
target: Madam , I'll take my leave .

input: Stay and hear me speak, why?
target: Why , stay and hear me speak .

input: Not right now, madam.
target: Madam , not now .

input: I am not fit for my own purposes, I am very ill at ease.
target: I am very ill at ease , Unfit for mine own purposes .

input: Do you have any discretion?
target: Well , do your discretion .

input: I think it's a good thing!
target: Ha !

input: I don't like that at all.
target: I like not that .

input: What are you going to say?
target: What dost thou say ?

input: Nothing, my lord, or if, I don't know what.
target: Nothing , my lord , or if , I know not what .

input: Was it not that my wife was parted from me?
target: Was not that Cassio parted from my wife ?

input: My lord, what is the name of the person?
target: Cassio , my lord ?

input: I believe he is right.
target: I do believe 'twas he .

input: How are you now, my lord?
target: How now , my lord ?

input: I have been talking with a suitor who is in your displeasure.
target: I have been talking with a suitor here , A man that languishes in your displeasure .

input: Who is you talking about?
target: Who is 't you mean ?

input: Why, your lieutenant, Cassio.
target: Why , your lieutenant , Cassio .

input: Good lord, if I have the power to move you, His present reconciliation take will be good.
target: Good my lord , If I have any grace or power to move you His present reconciliation take .

input: Call him back, I prithee.
target: I prithee , call him back .

input: Did he go now?
target: Went he hence now ?

input: He left a part of his grief with me, so I have to suffer with him.
target: Ay , sooth , so humbled That he hath left part of his grief with me To suffer with him .

input: Call him back, it is good love.
target: Good love , call him back .

input: Desdemona, don't now, sweet.
target: Not now , sweet Desdemona .

input: There were some other times.
target: Some other time .

input: But when will it be?
target: But shall 't be shortly ?

input: For you, it's the sooner, sweet.
target: The sooner , sweet , for you .

input: Is it possible to be tonight at supper?
target: Shall 't be tonight at supper ?

input: Nope, not tonight.
target: No , not tonight .

input: Tomorrow dinner, then the next day?
target: Tomorrow dinner , then ?

input: Why tomorrow night, or Tuesday morning?
target: Why , then , tomorrow night , or Tuesday morn .

input: On Tuesday noon, or night, or Wednesday morning.
target: On Tuesday noon , or night , or Wednesday morn .

input: I want to name the time, but not exceed three days.
target: I prithee name the time , but let it not Exceed three days .

input: In faith, he's penitent, and yet his trespass, in our common reason, is not a fault, because the wars must make example out of her best.
target: In faith , he's penitent , And yet his trespass , in our common reason ( Save that , they say , the wars must make example Out of her best ) is not , almost , a fault T ' incur a private check .

input: When shall he arrive?
target: When shall he come ?

input: Tell me, I need you to tell me.
target: Tell me , Othello .

input: Prithee, trust me, I could do a lot, but no more.
target: Trust me , I could do much , Prithee , no more .

input: I will deny thee nothing if he comes when he will.
target: Let him come when he will , I will deny thee nothing .

input: This is not a good thing, I would like you to wear gloves, feed on dishes, or keep you warm, I would like you to do a peculiar profit for your own person.
target: Why , this is not a boon , 'T is as I should entreat you wear your gloves , Or feed on nourishing dishes , or keep you warm , Or sue to you to do a peculiar profit To your own person .

input: I mean to touch your love when I have a suit, but it will be full of poise and difficult weight, and fearful to be granted.
target: Nay , when I have a suit Wherein I mean to touch your love indeed It shall be full of poise and difficult weight And fearful to be granted .

input: I will not deny thee anything.
target: I will deny thee nothing !

input: To leave me but a little to myself, whereon I do beseech thee, grant me this.
target: Whereon I do beseech thee , grant me this , To leave me but a little to myself .

input: Is it possible that I will deny you?
target: Shall I deny you ?

input: No, that's not true.
target: No .

input: Thank you, my lord.
target: Farewell , my lord .

input: farewell to my Desdemona
target: Farewell , my Desdemona .

input: I will come to thee straight.
target: I'll come to thee straight .

input: I do love thee, butdition catch my soul.
target: Perdition catch my soul But I do love thee !

input: Iago, what dost you say, my noble lord?
target: My noble lord , What dost thou say , Iago ?

input: Did you know your love for my lady when you wooed her?
target: Did Michael Cassio , when you wooed my lady , Know of your love ?

input: He did it from the beginning to the end.
target: He did , from first to last .

input: Why do you want to ask that?
target: Why dost thou ask ?

input: Iago, why did you think of that?
target: Why of thy thought , Iago ?

input: I didn't think he had met her before.
target: I did not think he had been acquainted with her .

input: Yes, Indeed?
target: Indeed ?

input: Yes, Indeed?
target: Indeed ?

input: Yes, indeed, Ay!
target: Ay , indeed !

input: Is it a good idea toDiscern'st you in that?
target: Discern'st thou aught in that ?

input: Is he not honest.
target: Is he not honest ?

input: My lord, was it honest?
target: Honest , my lord ?

input: Honest, ay and honest.
target: Honest , ay , honest .

input: I know for a fact that my lord for aught.
target: My lord , for aught I know .

input: What do you think about that?
target: What dost thou think ?

input: Do you think, my lord.
target: Think , my lord ?

input: Think, my lord, as if there was a monster in the picture.
target: Think , my lord ? " Alas , thou echo'st me As if there were some monster in thy thought Too hideous to be shown .

input: Something is what Thou dost mean.
target: Thou dost mean something .

input: I heard thee say that when Cassio left my wife.
target: I heard thee say even now thou lik'st not that When Cassio left my wife .

input: What did you not like about it?
target: What didst not like ?

input: When I told thee he was my counsel, he cried "Indeed" and pursed his brow together.
target: And when I told thee he was of my counsel Of my whole course of wooing , thou cried'st "Indeed ? " And didst contract and purse thy brow together As if thou then hadst shut up in thy brain Some horrible conceit .

input: Show me your love, if you dost love me.
target: If thou dost love me Show me thy thought .

input: You know I love you, my lord.
target: My lord , you know I love you .

input: I think that you are right.
target: I think thou dost .

input: I think that Michael is honest, I dare be sworn in.
target: For Michael Cassio , I dare be sworn , I think , that he is honest .

input: I think so as well.
target: I think so too .

input: Men should be what they seem, or if they are not, they might not seem that way.
target: Men should be what they seem , Or those that be not , would they might seem none !

input: Men should be what they appear to be.
target: Certain , men should be what they seem .

input: I think that the man is an honest one.
target: Why then I think Cassio's an honest man .

input: Yet there is more in this.
target: Nay , yet there's more in this .

input: I want to speak to you as to your thinkings, and give you the worst of thoughts.
target: I prithee speak to me as to thy thinkings , As thou dost ruminate , and give thy worst of thoughts The worst of words .

input: Is it possible to utter my thoughts.
target: Utter my thoughts ?

input: Iago is a stranger to the thoughts of Thou, if he is wronged and mak'st his ear.
target: Thou dost conspire against thy friend , Iago , If thou but think'st him wronged and mak'st his ear A stranger to thy thoughts .

input: What is the meaning of dost thou?
target: What dost thou mean ?

input: Good name in man and woman, dear my lord, I am the immediate jewel of their souls.
target: Good name in man and woman , dear my lord , Is the immediate jewel of their souls .

input: The person who stole my purse stole trash.
target: Who steals my purse steals trash .

input: It was mine and he has been slave to thousands.
target: Tis something , nothing : 'T was mine , 'tis his , and has been slave to thousands .

input: He makes me poor because he filches from me my good name Robs me.
target: But he that filches from me my good name Robs me of that which not enriches him And makes me poor indeed .

input: I'll know what he's thinking.
target: I'll know thy thoughts .

input: You can't, if my heart were in your hand, and I'm in your custody.
target: You can not , if my heart were in your hand , Nor shall not , whilst 'tis in my custody .

input: I think it's a good thing!
target: Ha !

input: I warn you, my lord, of jealousy.
target: Oh , beware , my lord , of jealousy !

input: The green-eyed monster mocks The meat it feeds on.
target: It is the green-eyed monster which doth mock The meat it feeds on .

input: Oh yeah, misery!
target: Oh , misery !

input: Poor and content is not as rich as it could be, but it is as poor as winter.
target: Poor and content is rich , and rich enough , But riches fineless is as poor as winter To him that ever fears he shall be poor .

input: The souls of my tribe defend themselves from jealousy.
target: Good heaven , the souls of all my tribe defend From jealousy !

input: Why is it that this is happening?
target: Why , why is this ?

input: I would make a life of jealousy, to follow still the changes of the moon.
target: Think'st thou I'd make a life of jealousy , To follow still the changes of the moon With fresh suspicions ?

input: No, absolutely!
target: No !

input: It is to be resolved to be once in doubt.
target: To be once in doubt Is to be resolved .

input: To say my wife is fair, feeds well, loves company, is free of speech, sings, plays and dances is not something I want to make me jealous of.
target: Tis not to make me jealous To say my wife is fair , feeds well , loves company , Is free of speech , sings , plays , and dances .

input: These are more moral than virtue would be.
target: Where virtue is , these are more virtuous .

input: Receive it from me as I am bound by it.
target: Therefore , as I am bound , Receive it from me .

input: I don't know if I speak of proof.
target: I speak not yet of proof .

input: Look to the left.
target: Look to 't .

input: I am familiar with our country's disposition.
target: I know our country disposition well .

input: They dare not show their husbands, because God sees the prank.
target: In Venice they do let God see the pranks They dare not show their husbands .

input: Dost you say that?
target: Dost thou say so ?

input: And so she did that.
target: And so she did .

input: Why do you want to then?
target: Why , go to then .

input: She was so young, she could see her father's eyes and give out such a strange feeling.
target: She that , so young , could give out such a seeming , To seel her father's eyes up close as oak , He thought 'twas witchcraft .

input: I am to blame for that.
target: But I am much to blame .

input: I would like to ask you for a pardon for loving you too much.
target: I humbly do beseech you of your pardon For too much loving you .

input: I will be bound to thee forever.
target: I am bound to thee forever .

input: Your spirits have been dashed a little by this.
target: I see this hath a little dashed your spirits .

input: Not a thing, not a thing.
target: Not a jot , not a jot .

input: Trust me, I am afraid it has.
target: Trust me , I fear it has .

input: I hope you will think about what Comes from my love is about.
target: I hope you will consider what is spoke Comes from my love .

input: You're moved, but I do not see it.
target: But I do see you're moved .

input: I am praying that you don't strain my speech to grosser issues or to larger reach than to suspicion.
target: I am to pray you not to strain my speech To grosser issues nor to larger reach Than to suspicion .

input: I am not going to do that.
target: I will not .

input: My speech should fall into such vile success if you do so, my lord.
target: Should you do so , my lord , My speech should fall into such vile success Which my thoughts aimed not at .

input: I see you're moved, my lord, I am a good friend of Cassio.
target: Cassio's my worthy friend , My lord , I see you're moved .

input: No, not a lot of movement.
target: No , not much moved .

input: It is time for farewell, farewell.
target: Farewell , farewell .

input: Let me know if more people perceive it.
target: If more thou dost perceive , let me know more .

input: To observe, set on your wife.
target: Set on thy wife to observe .

input: Leave me. Iago.
target: Leave me , Iago .

input: My lord, I am taking my leave.
target: My lord , I take my leave .

input: If your lady is watching too much entertainment.
target: Note if your lady strain his entertainment

input: I will be with him if you lead to the raised search and you find him.
target: That you shall surely find him , Lead to the Sagittary the raised search , And there will I be with him .

input: It's too true an evil.
target: It is too true an evil .

input: She is no longer with us.
target: Gone she is .

input: What's to come of my despised time, is naught but bitterness.
target: And what's to come of my despised time Is naught but bitterness .

input: How did you know that she was unhappy?
target: Now , Roderigo , Where didst thou see her ? , Oh , unhappy girl ! , With the Moor , say'st thou ? , Who would be a father ? , How didst thou know 'twas she ? , Oh , she deceives me Past thought ! , What said she to you ? , Get more tapers , Raise all my kindred .

input: Think you know if they are married.
target: Are they married , think you ?

input: I think that they are.
target: Truly , I think they are .

input: How did she get out, heaven?
target: Oh , heaven , how got she out ?

input: Oh, treason of the blood, that's right.
target: Oh , treason of the blood !

input: By what you see your daughters act, fathers trust not your daughters' minds.
target: Fathers , from hence trust not your daughters ' minds By what you see them act .

input: The property of youth and maidhood may be abused if there are not charms.
target: Is there not charms By which the property of youth and maidhood May be abused ?

input: Have you not read about something like that?
target: Have you not read , Roderigo , Of some such thing ?

input: Yes, sir, I have, indeed.
target: Yes , sir , I have indeed .

input: I think I can find him if you help me with the guard and go with me.
target: I think I can discover him , if you please To get good guard and go along with me .

input: Any strong or vehement importunity is welcome.
target: With any strong or vehement importunity .

input: There will be a lot of things to see in that.
target: Much will be seen in that .

input: Let me be thought too busy in my fears, as I have to fear I am, and hold her free, I do beseech your honor.
target: In the meantime , Let me be thought too busy in my fears , As worthy cause I have to fear I am , And hold her free , I do beseech your honor .

input: My government is not afraid.
target: Fear not my government .

input: I take my leave more often.
target: I once more take my leave .

input: The fellow knows all the quantities with a learned spirit and is exceeding honesty.
target: This fellow's of exceeding honesty And knows all quantities , with a learned spirit , Of human dealings .

input: I would whistle her off and let her down the wind if I could prove her haggardness.
target: If I do prove her haggard , Though that her jesses were my dear heartstrings , I'd whistle her off and let her down the wind To prey at fortune .

input: The curse of marriage is that we can call these delicate creatures ours, and not their appetites.
target: Oh , curse of marriage That we can call these delicate creatures ours And not their appetites !

input: I would rather be a toad and live in the dungeon than keep a corner in the thing I love.
target: I had rather be a toad And live upon the vapor of a dungeon Than keep a corner in the thing I love For others ' uses .

input: Prerogatived are they less than the base, that is the plague to great ones.
target: Yet 'tis the plague to great ones , Prerogatived are they less than the base .

input: Like death, Tis destiny is unshunnable.
target: Tis destiny unshunnable , like death .

input: When we do quicken, this fork plague is fated to us.
target: Even then this forked plague is fated to us When we do quicken .

input: Look at where she arrives.
target: Look where she comes .

input: Heaven ridiculed itself if she were false.
target: If she be false , heaven mocked itself .

input: I will not believe that.
target: I'll not believe 't .

input: How are you, my dear Othello.
target: How now , my dear Othello ?

input: You are invited to your dinner and the islanders are very generous.
target: Your dinner , and the generous islanders By you invited , do attend your presence .

input: I am responsible for that.
target: I am to blame .

input: Why do you speak in such a way?
target: Why do you speak so faintly ?

input: Are you not doing well?
target: Are you not well ?

input: There is a pain on my forehead.
target: I have a pain upon my forehead , here .

input: Why that is when you watch, 't will away again'.
target: Why that's with watching , 'twill away again .

input: It will be well within this hour, let me but bind it hard.
target: Let me but bind it hard , within this hour It will be well .

input: I'll join you in the room.
target: Come , I'll go in with you .

input: I am very sorry that you are not well.
target: I am very sorry that you are not well .

input: My husband has been unfaithful a hundred times.
target: My wayward husband hath a hundred times

input: She loves the token so much that she reserves it for kissing and talking to her.
target: Wooed me to steal it , but she so loves the token ( For he conjured her she should ever keep it ) That she reserves it evermore about her To kiss and talk to .

input: I will have the work done and give it to Iago.
target: I'll have the work ta'en out And give 't Iago .

input: Heaven knows what he will do with it, but I just want to please him.
target: What he will do with it Heaven knows , not I. I nothing but to please his fantasy .

input: How are you now?
target: How now !

input: What are you doing here alone?
target: What do you here alone ?

input: Do not chide at me.
target: Do not you chide .

input: I have something for you, that's for sure.
target: I have a thing for you .

input: Is that a thing for me?
target: A thing for me ?

input: It's a common thing, right?
target: It is a common thing , Ha ?

input: To have a wife that is foolish.
target: To have a foolish wife .

input: Is that everything?
target: Oh , is that all ?

input: What will you give me for the same handkerchief?
target: What will you give me now For the same handkerchief ?

input: What is that handkerchief?
target: What handkerchief ?

input: What is that handkerchief?
target: What handkerchief ?

input: The Moor first gave to Desdemona, which was why you bid me steal so many times.
target: Why , that the Moor first gave to Desdemona , That which so often you did bid me steal .

input: Hast it been taken from her?
target: Hast stolen it from her ?

input: I took 't up' because she let it drop by carelessness.
target: No , but she let it drop by negligence And , to th ' advantage , I being here , took 't up .

input: Here it is, look at it.
target: Look , here it is .

input: Give me a good wench, I need it.
target: A good wench , give it me .

input: You have been so earnest to have me filch it, what will you do with that?
target: What will you do with 't , that you have been so earnest To have me filch it ?

input: Why do you think that is?
target: Why , what is that to you ?

input: Give me another chance if it's not for some purpose.
target: If it be not for some purpose of import , Give 't me again .

input: Poor lady, she will run mad when she doesn't have it.
target: Poor lady , she'll run mad When she shall lack it .

input: Leave me and go.
target: Go , leave me .

input: The Moor is already changing with my poison.
target: The Moor already changes with my poison .

input: Where he comes is what you should look at.
target: Look , where he comes .

input: Shall ever medicine thee to that sweet sleep, not all of the drowsy syrups of the world.
target: Not poppy nor mandragora Nor all the drowsy syrups of the world , Shall ever medicine thee to that sweet sleep Which thou owedst yesterday .

input: Is it true that I'm false to you.
target: False to me ?

input: I swear it's better to be abused than to know a little about it.
target: I swear 'tis better to be much abused Than but to know 't a little .

input: How are you now, my lord?
target: How now , my lord !

input: What sense did I have in her hours of lust.
target: What sense had I in her stol'n hours of lust ?

input: I thought it didn't hurt me, but I did see it.
target: I saw 't not , thought it not , it harmed not me .

input: I had a good night's sleep and was free and merry the next night.
target: I slept the next night well , fed well , was free and merry .

input: I couldn't find her kisses on her lips.
target: I found not Cassio's kisses on her lips .

input: He was not robbed, he didn't know what was happening, and he didn't want what was happening.
target: He that is robbed , not wanting what is stol'n , Let him not know't , and he's not robbed at all .

input: I am very sorry to hear that.
target: I am sorry to hear this .

input: I was happy if the general camp had tasted her sweet body, but I had no idea.
target: I had been happy if the general camp , Pioneers and all , had tasted her sweet body , So I had nothing known .

input: Now forever, farewell the tranquil mind!
target: Oh , now forever Farewell the tranquil mind !

input: The farewell content is over!
target: Farewell content !

input: The plumed troops and the big wars make ambition virtue, goodbye.
target: Farewell the plumed troops and the big wars That makes ambition virtue !

input: Oh, farewell.
target: Oh , farewell !

input: The neighing steed and the shrill trump, The spirit-stirring drum, The royal banner, and all quality, are farewell!
target: Farewell the neighing steed and the shrill trump , The spirit-stirring drum , th ' ear-piercing fife , The royal banner , and all quality , Pride , pomp , and circumstance of glorious war !

input: The Jove's dead clamors counterfeit, and you mortal engines have rude throats.
target: And O you mortal engines , whose rude throats The immortal Jove's dead clamors counterfeit , Farewell !

input: The occupation of Othello has ended.
target: Othello's occupation's gone .

input: Is that possible, my lord?
target: Is 't possible , my lord ?

input: Is this something you've been looking for?
target: Is 't come to this ?

input: Make me to see it, or at the very least prove it, so that I don't have to think about it.
target: Make me to see 't , or at the least so prove it That the probation bear no hinge nor loop To hang a doubt on , or woe upon thy life !

input: Heaven, forgive me.
target: Oh , heaven forgive me !

input: Are you a male?
target: Are you a man ?

input: Did you have a soul or sense?
target: Have you a soul or sense ?

input: Take mine office and God will buy you.
target: God buy you , take mine office .

input: The world is monstrous!
target: O monstrous world !

input: It is not safe to be direct and honest.
target: Take note , take note , O world , To be direct and honest is not safe .

input: Don't leave, stay.
target: Nay , stay .

input: Thou shouldn't be dishonest.
target: Thou shouldst be honest .

input: For honesty is a fool and loses that it works for you.
target: I should be wise , for honesty's a fool And loses that it works for .

input: I think my wife should be honest and honest only if she is not.
target: By the world , I think my wife be honest and think she is not .

input: I think that it's just art and that it's not worth anything.
target: I think that thou art just and think thou art not .

input: I will have some evidence.
target: I'll have some proof .

input: Her name is now begrimed and black, as my own face is.
target: Her name , that was as fresh As Dian's visage , is now begrimed and black As mine own face .

input: Would I have been satisfied?
target: Would I were satisfied !

input: Sir, you are eaten up with passion, I see.
target: I see , sir , you are eaten up with passion .

input: I apologized for putting it to you.
target: I do repent me that I put it to you .

input: You would be satisfied.
target: You would be satisfied ?

input: Is it possible that would would?
target: Would ?

input: And I will do that.
target: Nay , and I will .

input: And may be, but how.
target: And may , but how ?

input: How satisfied were you, my lord?
target: How satisfied , my lord ?

input: Would you, the supervisor, allow her to be topped?
target: Would you , the supervisor , grossly gape on , Behold her topped ?

input: There is death and damnation.
target: Death and damnation !

input: Oh my gosh.
target: Oh !

input: I think it was difficult to bring them to that prospect.
target: It were a tedious difficulty , I think , To bring them to that prospect .

input: What should I say?
target: What shall I say ?

input: Where is your satisfaction?
target: Where's satisfaction ?

input: It is impossible to see this, Were they as good as goats, as hot as monkeys, as salt as wolves, and as gross as ignorant people.
target: It is impossible you should see this , Were they as prime as goats , as hot as monkeys , As salt as wolves in pride , and fools as gross As ignorance made drunk .

input: I say if imputation and strong circumstances lead directly to the door of truth you may have satisfaction.
target: But yet , I say , If imputation and strong circumstances Which lead directly to the door of truth Will give you satisfaction , you may have 't .

input: Give me a reason why she is disloyal.
target: Give me a living reason she's disloyal .

input: I don't like working in the office.
target: I do not like the office .

input: I am entered in this cause by foolish honesty and love, but I will continue.
target: But , sith I am entered in this cause so far , Pricked to 't by foolish honesty and love , I will go on .

input: I couldn't sleep because I was troubled with a raging tooth.
target: I lay with Cassio lately And , being troubled with a raging tooth , I could not sleep .

input: It's Monstrous.
target: Monstrous !

input: This was his dream, but not this one.
target: Nay , this was but his dream .

input: Though it be but a dream, it is a shrewd doubt.
target: Tis a shrewd doubt , though it be but a dream .

input: This may help to make the other proof more convincing.
target: And this may help to thicken other proofs That do demonstrate thinly .

input: I will destroy her all to pieces.
target: I'll tear her all to pieces !

input: Have you ever seen a handkerchief with strawberries in your wife's hand?
target: Tell me but this , Have you not sometimes seen a handkerchief Spotted with strawberries in your wife's hand ?

input: It speaks against her with the other proof if it is that or any that was hers.
target: If it be that , If it be that , or any that was hers , It speaks against her with the other proofs .

input: There were forty thousand lives of the slave.
target: Oh , that the slave had forty thousand lives !

input: One is too poor and weak for my revenge.
target: One is too poor , too weak for my revenge .

input: Is it true that I see it?
target: Now do I see 'tis true .

input: For 'tis of aspics' tongues, Swell, bosom, and fraught with trouble.
target: Swell , bosom , with thy fraught , For 'tis of aspics ' tongues !

target: At nine i ' th ' morning here we'll meet again .

input: The commission will bring to you quality and respect, as doth import you, if you leave some officer behind.
target: Othello , leave some officer behind And he shall our commission bring to you , And such things else of quality and respect As doth import you .

input: I assign my wife, with what else needful your good grace will think, to be sent after me.
target: To his conveyance I assign my wife , With what else needful your good grace shall think To be sent after me .

input: Wherein the toged consuls can propose as masterly as he is.
target: Wherein the toged consuls can propose As masterly as he .

input: Is it all his soldiership without practice?
target: Mere prattle without practice Is all his soldiership .

input: There's no remedy for that.
target: Why , there's no remedy .

input: The curse of service is that it is bad.
target: Tis the curse of service .

input: I am affined to love the Moor, so be judge yourself, whether I do or do not.
target: Now sir , be judge yourself , Whether I in any just term am affined To love the Moor .

target: I would not follow him then .

target: O sir , content you .

target: I follow him to serve my turn upon him .

input: We can't all be masters, and all masters can't be truly followed.
target: We can not all be masters , nor all masters Can not be truly followed .

target: You shall mark Many a duteous and knee-crooking knave That ( doting on his own obsequious bondage ) Wears out his time much like his master's ass For naught but provender , and when he's old , cashiered .

input: I need to whip me so that I can be honest.
target: Whip me such honest knaves .

input: These fellows have something in common.
target: These fellows have some soul ,

target: Let it be so .

input: Desdemona is a good place to use.
target: Use Desdemona well .

input: If you have eyes to see, look to her, Moor.
target: Look to her , Moor , if thou hast eyes to see .

input: She deceived her father and may he rest in peace.
target: She has deceived her father , and may thee .

input: Iago must leave to thee my life upon her faith.
target: My life upon her faith ! , Honest Iago , My Desdemona must I leave to thee .

input: I want the wife to attend on her and bring them after in the best advantage.
target: I prithee , let thy wife attend on her , And bring them after in the best advantage .

input: I have but an hour of love, of worldly matter and direction, to spend with thee.
target: Come , Desdemona , I have but an hour Of love , of worldly matter and direction , To spend with thee .

input: Obeying the time is what we must do.
target: We must obey the time .

input: Iago is the name of the person.
target: Iago .

input: What do you think about the noble heart?
target: What say'st thou , noble heart ?

input: I don't know what to do, think'st Thou.
target: What will I do , think'st thou ?

input: Go to bed and sleep, why?
target: Why , go to bed , and sleep .

input: I am going to drown myself.
target: I will incontinently drown myself .

input: I will never love thee again if you do it.
target: If thou dost I shall never love thee after .

input: The silly gentleman asked why.
target: Why , thou silly gentleman !

input: Oh, villainous.
target: Oh , villainous !

input: I have looked at the world for four years and I never found a man that knew how to love himself or a benefit.
target: I have looked upon the world for four times seven years , and since I could distinguish betwixt a benefit and an injury I never found man that knew how to love himself .

input: I would change my humanity with a baboon and drown myself for the love of a guinea hen, that's what I would say.
target: Ere I would say I would drown myself for the love of a guinea hen , I would change my humanity with a baboon .

input: I don't know what I should do.
target: What should I do ?

input: It is my shame to be so fond, but it is not something I can do to change.
target: I confess it is my shame to be so fond , but it is not in my virtue to amend it .

input: Is there any virtue?
target: Virtue ?

input: There is a fig.
target: A fig !

input: It is in ourselves that we are either this or that.
target: Tis in ourselves that we are thus or thus .

input: Our wills are gardeners, and our bodies are our gardens.
target: Our bodies are our gardens , to the which our wills are gardeners .

input: If we want to grow lettuce, set hyssop, and weed up thyme, we can either have it sterile, or distract it with many herbs, or both.
target: So that if we will plant nettles or sow lettuce , set hyssop and weed up thyme , supply it with one gender of herbs or distract it with many , either to have it sterile with idleness , or manured with industry , why , the power and corrigible authority of this lies in our wills .

input: The blood and baseness of our natures would cause us to make a lot of conclusions if the balance of our lives did not have one scale of reason to justify another of sensuality.
target: If the balance of our lives had not one scale of reason to poise another of sensuality , the blood and baseness of our natures would conduct us to most prepost'rous conclusions .

input: We have reason to cool our lusts and motions.
target: But we have reason to cool our raging motions , our carnal stings , our unbitted lusts .

input: It can't be that way.
target: It can not be .

input: It is just a lust of the blood and a permission of the will.
target: It is merely a lust of the blood and a permission of the will .

input: Come and be a man.
target: Come , be a man .

input: Do you want to own yourself?
target: Drown thyself ?

input: Do you own cats and blind puppies?
target: Drown cats and blind puppies !

input: I confess that I knit to my friend with cables of perdurable toughness.
target: I have professed me thy friend , and I confess me knit to thy deserving with cables of perdurable toughness .

input: I could never do a better job than I am at the moment.
target: I could never better stead thee than now .

input: Put your money in your purse.
target: Put money in thy purse .

input: The Moors will change their wills so fill their purse with money.
target: These Moors are changeable in their wills , fill thy purse with money .

input: The food that will be served to him soon will be just as bitter as coloquintida.
target: The food that to him now is as luscious as locusts shall be to him shortly as bitter as coloquintida .

input: She needs to change for the younger generation.
target: She must change for youth .

input: Put your money in your purse.
target: Therefore , put money in thy purse .

input: Do it in a more delicate way than drown if you need to.
target: If thou wilt needs damn thyself , do it a more delicate way than drowning .

input: All the money should be made by you.
target: Make all the money thou canst .

input: If sanctimony and a frail vow betwixt an arrogant barbarian and Venetian be not too hard for my wits and all the tribe of hell.
target: If sanctimony and a frail vow betwixt an erring barbarian and supersubtle Venetian be not too hard for my wits and all the tribe of hell , thou shalt enjoy her .

input: It was a pox of drowned thyself.
target: A pox of drowning thyself !

input: It's time to clean out of the way.
target: Tis clean out of the way .

input: Thou art sure of me.
target: Thou art sure of me .

input: Go and make some money.
target: Go , make money .

input: I have told thee many times that I hate the Moor, and I have told thee again and again.
target: I have told thee often , and I re-tell thee again and again , I hate the Moor .

input: We should be conjunctive in our revenge against him.
target: Let us be conjunctive in our revenge against him .

input: Go and provide the money.
target: Traverse , go , provide thy money .

input: tomorrow we will have more of this.
target: We will have more of this tomorrow .

input: Adieu, Adieu.
target: Adieu .

input: Where are we going to meet this morning?
target: Where shall we meet i ' th ' morning ?

input: At my place of residence.
target: At my lodging .

input: I will be with them.
target: I'll be with thee betimes .

input: Do you hear that there is no more of this?
target: No more of drowning , do you hear ?

input: I have been changed.
target: I am changed .

input: Go to and say farewell.
target: Go to , farewell .

input: You should put money in your purse.
target: Put money enough in your purse .

input: I will sell all of my land.
target: I'll sell all my land .

input: Do I ever make my purse look like a fool?
target: Thus do I ever make my fool my purse .

input: I have gained knowledge that should not be used for anything other than my sport and profits.
target: For I mine own gained knowledge should profane If I would time expend with such a snipe But for my sport and profit .

input: I don't like the Moor, and it is thought abroad that he's done my office.
target: I hate the Moor , And it is thought abroad that 'twixt my sheets He's done my office .

input: I know not if it's true, but I will do as surety if it is.
target: I know not if 't be true , But I , for mere suspicion in that kind , Will do as if for surety .

input: He holds me in good hands.
target: He holds me well .

input: He's a proper man, that's for sure.
target: Cassio's a proper man .

input: Let me look at it now.
target: Let me see now ,

input: To get his place and to make my will happen.
target: To get his place and to plume up my will In double knavery .

input: How do you do it?
target: How ?

input: How do you do it?
target: How ?

input: Let's see what happens.
target: Let's see .

input: I have a thing for that.
target: I have 't .

input: What can you see from the cape at sea?
target: What from the cape can you discern at sea ?

input: There was nothing at all.
target: Nothing at all .

input: It is a high-pitched flood.
target: It is a high-wrought flood .

input: The wind spoke loudly at land, and a full blast shook our battlements.
target: Methinks the wind hath spoke aloud at land , A fuller blast ne'er shook our battlements .

input: What should we know about this?
target: What shall we hear of this ?

input: There is a segregation of the fleet from Turkey.
target: A segregation of the Turkish fleet .

input: The wind-shaked surge, with high and monstrous mane, seems to cast water on the burning bear, and quench the guards of the ever-fixed pole, for do but stand upon the foaming shore.
target: For do but stand upon the foaming shore , The chidden billow seems to pelt the clouds , The wind-shaked surge , with high and monstrous mane , Seems to cast water on the burning bear , And quench the guards of th ' ever-fixed pole .

input: On the enchafed flood was not a view I liked.
target: I never did like molestation view On the enchafed flood .

input: The Turkish fleet will be drowned if they are not ensheltered.
target: If that the Turkish fleet Be not ensheltered and embayed , they are drowned .

input: It is not possible they will bear it out.
target: It is impossible they bear it out .

input: Our wars are over, News!
target: News , lads , Our wars are done !

input: The Turks were banged by the desperate tempest that halted their designment.
target: The desperate tempest hath so banged the Turks , That their designment halts .

input: A noble ship of Venice Hath saw a grievous wreck and sufferance on most part of their fleet.
target: A noble ship of Venice Hath seen a grievous wreck and sufferance On most part of their fleet .

input: How do you do it?
target: How ?

input: Is this not true?
target: Is this true ?

input: Lieutenant to the warlike Moor Othello, Michael Cassio, came on shore.
target: Michael Cassio , Lieutenant to the warlike Moor Othello , Is come on shore .

input: The Moor is here in full commission for Cyprus.
target: The Moor himself at sea And is in full commission here for Cyprus .

input: I am happy about it.
target: I am glad on 't .

input: The governor is a worthy one.
target: Tis a worthy governor .

input: They were violent and foul, and parted tempest.
target: For they were parted With foul and violent tempest .

input: I have served him and the man commands like a full soldier, so please pray for him.
target: Pray heavens he be , For I have served him , and the man commands Like a full soldier .

input: Let's do it, come.
target: Come , let's do so .

input: For every minute is how much more arrivance there is.
target: For every minute is expectancy Of more arrivance .

input: Thanks, you are the bravest of this warlike isle, that approves the Moor.
target: Thanks , you the valiant of this warlike isle That so approve the Moor .

input: Let the heavens give him defense against the elements because I have lost him on a dangerous sea.
target: Oh , let the heavens Give him defense against the elements , For I have lost him on a dangerous sea .

input: Is he well transported?
target: Is he well shipped ?

input: Stand in bold cure because his bark is stoutly timbered and his pilot is very expert and approved allowance.
target: His bark is stoutly timbered and his pilot Of very expert and approved allowance Therefore my hopes , not surfeited to death , Stand in bold cure .

input: What noise is that?
target: What noise ?

input: I am praying that you will tell us who that is arrived.
target: I pray you sir , go forth And give us truth who 'tis that is arrived .

input: I will do that.
target: I shall .

input: But good lieutenant, is your general weak?
target: But good lieutenant , is your general wived ?

input: The ancient Iago is ancient to the general population.
target: Tis one Iago , ancient to the general .

input: What is this person?
target: What is she ?

input: The riches of the ship are on the shore.
target: Oh , behold , The riches of the ship is come on shore !

input: Allow her to have your knees, you men of Cyprus.
target: You men of Cyprus , let her have your knees .

input: To thee, lady, and the grace of heaven, before, behind thee, and on every hand, Enwheel thee round.
target: Hail to thee , lady , and the grace of heaven , Before , behind thee , and on every hand , Enwheel thee round !

input: I would like to thank you very much.
target: I thank you , valiant Cassio .

input: Can you tell me what the future holds for my lord?
target: What tidings can you tell me of my lord ?

input: He isn't yet arrived.
target: He is not yet arrived .

input: I don't know, but he's well and will be here soon.
target: Nor know I aught But that he's well and will be shortly here .

input: I fear, but I don't.
target: Oh , but I fear .

input: How did you misplace your company?
target: How lost you company ?

input: The sea and skies had a big part to play in our fellowship.
target: The great contention of the sea and skies Parted our fellowship , But , hark !

input: You can see for the news.
target: See for the news .

input: I would not be Iago if I were the Moor, it is as certain as you are.
target: For , sir , It is as sure as you are Roderigo , Were I the Moor , I would not be Iago .

input: I am not what I think I am.
target: I am not what I am .

input: Do with a loud accent and dire yell, as when the fire was spotted in populous cities.
target: Do , with like timorous accent and dire yell As when , by night and negligence , the fire Is spied in populous cities .

input: What, ho, Brabantio.
target: What , ho , Brabantio !

input: Signior Brabantio, ho.
target: Signior Brabantio , ho !

input: They were thieves.
target: Thieves !

input: They were thieves.
target: Thieves !

input: You should look at your house, your daughter and your bags.
target: Look to your house , your daughter , and your bags !

input: They were thieves.
target: Thieves !

input: They were thieves.
target: thieves !

input: Is she going to give you so much of her lips, you'll have enough?
target: Sir , would she give you so much of her lips As of her tongue she oft bestows on me , You'll have enough .

input: When I have leave to sleep, I still find it.
target: I find it still , when I have leave to sleep .

input: She puts her tongue a little in her heart, and chides with thinking.
target: Marry , before your ladyship , I grant , She puts her tongue a little in her heart And chides with thinking .

input: You don't have much reason to say that.
target: You have little cause to say so .

input: Come on, come on, come on.
target: Come on , come on .

input: You have pictures out of door, bells in your parlors, wild-cats in your kitchens, devils being offended, players in your housewifery, and housewives in your beds.
target: You are pictures out of door , bells in your parlors , wild-cats in your kitchens , saints in your injuries , devils being offended , players in your housewifery , and housewives in your beds .

input: Oh, fie upon thee, slanderer!
target: Oh , fie upon thee , slanderer !

input: It is true, or else I am a Turk.
target: Nay , it is true , or else I am a Turk .

input: You wake up to play and go to bed to work.
target: You rise to play and go to bed to work .

input: Let me not, that's all.
target: No , let me not .

input: If you should praise me, what would you write about me?
target: What wouldst thou write of me , if thou should'st praise me ?

input: If not critical, do not put me to 't', for I am nothing.
target: O gentle lady , do not put me to 't , For I am nothing , if not critical .

input: Come on and do the test.
target: Come on , assay .

input: I am Ay and I am madam.
target: Ay , madam .

input: I am not merry but I do beguile the thing that I am.
target: I am not merry , but I do beguile The thing I am by seeming otherwise .

input: How would you praise me?
target: Come , how wouldst thou praise me ?

input: It was well praised!
target: Well praised !

input: If she is black and has a wit, she will find a white that will fit her.
target: If she be black , and thereto have a wit , She'll find a white that shall her blackness fit .

input: It was worse and worse.
target: Worse and worse !

input: How would it be if it were fair and foolish.
target: How if fair and foolish ?

input: Oh, a lot of ignorantness!
target: Oh , heavy ignorance !

input: The worst is praised by Thou.
target: Thou praisest the worst best .

input: But what praise could be given to a deserving woman, one that in the authority of her merit did justly put on the vouch of very malice itself?
target: But what praise couldst thou bestow on a deserving woman indeed , one that in the authority of her merit did justly put on the vouch of very malice itself ?

input: She was always fair and never proud, had a tongue at will, never lacked gold, and went never gay, but she was angered and said "Now I may."
target: She that was ever fair and never proud , Had tongue at will and yet was never loud , Never lacked gold and yet went never gay , Fled from her wish and yet said "Now I may , " She that being angered , her revenge being nigh , Bade her wrong stay and her displeasure fly , She that in wisdom never was so frail To change the cod's head for the salmon's tail , She that could think and ne'er disclose her mind , See suitors following and not look behind , She was a wight , if ever such wights were , To do what ?

input: To chronicle small beer and suckle fools.
target: To suckle fools and chronicle small beer .

input: The conclusion is most impotent and useless.
target: Oh , most lame and impotent conclusion !

input: Emilia, do not learn of him, though he be your husband.
target: Do not learn of him , Emilia , though he be thy husband .

input: How do you say you're with us?
target: How say you , Cassio ?

input: Is he not a very liberal counselor.
target: Is he not a most profane and liberal counselor ?

input: He speaks to his mother, madam.
target: He speaks home , madam .

input: You may like him more in the soldier than in the scholar.
target: You may relish him more in the soldier than in the scholar .

input: I am familiar with his trumpet.
target: I know his trumpet .

input: Is it really so?
target: Tis truly so .

input: Let's meet him and get to know him.
target: Let's meet him and receive him .

input: Where is he coming?
target: Lo , where he comes !

input: Oh my fair warrior!
target: Oh my fair warrior !

input: My dear friend, I adore you, Othello!
target: My dear Othello !

input: It gives me great pleasure to see you here before me.
target: It gives me wonder great as my content To see you here before me .

input: Oh, my soul's happiness!
target: Oh , my soul's joy !

input: If it were to die, I fear that my soul would be so happy that it wouldn't want to live anymore.
target: If it were now to die , 'Twere now to be most happy , for I fear My soul hath her content so absolute That not another comfort like to this Succeeds in unknown fate .

input: Even as our days do grow, our loves and comforts should increase.
target: The heavens forbid But that our loves and comforts should increase , Even as our days do grow .

input: Thank you to that, sweet powers!
target: Amen to that , sweet powers !

input: I don't speak enough about this content.
target: I can not speak enough of this content .

input: It is too much of a pleasure to stop me here.
target: It stops me here , it is too much of joy .

input: Come and let us go to the castle.
target: Come , let us to the castle .

input: News and friends.
target: News , friends !

input: The wars are over and the Turks are drowned.
target: Our wars are done , the Turks are drowned .

input: I have found great love amongst them, so how does my old acquaintances of this isle feel about me?
target: How does my old acquaintance of this isle ? , Honey , you shall be well desired in Cyprus , I have found great love amongst them .

input: The master should be brought to the citadel.
target: Bring thou the master to the citadel .

input: He is a good one, and his worthiness does challenge a lot of respect.
target: He is a good one , and his worthiness Does challenge much respect. , Come , Desdemona , Once more , well met at Cyprus .

input: Come hither, do you meet me at the harbor?
target: Do thou meet me presently at the harbor. , Come hither .

input: The guard has a lieutenant watching him on the court.
target: The lieutenant tonight watches on the court of guard .

input: Desdemona is in love with him and I must tell you this.
target: First , I must tell thee this : Desdemona is directly in love with him .

input: Is it with him?
target: With him ?

input: Why is it not possible.
target: Why , 'tis not possible .

input: Allow your soul to be instructed by laying your finger on the ground.
target: Lay thy finger thus , and let thy soul be instructed .

input: All of the Moor is not good.
target: All which the Moor is defective in .

input: This granted, as it is a most pregnant and unforced position, who stands so great in the degree of this fortune as Cassio does, sir?
target: Now sir , this granted , as it is a most pregnant and unforced position , who stands so eminent in the degree of this fortune as Cassio does ?

input: The knave is handsome, young, and has all the necessary qualities that the folly and green minds look after.
target: Besides , the knave is handsome , young , and hath all those requisites in him that folly and green minds look after .

input: I can't believe that she does that.
target: I can not believe that in her .

input: She's in very good condition.
target: She's full of most blessed condition .

input: The wine she drinks is made from grapes.
target: The wine she drinks is made of grapes .

input: She would never have liked the Moor if she had been blessed.
target: If she had been blessed , she would never have loved the Moor .

input: The pudding is Blessed.
target: Blessed pudding !

input: Didst not mark that?
target: Didst not mark that ?

input: Their breaths embraced each other after they met so near with their lips.
target: They met so near with their lips that their breaths embraced together .

input: It's Pish!
target: Pish !

input: But, sir, be ruled by me.
target: But , sir , be you ruled by me .

input: You were brought from Venice by me.
target: I have brought you from Venice .

input: I'll lay 't upon you' if you watch you tonight for the command.
target: Watch you tonight for the command , I'll lay 't upon you .

input: You don't know that Cassio knows you aren't.
target: Cassio knows you not .

input: I will be close to you.
target: I'll not be far from you .

input: Do you find a reason to anger Cassio, either by speaking too loud or tainting his discipline, or from what other course you please, which time will be more favorable minister?
target: Do you find some occasion to anger Cassio , either by speaking too loud , or tainting his discipline , or from what other course you please , which the time shall more favorably minister .

input: Well, that's right.
target: Well .

input: He's very sudden in his movements, and may strike at you.
target: Sir , he's rash and very sudden in choler , and haply may strike at you .

input: Allow him to believe that he may.
target: Provoke him that he may .

input: I will cause these of Cyprus to revolt, whose qualification will come into no true taste again, but by the displanting of Cassio.
target: For even out of that will I cause these of Cyprus to mutiny , whose qualification shall come into no true taste again but by the displanting of Cassio .

input: If you can bring it to any opportunity, I will do this.
target: I will do this , if you can bring it to any opportunity .

input: I want thee to know that.
target: I warrant thee .

input: You can meet me by and at the citadel.
target: Meet me by and by at the citadel .

input: I have to fetch his health issues.
target: I must fetch his necessaries ashore .

input: The farewell is over.
target: Farewell .

input: Adieu, Adieu.
target: Adieu .

input: The thought whereof Doth, like a poisonous mineral, gnawed my insides, and nothing can or will satisfy my soul until I am evened with him, wife for wife.
target: The thought whereof Doth , like a poisonous mineral , gnaw my inwards , And nothing can or shall content my soul Till I am evened with him , wife for wife .

input: I put the Moor into a jealousy so strong that my judgement can not cure.
target: Or , failing so , yet that I put the Moor At least into a jealousy so strong That judgment can not cure .

input: The celebration of his nuptial is the main reason for these beneficial news.
target: For besides these beneficial news , it is the celebration of his nuptial .

input: It was his pleasure that should be proclaimed.
target: So much was his pleasure should be proclaimed .

input: All offices are open and there is no need to leave until the bell has rung eleven.
target: All offices are open , and there is full liberty of feasting from this present hour of five till the bell have told eleven .

input: The isle of Cyprus and our general Othello are in my prayers.
target: Bless the isle of Cyprus and our noble general Othello !

input: Iago is the most honest person.
target: Iago is most honest .

input: Thank you Michael, good night.
target: Michael , good night .

input: Let me have a speech with you tomorrow. The purchase made and the fruits will come.
target: Tomorrow with your earliest Let me have speech with you. , Come , my dear love , The purchase made , the fruits are to ensue : That profit's yet to come 'tween me and you .

input: Thank you for a good night.
target: Good night .

input: Iago, welcome to the family.
target: Welcome , Iago .

input: We need to be on the watch.
target: We must to the watch .

input: The general cast us early for the love of his Desdemona, who let us not blame.
target: Our general cast us thus early for the love of his Desdemona , who let us not therefore blame .

input: What is the reason for this terrible summons?
target: What is the reason of this terrible summons ?

input: What is the situation there?
target: What is the matter there ?

input: Is all of your family within you?
target: Signior , is all your family within ?

input: Are you able to get into your doors?
target: Are your doors locked ?

input: Where are you going to ask you this?
target: Why , wherefore ask you this ?

input: Zounds, sir, you have been robbed.
target: Zounds , sir , you're robbed !

input: Put on your gown, for shame.
target: For shame , put on your gown .

input: Half your soul has been lost, your heart is bursting.
target: Your heart is burst , you have lost half your soul .

input: An old black ram is tupping your white ewe, even now.
target: Even now , now , very now , an old black ram Is tupping your white ewe .

input: If you don't wake the citizens with the bell, the devil will make a grandsire of you.
target: Arise , arise , Awake the snorting citizens with the bell Or else the devil will make a grandsire of you .

input: Arise, I say!
target: Arise , I say !

input: Have you lost your sense of humor?
target: What , have you lost your wits ?

input: Do you know the voice of the reverend signior?
target: Most reverend signior , do you know my voice ?

input: Not me, not at all.
target: Not I .

input: What are you doing?
target: What are you ?

input: I'm called Roderigo and I have a name.
target: My name is Roderigo .

input: I have asked thee not to say anything about my doors.
target: I have charged thee not to haunt about my doors .

input: I have said to you that my daughter is not for thee.
target: In honest plainness thou hast heard me say My daughter is not for thee .

input: Sir, sir, sir.
target: Sir , sir , sir ,

input: She's a fresh and delicate creature.
target: Indeed she's a most fresh and delicate creature .

input: She has an amazing eye.
target: What an eye she has !

input: An inviting eye, and yet I think of it as modest.
target: An inviting eye , and yet methinks right modest .

input: Is it not an alarum to love her when she speaks?
target: And when she speaks , is it not an alarum to love ?

input: She is absolutely perfect.
target: She is indeed perfection .

input: Well, happiness to their sheets.
target: Well , happiness to their sheets !

input: Iago, not tonight, good.
target: Not tonight , good Iago .

input: I don't like drinking and I have poor and unhappy brains.
target: I have very poor and unhappy brains for drinking .

input: I would like to see courtesy invent some other custom of entertainment.
target: I could well wish courtesy would invent some other custom of entertainment .

input: Oh, they are our friends.
target: Oh , they are our friends .

input: There is only one cup.
target: But one cup .

input: I'll let you drink from me.
target: I'll drink for you .

input: I have drunk but one cup tonight, and that was craftily qualified as well, and behold what innovation it makes here.
target: I have drunk but one cup tonight , and that was craftily qualified too , and behold what innovation it makes here .

input: It's a night of celebrations, man.
target: What , man , 'tis a night of revels !

input: The people who want it the most are the people who want it the most.
target: The gallants desire it .

input: Where are they located?
target: Where are they ?

input: There is a door here.
target: Here at the door .

input: I am praying you call them in.
target: I pray you call them in .

input: I'll do it, but it doesn't like me.
target: I'll do 't , but it dislikes me .

input: He'll be as full of quarrel and offense as my young mistress if I can get one cup upon him.
target: If I can fasten but one cup upon him , With that which he hath drunk tonight already , He'll be as full of quarrel and offense As my young mistress ' dog .

input: Am I going to take action against this bunch of drunkards that may offend the isle?
target: Now 'mongst this flock of drunkards Am I to put our Cassio in some action That may offend the isle .

input: But here they arrive.
target: But here they come .

input: If consequence do but approve my dream, my boat sails with wind and stream.
target: If consequence do but approve my dream My boat sails freely , both with wind and stream .

input: They have given me a rouse already.
target: Fore heaven , they have given me a rouse already .

input: Good faith, a little one and not past a beer, as I am a soldier.
target: Good faith , a little one , not past a pint , As I am a soldier .

input: There is some wine.
target: Some wine , ho !

input: An excellent song is Fore Heaven.
target: Fore heaven , an excellent song .

input: I learned it in England, where they are the most potent.
target: I learned it in England where indeed they are most potent in potting .

input: Drink, ho, are nothing to your English, your German, and your Danes.
target: Your Dane , your German , and your swag-bellied Hollander , Drink , ho ! , are nothing to your English .

input: Is your Englishman so knowledgeable in drinking?
target: Is your Englishman so expert in his drinking ?

input: He drinks you with facility your dead drunk, he sweats not to overthrow your Almain.
target: Why , he drinks you with facility your Dane dead drunk ; he sweats not to overthrow your Almain .

input: To the overall health of our population.
target: To the health of our general !

input: I will do you justice, lieutenant, and I am for it.
target: I am for it , lieutenant , and I'll do you justice .

input: Oh, England is sweet.
target: Oh , sweet England !

input: This is a more beautiful song than the other.
target: Why , this is a more exquisite song than the other .

input: Will you be able to hear it again?
target: Will you hear 't again ?

input: I don't hold him to be worthy of his place because he does those things.
target: No , for I hold him to be unworthy of his place that does those things .

input: Heaven is above all, and there must be souls saved and not saved.
target: Well , heaven's above all , and there be souls must be saved , and there be souls must not be saved .

input: Excellent lieutenant, it's true.
target: It's true , good lieutenant .

input: I hope to be saved, no offence to the general or any man of quality, for my own part.
target: For mine own part , no offence to the general nor any man of quality , I hope to be saved .

input: And so do I as well, lieutenant.
target: And so do I too , lieutenant .

input: By your leave, but not before me.
target: Ay , but ( by your leave ) not before me .

input: The lieutenant is going to be saved before the ancients.
target: The lieutenant is to be saved before the ancient .

input: Let's not have any more of this, let's focus on our business.
target: Let's have no more of this , let's to our affairs. , Forgive us our sins ! , Gentlemen , let's look to our business .

input: Do not think that I am drunk.
target: Do not think , gentlemen , I am drunk .

input: I am not drinking anymore.
target: I am not drunk now .

input: I speak well enough and I can stand well enough.
target: I can stand well enough , and I speak well enough .

input: Well done, well done!
target: Excellent well !

input: Well then, why, very well.
target: Why , very well then .

input: You should not think that I am drunk.
target: You must not think then that I am drunk .

input: It is pity of him.
target: Tis pity of him .

input: Is he often this way?
target: But is he often thus ?

input: The beginning to his sleep is here.
target: Tis evermore the prologue to his sleep .

input: He will watch the horologe if he drinks rock not his cradle.
target: He'll watch the horologe a double set If drink rock not his cradle .

input: The general were put in mind of it.
target: It were well The general were put in mind of it .

input: Is this not the case?
target: Is not this true ?

input: It's a pity that the noble Moor should hazard such a place as his own second home.
target: And 'tis great pity that the noble Moor Should hazard such a place as his own second With one of an ingraft infirmity .

input: "So to the Moor" was an honest action to take.
target: It were an honest action to say So to the Moor .

input: So, why.
target: Why , so .

input: Have I done a good job today?
target: Now have I done a good day's work .

input: You peers, continue this united league.
target: You peers , continue this united league .

input: Don't lie about your hatred.
target: Dissemble not your hatred .

input: Don't wear your love on your sleeve.
target: Swear your love .

input: My true heart's love is sealed with my hand.
target: And with my hand I seal my true heart's love .

input: I love Hastings with all of my heart.
target: And I as I love Hastings with my heart .

input: Wife, love Lord Hastings, you have been factious one against the other.
target: You have been factious one against the other. , Wife , love Lord Hastings .

input: Hastings and Dorset love Lord Marquess.
target: Dorset , embrace him. , Hastings , love Lord Marquess .

input: I protest this interchange of love because my part will be in violation.
target: This interchange of love , I here protest , Upon my part shall be inviolable .

input: I swear, and so do you.
target: And so swear I .

input: Buckingham, seal this league with your embracements to my wife's allies and make me happy in your unity.
target: Now , princely Buckingham , seal thou this league With thy embracements to my wife's allies And make me happy in your unity .

input: Buckingham, Is this your vow unto my sickly heart?
target: A pleasing cordial , princely Buckingham , Is this thy vow unto my sickly heart .

input: Sir Richard Ratcliffe and the duke will be here in good time.
target: And in good time , Here comes Sir Richard Ratcliffe and the duke .

input: Good morning to my king and queen, and princely peers, a happy time of the day.
target: Good morrow to my sovereign king and queen , And , princely peers , a happy time of day .

input: As we have spent the day, happy indeed.
target: Happy indeed , as we have spent the day .

input: A blessed labor, my most important lord.
target: A blessed labor , my most sovereign lord .

input: I want all good men's love, and I hate it when I am at enmity.
target: Tis death to me to be at enmity ; I hate it , and desire all good men's love .

input: This is a holy day and should be kept.
target: A holy day shall this be kept hereafter .

input: I would to God that all of the troubles were compounded.
target: I would to God all strifes were well compounded .

input: My lord, I would like for you to take Clarence to your grace.
target: My sovereign lord , I do beseech your Highness To take our brother Clarence to your grace .

input: Why did I not offer love for this, to be so violated in this royal presence?
target: Why , madam , have I offered love for this , To be so flouted in this royal presence ?

input: Who knows if the gentle duke is still alive.
target: Who knows not that the gentle duke is dead ?

input: Who knows if he is alive or dead.
target: Who knows not he is dead !

input: Who knows if he is a man or not.
target: Who knows he is ?

input: What a world is this, all-seeing heaven!
target: All-seeing heaven , what a world is this !

input: I am so pale, Lord Dorset, as the rest.
target: Look I so pale , Lord Dorset , as the rest ?

input: Is Clarence alive and well?
target: Is Clarence dead ?

input: The order had been reversed.
target: The order was reversed .

input: By your first order, he died, and that a winged Mercury did bear.
target: But he , poor man , by your first order died , And that a winged Mercury did bear .

input: The countermand came too slow to see him buried.
target: Some tardy cripple bear the countermand , That came too lag to see him buried .

input: God grant that some, less noble and less loyal, Nearer in bloody thoughts, and not in blood, and Deserve not worse than wretched Clarence did, and yet go current from suspicion.
target: God grant that some , less noble and less loyal , Nearer in bloody thoughts , and not in blood , Deserve not worse than wretched Clarence did , And yet go current from suspicion .

input: Peace and I prithee.
target: I prithee , peace .

input: My soul is filled with sadness.
target: My soul is full of sorrow .

input: Unless you hear me, I will not rise.
target: I will not rise unless your Highness hear me .

input: Then say what you need to.
target: Then say at once what is it thou requests .

input: A gentleman Lately attendant on the duke of Norfolk was slew today by the forfeiture of the sovereignty of my servant's life.
target: The forfeit , sovereign , of my servant's life , Who slew today a riotous gentleman Lately attendant on the duke of Norfolk .

input: We know that Brakenbury has a charge and will obey it.
target: We know thy charge , Brakenbury , and will obey .

input: We are the queen's servants and have to obey.
target: We are the queen's abjects and must obey. , Brother , farewell .

input: I know it's nice for both of us.
target: I know it pleaseth neither of us well .

input: Your imprisonment will not last very long.
target: Well , your imprisonment shall not be long .

input: I will either deliver you or lie for you.
target: I will deliver you or else lie for you .

input: Don't be impatient, have patience.
target: Meantime , have patience .

input: I have to perforce.
target: I must perforce .

input: The farewell is over.
target: Farewell .

input: The path that shalt ne'er return is the one that you should be following.
target: Go tread the path that thou shalt ne'er return .

input: Clarence, I love you so much that I will send your soul to heaven, if heaven will take the present at our hands.
target: Simple , plain Clarence , I do love thee so That I will shortly send thy soul to heaven , If heaven will take the present at our hands .

input: But who comes here?
target: But who comes here ?

input: My lord, good time of day.
target: Good time of day unto my gracious lord .

input: As much as I can for my good lord.
target: As much unto my good Lord Chamberlain .

input: Are you accepted to the open air?
target: Well are you welcome to the open air .

input: How did your lordship cause your imprisonment?
target: How hath your lordship brooked imprisonment ?

input: My brother's punishment was bitter because his fault was thought to be the reason he killed no man.
target: My brother killed no man ; his fault was thought , And yet his punishment was bitter death .

input: Who filed a lawsuit for him?
target: Who sued to me for him ?

input: The fruits of rashness are shown here.
target: This is the fruits of rashness .

input: When they heard of Clarence's death, the guilty kindred of the queen appeared pale.
target: Marked you not How that the guilty kindred of the queen Looked pale when they did hear of Clarence ' death ?

input: They urged the king to continue with it.
target: O , they did urge it still unto the king .

input: It will be revenged by God.
target: God will revenge it .

input: Will you come and comfort Edward with our company?
target: Come , lords , will you go To comfort Edward with our company ?

input: We are waiting upon your Grace.
target: We wait upon your Grace .

input: Tell us if our father is dead.
target: Good grandam , tell us , is our father dead ?

input: No, boy, no.
target: No , boy .

input: You mistake my cousins, they are both pretty.
target: My pretty cousins , you mistake me both .

input: Then, you conclude, my grandam, he is dead.
target: Then , you conclude , my grandam , he is dead .

input: The king mine uncle is to blame for it.
target: The king mine uncle is to blame for it .

input: All to that effect, God will revenge it, whom I will importune With earnest prayers.
target: God will revenge it , whom I will importune With earnest prayers , all to that effect .

input: And so will I as well.
target: And so will I .

input: There is peace, children and peace.
target: Peace , children , peace .

input: The king loves you very much.
target: The king doth love you well .

input: You can not guess who caused your father's death.
target: Incapable and shallow innocents , You can not guess who caused your father's death .

input: Is it possible that you think my uncle did something?
target: Think you my uncle did dissemble , grandam ?

input: A boy and a girl.
target: Ay , boy .

input: I can't think of a reason for it.
target: I can not think it .

input: Hark, what noise is that?
target: Hark , what noise is this ?

input: I'll join with black despair against my soul, and to myself become an enemy.
target: I'll join with black despair against my soul And to myself become an enemy .

input: When the root is gone, why grow the branches?
target: Why grow the branches when the root is gone ?

input: Why not wither the leaves that want the water?
target: Why wither not the leaves that want their sap ?

input: If you will live, say farewell.
target: If you will live , lament .

input: If die, be brief, that our swift-winged souls may catch the king's and then follow him to his new kingdom.
target: If die , be brief , That our swift-winged souls may catch the king's , Or , like obedient subjects , follow him To his new kingdom of ne'er-changing night .

input: Thine being a moiety of my moan, to overgo the troubles and drown the cries of the people.
target: O , what cause have I , Thine being but a moiety of my moan , To overgo thy woes and drown thy cries !

input: All springs reduce their currents to mine eyes, that I am being governed by the watery moon, and may send forth plenteous tears to drown the world.
target: All springs reduce their currents to mine eyes , That I , being governed by the watery moon , May send forth plenteous tears to drown the world .

input: For my dear lord Edward, for my husband.
target: Ah , for my husband , for my dear lord Edward !

input: For our dear lord Clarence, for our father!
target: Ah , for our father , for our dear lord Clarence !

input: Alas for Edward and Clarence, both mine.
target: Alas for both , both mine , Edward and Clarence !

input: What stay did I have with Edward?
target: What stay had I but Edward ?

input: And he's left.
target: And he's gone .

input: What stay did we have but Clarence?
target: What stay had we but Clarence ?

input: And he's left.
target: And he's gone .

input: They are no longer with us.
target: And they are gone .
