target: Give mine the benefit of seigniory , And let my griefs frown on the upper hand .

input: I had a Richard as well, and I did't hesitate to kill him.
target: I had a Richard too , and thou did'st kill him ; I had a Rutland too ; thou holp'st to kill him .

input: O upright, just, and true-disposing God, how do I thank thee that this man Preys on the issue of his mother's body, and makes her pew-fellow with other people?
target: O upright , just , and true-disposing God , How do I thank thee that this carnal cur Preys on the issue of his mother's body And makes her pew-fellow with others ' moan !

input: O Harry's wife, triumph not in my problems.
target: O Harry's wife , triumph not in my woes !

input: I have cried for you, God witness with me.
target: God witness with me , I have wept for thine .

input: My Edward is dead, my other Edward is dead, and Young York is but boot because they Matched not the high perfection of my loss.
target: Thy Edward he is dead , that killed my Edward , Thy other Edward dead , to quit my Edward ; Young York , he is but boot , because both they Matched not the high perfection of my loss .

input: Clarence is dead, and the beholders of this frantic play are smothered in their dusky graves.
target: Thy Clarence he is dead that stabbed my Edward , And the beholders of this frantic play , Th ' adulterate Hastings , Rivers , Vaughan , Grey , Untimely smothered in their dusky graves .

input: Richard lives, hell's black intelligencer, Only reserved their factor to buy souls, and send them away.
target: Richard yet lives , hell's black intelligencer , Only reserved their factor to buy souls And send them thither .

input: Cancel his bond of life, dear God, I pray that I will live to say that the dog is dead.
target: Cancel his bond of life , dear God I pray , That I may live to say , "The dog is dead."

input: It was prophesied that the time would come that I should wish for the help of the toad.
target: O , thou didst prophesy the time would come That I should wish for thee to help me curse That bottled spider , that foul bunch-backed toad !

input: The presentation of but what I was, The flattering index of a direful pageant, One heaved a-high, to be thrown down below.
target: I called thee then "vain flourish of my fortune." I called thee then poor shadow , "painted queen , " The presentation of but what I was , The flattering index of a direful pageant , One heaved a-high , to be hurled down below , A mother only mocked with two fair babes , A dream of what thou wast , a garish flag To be the aim of every dangerous shot , A sign of dignity , a breath , a bubble , A queen in jest , only to fill the scene .

input: Where is the husband now?
target: Where is thy husband now ?

input: Where are your brothers?
target: Where be thy brothers ?

input: Where are the two sons of you?
target: Where are thy two sons ?

input: The course of justice whirled about and left thee, but a very prey to time, having no more but thought of what to do to thee.
target: Thus hath the course of justice whirled about And left thee but a very prey to time , Having no more but thought of what thou wast To torture thee the more , being what thou art .

input: Do you not think that Usurp the just proportion of my sadness is appropriate?
target: Thou didst usurp my place , and dost thou not Usurp the just proportion of my sorrow ?

input: I will be happy in France because of these English problems.
target: These English woes will make me smile in France .

input: I need to learn how to curse mine enemies. I need to stay awhile.
target: O , thou well-skilled in curses , stay awhile , And teach me how to curse mine enemies .

input: Forbear to sleep the nights, and fast the days, and think that the babes were sweeter than they were.
target: Forbear to sleep the nights , and fast the days ; Compare dead happiness with living woe ; Think that thy babes were sweeter than they were , And he that slew them fouler than he is .

input: Making the bad causer worse is the consequence of bettering the loss.
target: Bettering thy loss makes the bad causer worse .

input: Revolving this will teach the person how to curse.
target: Revolving this will teach thee how to curse .

input: My words aren't very interesting.
target: My words are dull .

input: O, speed them up with your strength.
target: O , quicken them with thine !

input: My troubles will make them sharp and pierce like them.
target: Thy woes will make them sharp and pierce like mine .

input: The calamity should not be filled with words.
target: Why should calamity be full of words ?

input: If that is the case, then you should not be tongue-tied.
target: If so , then be not tongue-tied .

input: Go with me, and let's smother my damned son that my two sweet sons smothered.
target: Go with me , And in the breath of bitter words let's smother My damned son that thy two sweet sons smothered .

input: Who is watching my expedition?
target: Who intercepts my expedition ?

input: She might have killed thee by strangulating her in her uterus.
target: O , she that might have intercepted thee , By strangling thee in her accursed womb , From all the slaughters , wretch , that thou hast done .

input: The slaughter of the prince that owed that crown and the dire death of my poor sons and brothers should be branded with a golden crown.
target: Hid'st thou that forehead with a golden crown Where should be branded , if that right were right , The slaughter of the prince that owed that crown And the dire death of my poor sons and brothers ?

input: Where are my children? I want to know.
target: Tell me , thou villain-slave , where are my children ?

input: Where is gentle Rivers, Vaughan, and Grey?
target: Where is gentle Rivers , Vaughan , Grey ?

input: What is the location of kind Hastings?
target: Where is kind Hastings ?

input: Strike the drums!
target: Strike alarum , drums !

input: Rail on the Lord's anointed should not be heard by the heavens.
target: Let not the heavens hear these telltale women Rail on the Lord's anointed .

input: I want you to strike.
target: Strike , I say !

input: I will drown your exclamations if you either be patient and entreat me fair or with the clamorous report of war.
target: Either be patient and entreat me fair , Or with the clamorous report of war Thus will I drown your exclamations .

input: My son, what art are you doing?
target: Art thou my son ?

input: I would like to thank God, my father, and yourself.
target: Ay , I thank God , my father , and yourself .

input: Wait until I hear my impatience.
target: Then patiently hear my impatience .

input: I have a touch of your condition, which can not help but make you sound reproof.
target: Madam , I have a touch of your condition , Which can not brook the accent of reproof .

input: Let me say something.
target: O , let me speak !

input: I'll not hear if you do then.
target: Do then , but I'll not hear .

input: In my words, I will be gentle and mild.
target: I will be mild and gentle in my words .

input: Good mother, for I am in haste.
target: And brief , good mother , for I am in haste .

input: Art was so hasty?
target: Art thou so hasty ?

input: God knows that I have stayed for thee, in torment and agony.
target: I have stayed for thee , God knows , in torment and in agony .

input: I wasn't at last able to comfort you.
target: And came I not at last to comfort you ?

input: It was a comfortable hour that graced me in the company of my friends.
target: What comfortable hour canst thou name , That ever graced me in thy company ?

input: Your Grace To breakfast was called by Humfrey Hower, Faith, and all of them.
target: Faith , none but Humfrey Hower , that called your Grace To breakfast once , forth of my company .

input: I want you to hear me speak.
target: I prithee , hear me speak .

input: You speak so bitterly.
target: You speak too bitterly .

input: I will never speak to thee again, hear me a word.
target: Hear me a word , For I shall never speak to thee again .

input: So that's right.
target: So .

input: More cause, but less spirit to curse my spirit.
target: Though far more cause , yet much less spirit to curse Abides in me .

input: I say a prayer to her.
target: I say amen to her .

input: Stay there, madam.
target: Stay , madam .

input: I need to speak with you.
target: I must talk a word with you .

input: I don't have any more sons of the royal blood to slaughter.
target: I have no more sons of the royal blood For thee to slaughter .

input: You have a daughter named Elizabeth, she's fair and she's royal.
target: You have a daughter called Elizabeth , Virtuous and fair , royal and gracious .

input: Is she going to die for this.
target: And must she die for this ?

input: O, let her live, and I'll ruin her manners, stain her beauty, and make her look bad. Throw over her the veil of infamy.
target: O , let her live , And I'll corrupt her manners , stain her beauty , Slander myself as false to Edward's bed , Throw over her the veil of infamy .

input: I will confess that she was not Edward's daughter and that she may live unscarred of bleeding slaughter.
target: So she may live unscarred of bleeding slaughter , I will confess she was not Edward's daughter .

input: She was wrong not her birth.
target: Wrong not her birth .

input: She is a member of the royal family.
target: She is a royal princess .

input: I will say that she is not so to save her life.
target: To save her life , I'll say she is not so .

input: Her brothers died because of that safety.
target: And only in that safety died her brothers .

input: No, to their lives ill friends were not true.
target: No , to their lives ill friends were contrary .

input: If grace had blessed thee with a fair life, my babes would have died in a fair death.
target: My babes were destined to a fairer death If grace had blessed thee with a fairer life .

input: The hand that launched their hearts was given direction by the head that indirectly gave it.
target: Whose hand soever launched their tender hearts , Thy head , all indirectly , gave direction .

input: The murd'rous knife was dull and blunt, but it was whetted on my stone-hard heart, to revel in the entrails of my lambs.
target: No doubt the murd'rous knife was dull and blunt Till it was whetted on thy stone-hard heart , To revel in the entrails of my lambs .

input: But that still use of grief makes wild grief tame, my tongue should not name my boys, I was in a bay of death, like a poor bark of sails, and tackling reft.
target: But that still use of grief makes wild grief tame , My tongue should to thy ears not name my boys Till that my nails were anchored in thine eyes , And I , in such a desp'rate bay of death , Like a poor bark of sails and tackling reft , Rush all to pieces on thy rocky bosom .

input: So thrive I in my enterprise, and dangerous success of bloody wars, as I intend more good to you and yours, than ever you or yours were harmed by me.
target: Madam , so thrive I in my enterprise And dangerous success of bloody wars As I intend more good to you and yours Than ever you or yours were by me harmed !

input: To be discovered, that can do me good, what good is covered with the face of heaven.
target: What good is covered with the face of heaven , To be discovered , that can do me good ?

input: The advancement of your children is being done by a gentle lady.
target: The advancement of your children , gentle lady .

input: Up to a scaffold, there is a chance of them losing their heads.
target: Up to some scaffold , there to lose their heads .

input: The high imperial type of this earth's glory is not to the dignity and height of fortune.
target: Unto the dignity and height of fortune , The high imperial type of this earth's glory .

input: For any place but hell, you are not fit for it.
target: And thou unfit for any place but hell .

input: If you will hear me name it, that's one place else.
target: Yes , one place else , if you will hear me name it .

input: There is a dungeon.
target: Some dungeon .

input: The bedchamber is yours.
target: Your bedchamber .

input: I'm going to rest in the chamber where you lie.
target: Ill rest betide the chamber where thou liest !

input: So will it be, madam, until I tell you the truth.
target: So will it , madam till I lie with you .

input: Be brief, because the process of kindness lasts longer than the date.
target: Be brief , lest that the process of thy kindness Last longer telling than thy kindness ' date .

input: I love my daughter from my heart.
target: Then know that from my soul I love thy daughter .

input: My daughter's mother thinks it through her soul.
target: My daughter's mother thinks it with her soul .

input: What do you think about this?
target: What do you think ?

input: My daughter is loved from the soul of my father.
target: That thou dost love my daughter from thy soul .

input: Don't be so hasty to misunderstand my meaning.
target: Be not so hasty to confound my meaning .

input: She makes her queen even though he is.
target: Even he that makes her queen .

input: Who else should be in this situation?
target: Who else should be ?

input: What are you talking about, Thou?
target: What , thou ?

input: What do you think about it?
target: How think you of it ?

input: How can you get her to marry you?
target: How canst thou woo her ?

input: With all my heart, Madame.
target: Madam , with all my heart .

input: You make me feel bad, madam.
target: You mock me , madam .

input: The way to win your daughter is not this way.
target: This is not the way To win your daughter .

input: Unless you could put on some other shape, and not be Richard, then there is no other way.
target: There is no other way , Unless thou couldst put on some other shape And not be Richard , that hath done all this .

input: Say that I did this for her.
target: Say that I did all this for love of her .

input: She can't choose but hates thee because she bought love with such a bloody spoil.
target: Nay , then indeed she can not choose but hate thee , Having bought love with such a bloody spoil .

input: What is done can not be changed now.
target: Look what is done can not be now amended .

input: Men will sometimes deal unadvisedly, which after-hours give leisure to repent.
target: Men shall deal unadvisedly sometimes , Which after-hours give leisure to repent .

input: If I took the kingdom from your sons, I will give it to your daughter.
target: If I did take the kingdom from your sons , To make amends I'll give it to your daughter .

input: If I have killed the issue of your uterus, I will get the issue of your blood upon your daughter.
target: If I have killed the issue of your womb , To quicken your increase I will beget Mine issue of your blood upon your daughter .

input: A mother's title is doting, but her grandam's name is less in love.
target: A grandam's name is little less in love Than is the doting title of a mother .

input: My age will be a comfort to you, because your children were vexation to your youth.
target: Your children were vexation to your youth , But mine shall be a comfort to your age .

input: Accept such kindness as I can because I can't make you what I'd want.
target: I can not make you what amends I would ; Therefore accept such kindness as I can .

input: We have many good days to look at.
target: What , we have many goodly days to see !

input: Go then, my mother, and to my daughter.
target: Go then , my mother ; to thy daughter go .

input: What was the best thing I could say?
target: What were I best to say ?

input: Her father's brother would be her leader.
target: Her father's brother Would be her lord ?

input: Is it possible to say her uncle.
target: Or shall I say her uncle ?

input: Or he slew her brothers and her family?
target: Or he that slew her brothers and her uncles ?

input: Can make seem pleasing to her tender years, under what title shall I woo for thee, that God, the law, my honor, and her love?
target: Under what title shall I woo for thee , That God , the law , my honor and her love Can make seem pleasing to her tender years ?

input: England's peace has been fair by this alliance.
target: Infer fair England's peace by this alliance .

input: Which she will purchase with the war.
target: Which she shall purchase with still-lasting war .

input: The king's King forbids her from telling him that, but she should tell him that.
target: Tell her the king , that may command , entreats , That , at her hands , which the king's King forbids .

input: She will be a high and powerful queen.
target: Say she shall be a high and mighty queen .

input: As her mother doth, to vail the title.
target: To vail the title , as her mother doth .

input: I will love her for the rest of my life.
target: Say I will love her everlastingly .

input: But how long will that title last?
target: But how long shall that title "ever" last ?

input: She was in force at her fair life's end.
target: Sweetly in force unto her fair life's end .

input: How long shall her sweet life last?
target: But how long fairly shall her sweet life last ?

input: As long as heaven and nature continue to grow, so be it.
target: As long as heaven and nature lengthens it .

input: As long as Richard likes it, that's all.
target: As long as hell and Richard likes of it .

input: Is her subject low? Say I, her leader.
target: Say I , her sovereign , am her subject low .

input: She dislikes such sovereignty.
target: But she , your subject , loathes such sovereignty .

input: I want you to be eloquent in my defense.
target: Be eloquent in my behalf to her .

input: Being told an honest tale is the best way to speed it up.
target: An honest tale speeds best being plainly told .

input: Then tell my story to her.
target: Then plainly to her tell my loving tale .

input: It is too harsh a style to be plain and not honest.
target: Plain and not honest is too harsh a style .

input: Your reasons are too quick and shallow.
target: Your reasons are too shallow and too quick .

input: My reasons are too deep and dead, and poor infants are in their graves.
target: O no , my reasons are too deep and dead , Too deep and dead , poor infants , in their graves .

input: That is past, madam, and the harp is not on that string.
target: Harp not on that string , madam ; that is past .

input: I will keep harp on it until heart- strings break.
target: Harp on it still shall I till heart-strings break .

input: By my Garter and my crown, Profaned, and the third usurped, by my George, my Garter, and my crown.
target: Now by my George , my Garter , and my crown , Profaned , dishonored , and the third usurped .

input: I don't swear by anything, for this is not an oath.
target: I swear , By nothing , for this is no oath .

input: Then, by myself, he is self-misused.
target: Then , by myself , Thyself is self-misused .

input: Now, by the world, 'T is full of foul wrongs.
target: Now , by the world , 'T is full of thy foul wrongs .

input: My life has been ruined by my father's death.
target: My father's death , Thy life hath it dishonored .

input: My child had graced the tender temples of my child, and both the princes had been breathing here, which now was two tender bedfellows for dust.
target: If thou hadst feared to break an oath by Him , Th ' imperial metal circling now thy head Had graced the tender temples of my child , And both the princes had been breathing here , Which now , two tender bedfellows for dust , Thy broken faith hath made the prey for worms .

input: What do you think can be said by now?
target: What canst thou swear by now ?

input: The time has come.
target: The time to come .

input: The children live with their fathers who have slaughtered the youth and the parents who have butchered the old plants.
target: The children live whose fathers thou hast slaughtered , Ungoverned youth , to wail it in their age ; The parents live whose children thou hast butchered , Old barren plants , to wail it with their age .

input: By times ill-used o'erpast, wear not by time to come, for that you hast Misused ere used.
target: Swear not by time to come , for that thou hast Misused ere used , by times ill-used o'erpast .

target: God pardon them that are the cause thereof .

target: And for my name of George begins with It follows in his thought that I am he .

target: My Lady Grey his wife , Clarence , 'tis she That tempers him to this extremity .

target: Madam , his majesty doth call for you , , And for your Grace , , and yours , my gracious lords .

target: We wait upon your Grace .

input: But, soft!
target: But , soft !

input: Are you going to dispatch this thing now?
target: Are you now going to dispatch this thing ?

target: Why looks your grace so heavily today ?

target: What was your dream , my lord ?

target: I pray you tell me .

target: Methoughts that I had broken from the Tower And was embarked to cross to Burgundy , And in my company my brother Gloucester , Who from my cabin tempted me to walk Upon the hatches .

input: During the wars of York and Lancaster, we had been cited up a thousand times.
target: Thence we looked toward England And cited up a thousand fearful times , During the wars of York and Lancaster That had befall'n us .

input: What pain it was to drown, what terrible noise of water in my ears, what sights of death within my eyes, I thought.
target: O Lord , methought what pain it was to drown , What dreadful noise of waters in my ears , What sights of ugly death within my eyes .

input: I saw a lot of fearful wracks, a lot of men that were eaten by fishes, lots of gold, gems, and pearls, and all scattered in the jewels of the sea.
target: Methoughts I saw a thousand fearful wracks , A thousand men that fishes gnawed upon , Wedges of gold , great anchors , heaps of pearl , Inestimable stones , unvalued jewels , All scattered in the bottom of the sea .

input: Did you enjoy the time of death to look at the secrets of the deep?
target: Had you such leisure in the time of death To gaze upon the secrets of the deep ?

input: I tried to yield the ghost, but the flood of envy in my soul kept me from finding the empty, vast, and wand'ring air that I was looking for.
target: Methought I had , and often did I strive To yield the ghost , but still the envious flood Stopped in my soul and would not let it forth To find the empty , vast , and wand'ring air , But smothered it within my panting bulk , Who almost burst to belch it in the sea .

input: I passed by the melancholy flood, with that sour ferryman which poets write about.
target: I passed , methought , the melancholy flood , With that sour ferryman which poets write of , Unto the kingdom of perpetual night .

input: The first person to greet my stranger-soul was my great father-in-law, renowned Warwick.
target: The first that there did greet my stranger-soul Was my great father-in-law , renowned Warwick , Who spake aloud , "What scourge for perjury Can this dark monarchy afford false Clarence ? " And so he vanished .

input: Though it affrighted you, there was no marvel.
target: No marvel , lord , though it affrighted you .

input: I am afraid that you will tell it.
target: I am afraid , methinks , to hear you tell it .

input: I have done things that will give evidence against my soul, for Edward's sake, if my prayers don't work out.
target: Ah keeper , keeper , I have done those things , That now give evidence against my soul , For Edward's sake , and see how he requites me. , O God , if my deep prayers can not appease thee , But thou wilt be avenged on my misdeeds , Yet execute thy wrath in me alone !

input: I would like to spare my guiltless wife and my poor children.
target: O , spare my guiltless wife and my poor children ! , Keeper , I prithee sit by me awhile .

input: My soul is heavy, and I would sleep if I could.
target: My soul is heavy , and I fain would sleep .

input: My lord, I will, I will.
target: I will , my lord .

input: Good rest, God, give your Grace.
target: God give your Grace good rest .

input: Sorrow breaks seasons and reposing hours, it makes the night morning and the noontide night.
target: Sorrow breaks seasons and reposing hours , Makes the night morning , and the noontide night .

input: Princes have titles for their glories, which is an outward honor for an inward toil.
target: Princes have but their titles for their glories , An outward honor for an inward toil ,

input: What would it be like to be a fellow?
target: What wouldst thou , fellow ?

input: How cam'st he hither?
target: And how cam'st thou hither ?

input: Clarence came hither on my legs after I spoke with him.
target: I would speak with Clarence , and I came hither on my legs .

input: What is it that is so short?
target: What , so brief ?

input: Let him see our commission, and talk no more, sir.
target: Tis better , sir , to be brief than tedious. , Let him see our commission , and talk no more .

input: The noble duke of Clarence is to be delivered to you.
target: I am in this commanded to deliver The noble duke of Clarence to your hands .

input: The duke is asleep and the keys are in there.
target: There lies the duke asleep , and there the keys .

input: You might, sir.
target: You may , sir .

input: A point of wisdom is what it is.
target: Tis a point of wisdom .

input: Well done, Fare you well.
target: Fare you well .

input: Shall I stab him while he sleeps?
target: What , shall I stab him as he sleeps ?

input: No, that's not true.
target: No .

input: When he wakes, he'll say 'twas done cowardice'.
target: He'll say 'twas done cowardly , when he wakes .

input: He will never wake up until Judgement Day.
target: Why , he shall never wake until the great Judgment Day .

input: He will say that we stabbed him sleeping.
target: Why , then he'll say we stabbed him sleeping .

input: It was the word "judgment" that caused me to feel remorse.
target: The urging of that word "judgment" hath bred a kind of remorse in me .

input: What are you afraid of, art?
target: What , art thou afraid ?

input: Not to kill him, having a warrant, but to be damned for killing him, from the point of view of no warrant can defend me.
target: Not to kill him , having a warrant , but to be damned for killing him , from the which no warrant can defend me .

input: I thought that he had been steadfast.
target: I thought thou hadst been resolute .

input: I am going to let him live.
target: So I am , to let him live .

input: I'll tell the duke of Gloucester about it.
target: I'll back to the duke of Gloucester and tell him so .

input: I prithee stay a little.
target: Nay , I prithee stay a little .

input: I hope this passionate humor of mine will change.
target: I hope this passionate humor of mine will change .

input: It wasn't going to hold me but at least one told twenty.
target: It was wont to hold me but while one tells twenty .

input: How do you feel right now?
target: How dost thou feel thyself now ?

input: Some dregs of conscience are still within me.
target: Faith , some certain dregs of conscience are yet within me .

input: When the deed is done, remember our reward.
target: Remember our reward when the deed's done .

input: Zounds, he dies.
target: Zounds , he dies !

input: I didn't remember the reward.
target: I had forgot the reward .

input: Where are your conscience now?
target: Where's thy conscience now ?

input: The duke of Gloucester had a purse.
target: O , in the duke of Gloucester's purse .

input: When he opens his purse to give us our reward, his conscience flies out.
target: So when he opens his purse to give us our reward , thy conscience flies out .

input: No matter, Tis no matter.
target: Tis no matter .

input: It's time to let it go.
target: Let it go .

input: There's not many that will entertain it.
target: There's few or none will entertain it .

input: Is it possible that it will come to thee again.
target: What if it come to thee again ?

input: I don't want to meddle with it.
target: I'll not meddle with it .

input: It's a shamefaced spirit that takes advantage of a man's bosom.
target: Tis a blushing , shamefaced spirit that mutinies in a man's bosom .

input: My frame is strong.
target: I am strong-framed .

input: He couldn't prevail with me.
target: He can not prevail with me .

input: It was like a tall man that respected his reputation.
target: Spoke like a tall man that respects thy reputation .

input: Shall we fall to work?
target: Come , shall we fall to work ?

input: Take him on the costard with the hilts of the sword and throw him into the malmsey butt in the next room.
target: Take him on the costard with the hilts of thy sword , and then throw him into the malmsey butt in the next room .

input: Make a sop of him, and use an excellent device.
target: O excellent device , and make a sop of him .

input: It's time to strike.
target: Strike !

input: No, we'll explain to him.
target: No , we'll reason with him .

input: Where art is, keeper?
target: Where art thou , keeper ?

input: Give me a glass of wine.
target: Give me a cup of wine .

input: My lord, you will have enough wine, anon.
target: You shall have wine enough , my lord , anon .

input: In God's name, what art is it?
target: In God's name , what art thou ?

input: As you are, a man as well.
target: A man , as you are .

input: But not as I am, a royal.
target: But not , as I am , royal .

input: We are loyal to you, as well.
target: Nor you , as we are , loyal .

input: The voice is thunder, but the looks are modest.
target: Thy voice is thunder , but thy looks are humble .

input: My voice is now the king's, and I look like it.
target: My voice is now the king's , my looks mine own .

input: Your eyes are dangerous to me.
target: Your eyes do menace me .

input: Why do you look pale?
target: Why look you pale ?

input: Who sent you to kill her?
target: Who sent you hither ?

input: Where are you heading?
target: Wherefore do you come ?

input: To murder me, what?
target: To , to , to , To murder me ?

input: Ay, Ay.
target: Ay , ay .

input: You can't have the hearts to tell me that, because you don't have any.
target: You scarcely have the hearts to tell me so , And therefore can not have the hearts to do it .

input: Wherein, my friends, have I offended you?
target: Wherein , my friends , have I offended you ?

input: Offended us you have not, but the king.
target: Offended us you have not , but the king .

input: I will be able to reconcile with him again.
target: I shall be reconciled to him again .

input: My lord, never, my lord.
target: Never , my lord .

input: Prepare to die, therefore.
target: Therefore prepare to die .

input: Are you drawn into a world of men to kill the innocent?
target: Are you drawn forth among a world of men To slay the innocent ?

input: What is it that I do?
target: What is my offense ?

input: Where is the evidence that supports the accusations against me?
target: Where is the evidence that doth accuse me ?

input: What was the lawful quest that led to the frowning judge's verdict?
target: What lawful quest have given their verdict up Unto the frowning judge ?

input: Clarence's death Before I be convicted by course of law was pronounced by someone.
target: Or who pronounced The bitter sentence of poor Clarence ' death Before I be convict by course of law ?

input: To threaten me with death is not permissible.
target: To threaten me with death is most unlawful .

input: I charge you, as you hope to have redemption, by Christ's blood shed for our grievous sins, that you leave and leave me alone, and that you lay no hands on me.
target: I charge you , as you hope to have redemption , By Christ's dear blood shed for our grievous sins , That you depart , and lay no hands on me .

input: We do upon command, what we will do.
target: What we will do , we do upon command .

input: Even so is true.
target: Even so .

input: Brakenbury, you may partake of whatever we say.
target: An please your Worship , Brakenbury , You may partake of anything we say .

input: We don't speak no treason, man.
target: We speak no treason , man .

input: We think the king is wise and good, and his queen is fair and not jealous.
target: We say the king Is wise and virtuous , and his noble queen Well struck in years , fair , and not jealous .

input: How do you say something?
target: How say you , sir ?

input: Is it possible to deny all this?
target: Can you deny all this ?

input: My lord, with this, I have nothing to do.
target: With this , my lord , myself have naught to do .

input: She has a husband, knave.
target: Her husband , knave .

input: Is it possible that he would betray me?
target: Wouldst thou betray me ?

input: I request that you grant me a pardon and allow me to attend your conference with the noble duke.
target: I do beseech your Grace to pardon me , and withal Forbear your conference with the noble duke .

input: Our king is that man that was commanded.
target: And he that hath commanded is our king .

input: He hurls vengeance for false forswearing and for murder too.
target: And that same vengeance doth He hurl on thee For false forswearing and for murder too .

input: Whom we swore to defend and preserve.
target: Whom thou wert sworn to cherish and defend .

input: How can he urge us to obey God's law when he has broken it in such a way?
target: How canst thou urge God's dreadful law to us When thou hast broke it in such dear degree ?

input: Whose sake did I do that horrible thing?
target: For whose sake did I that ill deed ?

input: For Edward, for my brother, for his sake.
target: For Edward , for my brother , for his sake .

input: If God will be avenged for this deed, then you should know that he will do it publicly.
target: If God will be avenged for this deed , O , know you yet He doth it publicly !

input: He doesn't need an indirect or lawless course to cut off those that have offended Him.
target: Take not the quarrel from His powerful arm ; He needs no indirect or lawless course To cut off those that have offended Him .

input: My brother's love, the devil, and my rage are what I remember.
target: My brother's love , the devil , and my rage .

input: I love my brother and I am his brother as well.
target: I am his brother , and I love him well .

input: You are not aware of it.
target: You are deceived .

input: Your brother Gloucester dislikes you.
target: Your brother Gloucester hates you .

input: He loves me, and he holds me dear.
target: O , no , he loves me , and he holds me dear .

input: Go to him from me, you know what I mean.
target: Go you to him from me .

input: So we will do that.
target: Ay , so we will .

input: When our princely father York Blessed his three sons with his victorious arm, He didn't think about the divided friendship.
target: Tell him , when that our princely father York Blessed his three sons with his victorious arm , He little thought of this divided friendship .

input: Bid Gloucester will weep when he thinks of this.
target: Bid Gloucester think of this , and he will weep .

input: As he showed us to weep, Ay, millstones.
target: Ay , millstones , as he lessoned us to weep .

input: Right, as snow falls in the harvest.
target: Right , as snow in harvest .

input: You lie to yourself, come.
target: Come , you deceive yourself .

input: He sends us to destroy you here.
target: Tis he that sends us to destroy you here .

input: When he delivers you from this earth's thralldom to the joys of heaven, why?
target: Why , so he doth , when he delivers you From this earth's thralldom to the joys of heaven .

input: For you must die, my lord, and make peace with God.
target: Make peace with God , for you must die , my lord .

input: Are you so blind that you will war with God if you counsel me to make my peace with him?
target: Have you that holy feeling in your souls To counsel me to make my peace with God , And art you yet to your own souls so blind That thou will war with God by murd'ring me ?

input: They will hate you for the deed if they set you on doing it.
target: O sirs , consider : they that set you on To do this deed will hate you for the deed .

input: Don't give up, and save your souls.
target: Relent , and save your souls .

input: If you were a prince's son, and two murderers came to you, would you not want to live?
target: Which of you , if you were a prince's son Being pent from liberty , as I am now , If two such murderers as yourselves came to you , Would not entreat for life ?

input: If you were in my distress, you would beg.
target: Ay , you would beg , Were you in my distress .

input: Is it possible to be relentless?
target: Relent ?

input: No, that's not true.
target: No .

input: Is it cowardice and womanish?
target: Tis cowardly and womanish .

input: Look behind you, my lord,
target: Look behind you , my lord .

input: Take that and everything else.
target: Take that , and that .

input: How are you now?
target: How now ?

input: What does that mean, that I don't need help?
target: What mean'st thou , that thou help'st me not ?

input: The duke will know how much slack you have been by the stars.
target: By heavens , the duke shall know how slack you have been .

input: I would let him know that I had saved his brother.
target: I would he knew that I had saved his brother .

input: I do not do that.
target: So do not I .

input: Go and be the epitome of cowardice as you are.
target: Go , coward as thou art .

input: I will hide the body in a hole until the duke gives the order for his burial.
target: Well , I'll go hide the body in some hole Till that the duke give order for his burial .

input: When I have my meed, I will leave, and then I have to leave.
target: And when I have my meed , I will away , For this will out , and then I must not stay .

input: Here comes your father.
target: Here comes your father .

input: Never make a denial.
target: Never make denial .

input: I have to have my wife with him.
target: I must and will have Katherine to my wife .

input: How fast do you travel with my daughter?
target: Now , Signior Petruchio , how speed you with my daughter ?

input: How are you doing, sir?
target: How but well , sir ?

input: How do you know why, daughter Katherine?
target: Why , how now , daughter Katherine ?

input: Do you have your dumps in?
target: In your dumps ?

input: Is it possible to call you daughter?
target: Call you me daughter ?

input: Father, 'tis thus, you and all the world, that talked of her, have talked amiss of her.
target: Father , 'tis thus : yourself and all the world That talked of her have talked amiss of her .

input: Thee will be hanged on Sunday first.
target: I'll see thee hanged on Sunday first .

input: She says that she will see thee hanged first.
target: Hark , Petruchio : she says she'll see thee hanged first .

input: Is this the speed you are travelling?
target: Is this your speeding ?

input: Good night our part, then.
target: Nay , then , good night our part .

input: Gentlemen, be patient, be patient.
target: Be patient , gentlemen .

input: She is my choice for myself.
target: I choose her for myself .

input: What do you think about if she and I are pleased?
target: If she and I be pleased , what's that to you ?

input: She would still be in company if we bargained 'twixt us twain, being alone.
target: Tis bargained 'twixt us twain , being alone , That she shall still be curst in company .

input: I tell you how much she loves me, it's incredible.
target: I tell you , 'tis incredible to believe How much she loves me .

input: Kate, you are the loveliest person!
target: O , the kindest Kate !

input: You are new to the game.
target: O , you are novices !

input: When men and women are alone, a meacock wretch can make a woman throw a shrew.
target: Tis a world to see , How tame , when men and women are alone , A meacock wretch can make the curstest shrew. , Give me thy hand , Kate .

input: I will go to Venice to purchase apparel for the wedding day.
target: I will unto Venice To buy apparel 'gainst the wedding day .

input: Thank you, God, for sending you joy, Petruchio.
target: God send you joy , Petruchio .

input: A match is being played.
target: Tis a match .

input: Amen, say us.
target: Amen , say we .

input: We will be witnesses.
target: We will be witnesses .

input: Father, and wife, and gentlemen, adieu.
target: Father , and wife , and gentlemen , adieu .

input: I will travel to Venice.
target: I will to Venice .

input: The Sunday comes a bit later.
target: Sunday comes apace .

input: We are going to be married on Sunday.
target: We will be married o ' Sunday .

input: Was it ever a match that clapped up suddenly?
target: Was ever match clapped up so suddenly ?

input: You will either gain or lose on the seas.
target: Twill bring you gain or perish on the seas .

input: The gain that I seek is not heard in the match.
target: The gain I seek is quiet in the match .

input: He got a quiet catch, no doubt about it.
target: No doubt but he hath got a quiet catch .

input: Now, Baptista, to your younger daughter.
target: But now , Baptista , to your younger daughter .

input: We have been looking for that day for a long time.
target: Now is the day we long have looked for .

input: I am your neighbor, and was the first one to propose.
target: I am your neighbor , and was suitor first .

input: Youngling, you cannot love as much as I. Graybeard.
target: Youngling , thou canst not love so dear as I. Graybeard , thy love doth freeze .

input: But doth cook.
target: But thine doth fry .

input: Stand back, Skipper.
target: Skipper , stand back .

input: It is age that replenisheth.
target: Tis age that nourisheth .

input: Gentlemen, you have content.
target: Content you , gentlemen .

input: I will make this a bigger problem.
target: I will compound this strife .

input: My house within the city is richly furnished with plate and gold, Basins and ewers to lave her dainty hands, and my hangings all of Tyrian tapestry are in ivory coffers.
target: First , as you know , my house within the city Is richly furnished with plate and gold , Basins and ewers to lave her dainty hands ; My hangings all of Tyrian tapestry , In ivory coffers I have stuffed my crowns , In cypress chests my arras counterpoints , Costly apparel , tents , and canopies , Fine linen , Turkey cushions bossed with pearl , Valance of Venice gold in needlework , Pewter and brass , and all things that belong To house or housekeeping .

input: At my farm, I have a hundred milch-kine to the pail, six score fat oxen standing in my stalls, and all of this is answerable to this portion.
target: Then , at my farm I have a hundred milch-kine to the pail , Six score fat oxen standing in my stalls , And all things answerable to this portion .

input: By the year of land, there will be two thousand ducats!
target: Two thousand ducats by the year of land !

input: I have offered all, I have no more, and she can have no more than I have.
target: Nay , I have offered all , I have no more , And she can have no more than all I have .

input: I have to confess that your offer is the best, and that she is your own, but you must pardon me.
target: I must confess your offer is the best , And , let your father make her the assurance , She is your own ; else , you must pardon me .

input: If you should die before him, where is the dower?
target: If you should die before him , where's her dower ?

input: Is it possible that young men will die as well as old ones?
target: And may not young men die as well as old ?

input: My daughter Katherina is going to be married on Sunday next.
target: Well , gentlemen , I am thus resolved : On Sunday next , you know My daughter Katherina is to be married .

input: I think that your honor means something to you.
target: I think 'twas Soto that your Honor means .

input: It is very true.
target: Tis very true .

input: It was excellent, Thou didst it very well.
target: Thou didst it excellent .

input: There is a lord who will hear you play tonight, but I am doubtful of your modesties, for yet his honor never heard a play, you break into some merry passion, and so offend him.
target: There is a lord will hear you play tonight ; But I am doubtful of your modesties , Lest over-eyeing of his odd behavior , For yet his Honor never heard a play , You break into some merry passion And so offend him .

input: Sirrah, take them to the butter and give them a friendly welcome.
target: Go , sirrah , take them to the buttery And give them friendly welcome every one .

input: Good neighbor. Adieu.
target: Adieu , good neighbor .

input: Sirrah young gamester, your father was a fool, to give thee all and in his waning age, set foot under the table.
target: Sirrah young gamester , your father were a fool To give thee all and in his waning age Set foot under thy table .

input: The toy is called Tut.
target: Tut , a toy !

input: My boy says that an old Italian fox is not kind.
target: An old Italian fox is not so kind , my boy .

input: Your withered hide is going to get a vengeance.
target: A vengeance on your crafty withered hide !

input: Most fathers do get their children.
target: Fathers commonly Do get their children .

input: A child will get a sire if I fail not to woo them.
target: But in this case of wooing , A child shall get a sire , if I fail not of my cunning .

input: His lecture will be over by then.
target: His lecture will be done ere you have tuned .

input: Where did we leave?
target: Where left we last ?

input: Here, madam, you should conster them.
target: Here , madam : Conster them .

input: If I can conster it, let me know.
target: Now let me see if I can conster it .

input: I have to believe my master, otherwise I should be arguing with that doubt.
target: I must believe my master ; else , I promise you , I should be arguing still upon that doubt .

input: Let it rest, now, Litio, to you.
target: But let it rest. , Now , Litio , to you .

input: Good master, take it with a grain of salt, pray that I have been a pleasure to be around you both.
target: Good master , take it not unkindly , pray , That I have been thus pleasant with you both .

input: Do you mean this "gamut?"
target: Call you this "gamut" ?

input: I don't like it, Tut.
target: Tut , I like it not .

input: I like old fashions the best.
target: Old fashions please me best .

input: Your father is praying that you leave your books and help to dress your sister's chamber.
target: Mistress , your father prays you leave your books And help to dress your sister's chamber up .

input: Tomorrow is the wedding day.
target: You know tomorrow is the wedding day .

input: It was a farewell for sweet masters both.
target: Farewell , sweet masters both .

input: I have to be gone.
target: I must be gone .

input: This pedant has cause for me to pry into it.
target: But I have cause to pry into this pedant .

input: He looks like he was in love, I think.
target: Methinks he looks as though he were in love .

input: No shame, but mine too.
target: No shame but mine .

input: "If it would please him to come and marry her, I'll let the world point at my poor wife," said the man.
target: Now must the world point at poor Katherine And say , "Lo , there is mad Petruchio's wife , If it would please him come and marry her ! " Upon my life , Petruchio means but well , Whatever fortune stays him from his word : Though he be blunt , I know him passing wise ; Though he be merry , yet withal he's honest .

input: Would Katherine have ever seen him?
target: Would Katherine had never seen him , though !

input: Go, girl.
target: Go , girl .

input: I don't think it's a bad idea for thee to weep for such an injury, it would be a very saint.
target: I can not blame thee now to weep , For such an injury would vex a very saint , Much more a shrew of thy impatient humor .

input: Master, master!
target: Master , master !

input: You have never heard of news, old news, and such news.
target: News , old news , and such news as you never heard of !

input: Is it old and new at the same time?
target: Is it new and old too ?

input: How may that happen?
target: How may that be ?

input: It's not news to hear of the coming of Petruchio.
target: Why , is it not news to hear of Petruchio's coming ?

input: Is he going to be here?
target: Is he come ?

input: Why, no, sir.
target: Why , no , sir .

input: What do you think about that?
target: What then ?

input: He is going to come.
target: He is coming .

input: How soon will he be here?
target: When will he be here ?

input: He will see you when he stands where he is.
target: When he stands where I am and sees you there .

input: Who brings him with them?
target: Who comes with him ?

input: A monster, a very monster in apparel, and not like a Christian footboy or a gentleman's lackey.
target: A monster , a very monster in apparel , and not like a Christian footboy or a gentleman's lackey .

input: I'm glad he's here, howsoe'er he arrives.
target: I am glad he's come , howsoe'er he comes .

input: Why, sir, he doesn't show up.
target: Why , sir , he comes not .

input: Did he not say he was coming?
target: Didst thou not say he comes ?

input: Who is this person?
target: Who ?

input: That was the person that came?
target: That Petruchio came ?

input: That's right, that's right, that's right, that's right, that's right, that's right, that's right, that's right, that's right, that's right, that's right, that's
target: Ay , that Petruchio came .

input: No, sir, I say his horse comes with him on his back.

input: The beef and the mustard should be left to rest.
target: Why then , the beef , and let the mustard rest .

target: Nay then , I will not .

input: If you don't have the mustard, you won't get any beef of Grumio.
target: You shall have the mustard Or else you get no beef of Grumio .

target: Then both , or one , or anything thou wilt .

input: The beef is not included in the mustard without it.
target: Why then , the mustard without the beef .

target: Go , get thee gone , I say .

input: What cheer do you have?
target: Mistress , what cheer ?

input: Pluck up your friends.
target: Pluck up thy spirits .

input: I dress my meat myself and bring it to you, I am very careful.
target: Here love , thou seest how diligent I am , To dress thy meat myself and bring it thee .

target: I am sure , sweet Kate , this kindness merits thanks .

target: What , not a word ?

target: Nay , then thou lov'st it not And all my pains is sorted to no proof .

target: Why , this was molded on a porringer !

target: A velvet dish !

target: Fie , fie , 'tis lewd and filthy !

target: Why , 'tis a cockle or a walnut shell , A knack , a toy , a trick , a baby's cap .

target: Away with it !

target: I'll have no bigger .

target: When you are gentle , you shall have one too , And not till then .

target: Why , sir , I trust I may have leave to speak , And speak I will .

target: I am no child , no babe .

target: Your betters have endured me say my mind , And if you can not , best you stop your ears .

target: Why , thou say'st true .

target: It is a paltry cap , A custard-coffin , a bauble , a silken pie .

target: I love thee well in that thou lik'st it not .

target: Thy gown ?

input: Why, ay?
target: Why , ay .

input: Let us see 't, come, tailor.
target: Come , tailor , let us see 't .

input: God, O mercy, please!
target: O mercy , God !

input: What's this thing?
target: What's this ?

target: A sleeve ?

input: It is like acannon.
target: Tis like a demi-cannon .

input: What is it that was carved like an apple tart?
target: What , up and down , carved like an apple tart ?

target: Here's snip and nip and cut and slish and slash , Like to a censer in a barber's shop .

input: Why do I call this devil's name, tailor?
target: Why , what i ' devil's name , tailor , call'st thou this ?

input: According to the fashion and the time, you bid me make it orderly and well.
target: You bid me make it orderly and well , According to the fashion and the time .

input: They married and did.
target: Marry , and did .

input: If you are remembered, I didn't want you to mar it to the time.
target: But if you be remembered , I did not bid you mar it to the time .

input: I'll not be involved in it.
target: I'll none of it .

input: Make your best of it, that's all.
target: Hence , make your best of it .

input: I have never seen a better-fashioned gown, More quaint, more pleasing, or more commendable.
target: I never saw a better-fashioned gown , More quaint , more pleasing , nor more commendable .

input: Why would he want to make a puppet of thee?
target: Why , true , he means to make a puppet of thee .

input: Thou liest, Thou thread, Thou thimble, Thou yard, three-quarters, half-yard, quarter, nail, and so on.
target: Thou liest , thou thread , thou thimble , Thou yard , three-quarters , half-yard , quarter , nail !

input: The flea, nit, and winter cricket are related.
target: Thou flea , thou nit , thou winter cricket thou !

input: I was braved in my own house with a skein of thread.
target: Braved in mine own house with a skein of thread ?

input: I tell thee that she has been marred by her gown.
target: I tell thee , I , that thou hast marred her gown .

input: Your worship is being deceived.
target: Your Worship is deceived .

input: The gown is the same as the direction my master gave it.
target: The gown is made Just as my master had direction .

input: The order how it should be done was given by the person.
target: Grumio gave order how it should be done .

target: I gave him no order .

input: I gave him some things.
target: I gave him the stuff .

input: How did you think it should be made?
target: But how did you desire it should be made ?

input: Marry, sir, with a needle and a thread.
target: Marry , sir , with needle and thread .

input: Did you not request that it be cut?
target: But did you not request to have it cut ?

input: Don't face me, face not me.
target: Face not me .

input: Thou has braved a lot of men, but not me.
target: Thou hast braved many men ; brave not me .

input: I will not be facing or braved.
target: I will neither be faced nor braved .

input: I did not bid him to cut it to pieces, but I did bid him to cutout the gown.
target: I say unto thee , I bid thy master cutout the gown , but I did not bid him cut it to pieces .

input: Why is the note of the fashion to testify here.
target: Why , here is the note of the fashion to testify .

input: It's a good idea to read it.
target: Read it .

input: If he says I said so, the note lies in his throat.
target: The note lies in 's throat , if he say I said so .

input: Dost you love pictures?
target: Dost thou love pictures ?

input: There is a lady far more beautiful than any woman in this waning age.
target: Thou hast a lady far more beautiful Than any woman in this waning age .

input: She was the prettiest creature in the world and yet she is inferior to none.
target: And till the tears that she hath shed for thee Like envious floods o'errun her lovely face , She was the fairest creature in the world , And yet she is inferior to none .

input: I confess that I wore the cape.
target: I confess the cape .

input: I confess that I have two sleeves.
target: I confess two sleeves .

input: The villany is there.
target: Ay , there's the villany .

input: I had an error with the bill, sir!
target: Error i ' the bill , sir , error i ' the bill !

input: I told them to cut out the sleeves and sew them up again, and that I'll show them that they're wrong, though I have a small finger.
target: I commanded the sleeves should be cut out and sewed up again , and that I'll prove upon thee , though thy little finger be armed in a thimble .

input: I am for the straight story.
target: I am for thee straight .

input: Take the bill, give me the yard, and spare me.
target: Take thou the bill , give me thy mete- yard , and spare not me .

input: God-a-mercy, Grumio.
target: God-a-mercy , Grumio !

input: Then he will have no chance.
target: Then he shall have no odds .

input: In brief, the gown is not for me.
target: Well , sir , in brief , the gown is not for me .

input: You are the right man, sir, for my mistress.
target: You are i ' the right , sir , 'tis for my mistress .

input: Take it up and use it for your master's use.
target: Go , take it up unto thy master's use .

input: Not a villain, but a person.
target: Villain , not for thy life !

input: For my master's use, take up my mistress' gown.
target: Take up my mistress ' gown for thy master's use !

input: Why, sir, what's your reason for doing that?
target: Why , sir , what's your conceit in that ?

input: The conceit is deeper than you might think.
target: O , sir , the conceit is deeper than you think for .

input: Take my mistress gown with me to his master's use.
target: Take up my mistress ' gown to his master's use !

input: O, fie, fie, fie!
target: O , fie , fie , fie !

input: My Kate, come, come.
target: Well , come , my Kate .

input: Is the lark more precious than the jay because his feathers are more beautiful?
target: What , is the jay more precious than the lark Because his feathers are more beautiful ?

input: Is the adder better than the eel because of the paint on his skin.
target: Or is the adder better than the eel Because his painted skin contents the eye ?

input: Good Kate, no, no.
target: Oh , no , good Kate .

input: If it's shame, lay it on me, and then frolic.
target: If thou account'st it shame , lay it on me , And therefore frolic !

input: We are going to feast and sport ourselves at the father's house.
target: We will hence forthwith To feast and sport us at thy father's house .

target: I dare assure you , sir , 'tis almost two , And 'twill be supper time ere you come there .

input: I will go to the horse at seven.
target: It shall be seven ere I go to horse .

input: You are still crossing it, look what I say, or do, or think about it.
target: Look what I speak , or do , or think to do , You are still crossing it .

input: Let 't alone, Sirs.
target: Sirs , let 't alone .

input: I will not be going today, and it will be at what time I say it is.
target: I will not go today , and ere I do It shall be what o'clock I say it is .

input: What else are you talking about?
target: Ay , what else ?

input: Signior Baptista may remember me from twenty years ago, when we were lodgers at the Pegasus in Genoa.
target: and but I be deceived , Signior Baptista may remember me , Near twenty years ago , in Genoa , Where we were lodgers at the Pegasus .

input: I want you to be mine.
target: I warrant you .

input: But, sir, here comes your boy.
target: But , sir , here comes your boy .

input: Don't worry not me.
target: Tut , fear not me .

input: I told you that your father was in Venice and that you were looking for him in Padua.
target: I told him that your father was at Venice , And that you looked for him this day in Padua .

input: Baptista arrives here.
target: Here comes Baptista .

input: Sir, set your face on the table.
target: Set your countenance , sir .

input: Signior Baptista, Sir, this is the gentleman that I told you.
target: Signior Baptista , you are happily met. , Sir , this is the gentleman I told you of .

input: I want you to be a good father to me now.
target: I pray you stand good father to me now .

input: Give Bianca to me for my patriotism.
target: Give me Bianca for my patrimony .

input: Sir, please forgive me for what I have to say.
target: Sir , pardon me in what I have to say .

input: Your plainness and the way you speak please me.
target: Your plainness and your shortness please me well .

input: It is your son Lucentio who Doth love my daughter and she love him, or both of them.
target: Right true it is your son Lucentio here Doth love my daughter and she loveth him , Or both dissemble deeply their affections .

input: My daughter will have your son's consent.
target: Your son shall have my daughter with consent .

input: Pitchers have ears, and I have many servants, but not in my house, Lucentio.
target: Not in my house , Lucentio , for you know Pitchers have ears , and I have many servants .

input: We might be interrupted, because old Gremio is still heark'ning.
target: Besides , old Gremio is heark'ning still , And happily we might be interrupted .

input: I am praying for her with all of my strength.
target: I pray the gods she may , with all my heart !

input: It was called Cambio.
target: Cambio .

input: What do you think about Biondello?
target: What sayest thou , Biondello ?

input: You watched my master wink and laugh at you?
target: You saw my master wink and laugh upon you ?

input: What is that, Biondello?
target: Biondello , what of that ?

input: I am praying that thee moralize them.
target: I pray thee , moralize them .

input: Baptista is safe, talking with the father of a son that is deceiving.
target: Then thus : Baptista is safe , talking with the deceiving father of a deceitful son .

input: And what about him?
target: And what of him ?

input: His daughter is going to be with you at the supper.
target: His daughter is to be brought by you to the supper .

target: And then ?

input: At all hours, the old priest at Saintluke's Church is at your command.
target: The old priest at Saint Luke's Church is at your command at all hours .

input: And what about this?
target: And what of all this ?

input: I don't know, except they are busied about a counterfeit assurance.
target: I can not tell , except they are busied about a counterfeit assurance .

input: You should take assurance of her cum privilegio ad imprimendum solum.
target: Take you assurance of her cum privilegio ad imprimendum solum .

input: To the church, take the priest, clerk, and some honest witnesses.
target: To th ' church take the priest , clerk , and some sufficient honest witnesses .

input: If this is not what you are looking for, I have no more to say, but bid Bianca farewell.
target: If this be not that you look for , I have no more to say , But bid Bianca farewell forever and a day .

input: I knew that a wench married in the afternoon when she went to the garden for parsley to stuff the rabbit.
target: I knew a wench married in an afternoon as she went to the garden for parsley to stuff a rabbit , and so may you , sir .

target: And so adieu , sir .

input: I was appointed by my master to go to Saintluke's to try to get the priest to come against you.
target: My master hath appointed me to go to Saint Luke's to bid the priest be ready to come against you come with your appendix .

input: She will be very happy.
target: She will be pleased .

input: I don't know where to think about doubt.
target: Then wherefore should I doubt ?

target: It shall go hard if "Cambio" go without her .

input: I want God's name to once more be toward our father's.
target: Come on , i ' God's name , once more toward our father's .

target: Good Lord , how bright and goodly shines the moon !

target: The moon ?

target: The sun !

input: It is not night time now.
target: It is not moonlight now .

target: I say it is the moon that shines so bright .

target: I know it is the sun that shines so bright .

target: Now , by my mother's son , and that's myself , It shall be moon , or star , or what I list , Or e'er I journey to your father's house .

input: I think it is the moon.
target: I say it is the moon .

input: The moon is what I am aware of.
target: I know it is the moon .

input: Then you tell the truth.
target: Nay , then you lie .

input: It is the sun that is blessed.
target: It is the blessed sun .

input: It is the blessed sun that God be blessed.
target: Then God be blessed , it is the blessed sun .

target: Petruchio , go thy ways ; the field is won .

input: Well, forward, forward.
target: Well , forward , forward !

input: The bowl should run, and not be unluckily against the bias.
target: Thus the bowl should run , And not unluckily against the bias .

input: But, soft!
target: But , soft !

input: There is a company coming here.
target: Company is coming here .

input: Young budding virgin, fair and fresh and sweet, or where is she located?
target: Young budding virgin , fair and fresh and sweet , Whither away , or where is thy abode ?

input: Happy birthday to the parents of a fair child.
target: Happy the parents of so fair a child .

input: Will it please you to wash your hands?
target: Will 't please your Mightiness to wash your hands ?

input: How happy we are to see your wit restored!
target: O , how we joy to see your wit restored !

input: That once more you know, but what are you?
target: O , that once more you knew but what you are !

target: These fifteen years you have been in a dream Or , when you waked , so waked as if you slept .

target: These fifteen years !

input: By my fay, a good sleep.
target: By my fay , a goodly nap .

target: But did I never speak of all that time ?

target: O , yes , my lord , but very idle words .

input: Why, how now, Kate!
target: Why , how now , Kate !

input: I hope he doesn't get mad.
target: I hope thou art not mad .

target: Fair sir , and you , my merry mistress , That with your strange encounter much amazed me , My name is called Vincentio , my dwelling Pisa , And bound I am to Padua , there to visit A son of mine which long I have not seen .

input: What is his name, what is it?
target: What is his name ?

input: Sir, gentle sir, Lucentio.
target: Lucentio , gentle sir .

input: It was a happy meeting for the boy.
target: Happily met , the happier for thy son .

input: My wife's sister, this gentle woman, and my son by this are married.
target: The sister to my wife , this gentlewoman , Thy son by this hath married .

input: Wonder not be upset.
target: Wonder not Nor be grieved .

input: Let me embrace with oldVincentio, and then wander to see his honest son, who will be full joyous when he arrives.
target: Let me embrace with old Vincentio , And wander we to see thy honest son , Who will of thy arrival be full joyous .

input: I assure you that it is, father.
target: I do assure thee , father , so it is .

input: This has put me in a state of mind.
target: Well , Petruchio , this has put me in heart .

input: Sir, for the priest is ready, Softly and quickly.
target: Softly and swiftly , sir , for the priest is ready .

input: Biondello is where I fly.
target: I fly , Biondello .

input: I'll see the church and then come back to my master's as soon as possible.
target: Nay , faith , I'll see the church a ' your back , and then come back to my master's as soon as I can .

input: I am amazed that Cambio doesn't come all this while.
target: I marvel Cambio comes not all this while .

input: Here is the door, Sir.
target: Sir , here's the door .

input: The house is owned by Lucentio.
target: This is Lucentio's house .

input: My father is more towards the marketplace.
target: My father's bears more toward the marketplace .

input: I leave you here, sir, because Thither must I.

input: You should drink before you leave.
target: You shall not choose but drink before you go .

input: They are busy inside.
target: They're busy within .

input: You were the best to shout louder.
target: You were best knock louder .

input: Is Signior Lucentio a part of me?
target: Is Signior Lucentio within , sir ?

input: If a man brought him a hundred pound or two, what would that do to him?
target: What if a man bring him a hundred pound or two to make merry withal ?

target: Hope I may choose , sir .

input: You rogue, come hither.
target: Come hither , you rogue !

input: Have you not remembered me?
target: What , have you forgot me ?

input: I'm sorry, I forgot you.
target: Forgot you !

input: Yes, sir.
target: No , sir .

input: For I have never seen you before, I could not forget you.
target: I could not forget you , for I never saw you before in all my life .

input: My old worshipful old master, what are you doing?
target: What , my old worshipful old master ?

input: Yes, sir, marry.
target: Yes , marry , sir .

input: You can see where he is looking out of the window.
target: See where he looks out of the window .

input: Is that true, indeed.
target: Is 't so , indeed .

input: Help, help, help, help!
target: Help , help , help !

input: Here's a madman who will kill me.
target: Here's a madman will murder me .

input: Oh, I am undone!
target: Oh , I am undone , I am undone !

input: What is the man crazy about?
target: What , is the man lunatic ?

input: The father!
target: Thy father !

input: The villain.
target: O villain !

input: He is a sailmaker in Bergamo.
target: He is a sailmaker in Bergamo .

input: You mistake, sir, you mistake, sir.
target: You mistake , sir , you mistake , sir .

input: What do you think about his name, please?
target: Pray , what do you think is his name ?

input: His name was mentioned.
target: His name !

input: It is Lucentio.
target: Lucentio !

input: Oh, he murdered his master.
target: Oh , he hath murdered his master !

input: O my son and my son!
target: O my son , my son !

input: I want to know where my son Lucentio is.
target: Tell me , thou villain , where is my son Lucentio ?

input: Father Baptista, I charge you see that he will be forthcoming.
target: Carry this mad knave to the jail. , Father Baptista , I charge you see that he be forthcoming .

input: Is it possible to bring me to the jail.
target: Carry me to the jail ?

input: He will not be going to prison.
target: He shall not go to prison .

input: Signior Gremio, don't talk.
target: Talk not , Signior Gremio .

input: I believe he will go to prison.
target: I say he shall go to prison .

input: Signior Baptista, do not allow yourself to be caught up in this business.
target: Take heed , Signior Baptista , lest you be cony-catched in this business .

input: I dare say this is the right man.
target: I dare swear this is the right Vincentio .

input: I don't dare to swear it.
target: Nay , I dare not swear it .

input: I know I'm supposed to be Signior Lucentio.
target: Yes , I know thee to be Signior Lucentio .

input: The dotard was away with me.
target: Away with the dotard !

input: To the prison with him.
target: To the jail with him !

input: It's O!
target: O !

input: We are spoiled and he is too.
target: We are spoiled and yonder he is !

input: Pardon is a sweet father.
target: Pardon , sweet father .

input: Is my sweet son still alive?
target: Lives my sweet son ?

input: Thank you Pardon, dear father.
target: Pardon , dear father .

input: How hast he been offended?
target: How hast thou offended ?

input: What is the location of Lucentio.
target: Where is Lucentio ?

input: Here's Lucentio, right son to the rightVincentio, that have by marriage made their daughter mine.
target: Here's Lucentio , right son to the right Vincentio , That have by marriage made thy daughter mine While counterfeit supposes bleared thine eyne .

input: To deceive us all, here's packing, with a witness!
target: Here's packing , with a witness , to deceive us all !

input: That faced and braved me in this matter, where is that damned villain, Tranio?
target: Where is that damned villain , Tranio , That faced and braved me in this matter so ?

input: Tell me why this is not my Cambio.
target: Why , tell me , is not this my Cambio ?

input: Lucentio is the new name for Cambio.
target: Cambio is changed into Lucentio .

input: These miracles were made possible by love.
target: Love wrought these miracles .

input: While he did bear my countenance in the town, I have arrived at the last Unto the wished haven of my bliss, because of Bianca's love.
target: Bianca's love Made me exchange my state with Tranio , While he did bear my countenance in the town , And happily I have arrived at the last Unto the wished haven of my bliss .

input: I enforced him to what Tranio did.
target: What Tranio did , myself enforced him to .

input: For my sake, please pardon him, sweet father.
target: Then pardon him , sweet father , for my sake .

input: I'll slit the villain's nose to prevent him from sending me to the jail.
target: I'll slit the villain's nose that would have sent me to the jail .

input: But do you know if you married my daughter without asking for my goodwill?
target: But do you hear , sir , have you married my daughter without asking my goodwill ?

input: Baptista, we will be content with you.
target: Fear not , Baptista , we will content you .

input: Go to that place.
target: Go to .

input: My cake is dough, but I'll be in among the rest, out of hope, but my share of the feast.
target: My cake is dough , but I'll in among the rest , Out of hope of all but my share of the feast .

input: Let's see what the end of this ado looks like.
target: Husband , let's follow to see the end of this ado .

input: First kiss me, Kate, and we will do it again.
target: First kiss me , Kate , and we will .

input: What is happening in the middle of the street?
target: What , in the midst of the street ?

input: What do you think, art, I'm ashamed of you?
target: What , art thou ashamed of me ?

input: God forbid, but ashamed to kiss.
target: No , sir , God forbid , but ashamed to kiss .

input: Let's return to home again.
target: Why , then let's home again .

target: Are you my wife and will not call me "husband" ?

target: My men should call me "lord." I am your goodman .

target: My fair Bianca , bid my father welcome , While I with selfsame kindness welcome thine .

target: My banquet is to close our stomachs up , After our great good cheer .

target: Pray you , sit down , For now we sit to chat as well as eat .

target: Nothing but sit and sit , and eat and eat !

target: For both our sakes , I would that word were true .

target: Now , for my life , Hortensio fears his widow .

target: You are very sensible , and yet you miss my sense : I mean , Hortensio is afeard of you .

target: Mistress , how mean you that ?

target: He that is giddy thinks the world turns round" , I pray you , tell me what you meant by that .

target: Your husband being troubled with a shrew Measures my husband's sorrow by his woe .

target: And now you know my meaning .

target: A very mean meaning .

target: Right , I mean you .

target: To her , widow !

target: A hundred marks , my Kate does put her down .

target: That's my office .

input: It sounded like an officer.
target: Spoke like an officer !

input: I wish to thee, lad.
target: Ha ' to thee , lad !

input: How much do you like these quick-witted people?
target: How likes Gremio these quick-witted folks ?

target: Believe me , sir , they butt together well .

input: I was not frighted by Ay.
target: Ay , but not frighted me .

input: I'll be able to sleep again.
target: Therefore I'll sleep again .

input: Do you have your bird?
target: Am I your bird ?

target: Here , Signior Tranio , This bird you aimed at , though you hit her not. , Therefore a health to all that shot and missed .

target: A good swift simile , but something currish .

target: Tis well , sir , that you hunted for yourself .

target: Tranio hits you now .

target: I thank thee for that gird , good Tranio .

target: Twenty crowns ?

input: I'll venture so much of my hound or hawk that I'll venture so much of my wife as well.
target: I'll venture so much of my hawk or hound , But twenty times so much upon my wife .

target: Content .

target: Go , Biondello , bid your mistress come to me .

target: I'll have no halves .

target: How !

target: She's busy , and she can not come ! " Is that an answer ?

target: Ay , and a kind one too .

target: Pray God , sir , your wife send you not a worse .

target: I hope better .

target: Now , where's my wife ?

target: She says you have some goodly jest in hand .

target: She bids you come to her .

target: Worse and worse .

input: I know her answer, I know that.
target: I know her answer .

target: What ?

target: She will not .

target: Now , by my holidam , here comes Katherina !
