target: What is your will , sir , that you send for me ?

input: Hortensio's wife and your sister are not located.
target: Where is your sister , and Hortensio's wife ?

input: They are sitting by the parlor fire.
target: They sit conferring by the parlor fire .

input: Go fetch them and hither.
target: Go fetch them hither .

input: If they don't show up, Swinge me them against their husbands.
target: If they deny to come , Swinge me them soundly forth unto their husbands .

input: If you talk of a wonder here, it is a wonder.
target: Here is a wonder , if you talk of a wonder .

input: And so it is as well.
target: And so it is .

input: I am wondering what it means.
target: I wonder what it bodes .

input: Marry, peace, and love, and quiet life, and awful rule, and right supremacy, and to be short, what not that's sweet and happy?
target: Marry , peace it bodes , and love , and quiet life , And awful rule , and right supremacy , And , to be short , what not that's sweet and happy ?

input: Good Petruchio, fair befall thee!
target: Now , fair befall thee , good Petruchio !

input: I will add their losses of twenty thousand crowns and another daughter to their total, for she is changed as she had never been before.
target: The wager thou hast won , and I will add Unto their losses twenty thousand crowns , Another dowry to another daughter , For she is changed as she had never been .

input: See where she comes and brings your wives as well as her prisoners.
target: See where she comes and brings your froward wives As prisoners to her womanly persuasion. , Katherine , that cap of yours becomes you not .

input: Throw that bauble at the ground.
target: Off with that bauble , throw it underfoot .

input: Lord, I will never have a reason to sigh, until I am brought to such a silly pass.
target: Lord , let me never have a cause to sigh , Till I be brought to such a silly pass !

input: Fie, Fie!
target: Fie !

input: What is a foolish duty to call you this?
target: What a foolish duty call you this ?

input: I would think your duty was foolish too.
target: I would your duty were as foolish too .

input: Since suppertime, Bianca, Hath cost me an hundred crowns for the wisdom of your duty.
target: The wisdom of your duty , fair Bianca , Hath cost me an hundred crowns since suppertime .

input: You have to be more careful for laying on my duty.
target: The more fool you for laying on my duty .

input: We won't have any clue.
target: We will have no telling .

input: She will not do that.
target: She shall not .

input: First, I say she will.
target: I say she shall. , And first begin with her .

input: Fie, fie.
target: Fie , fie !

input: Unknit that threat, and dart not to look at those eyes, to wound the lord, king, and governor.
target: Unknit that threat'ning unkind brow And dart not scornful glances from those eyes To wound thy lord , thy king , thy governor .

input: The subject owes the prince and the woman owes his husband.
target: Such duty as the subject owes the prince , Even such a woman oweth to her husband .

input: When she is froward, peevish, sullen, sour, and not obedient to his honest will, what is she?
target: And when she is froward , peevish , sullen , sour , And not obedient to his honest will , What is she but a foul contending rebel And graceless traitor to her loving lord ?

input: I am ashamed that women are so simple to offer war, where they should kneel for peace, or seek for rule, supremacy, and sway, when they are bound to serve, love, and obey.
target: I am ashamed that women are so simple To offer war where they should kneel for peace ; Or seek for rule , supremacy and sway When they are bound to serve , love , and obey .

input: Our bodies are soft and weak, we are not able to toil and trouble in the world, and we should agree with our external parts.
target: Why are our bodies soft and weak and smooth , Unapt to toil and trouble in the world , But that our soft conditions and our hearts Should well agree with our external parts ?

input: You can't froward and unable worms!
target: Come , come , you froward and unable worms !

input: To bandy word for word and frown for frown, my mind has been as big as one of yours.
target: My mind hath been as big as one of yours , My heart as great , my reason haply more , To bandy word for word and frown for frown .

input: Our strength as weak, our weakness past compare, and our lances are but straws, that seems to be what we least are.
target: But now I see our lances are but straws , Our strength as weak , our weakness past compare , That seeming to be most which we indeed least are .

input: Come on and kiss me, Kate.
target: Come on and kiss me , Kate .

input: When children are near, it is a good hearing.
target: Tis a good hearing when children are toward .

input: When women are froward, the hearing is very harsh.
target: But a harsh hearing when women are froward .

input: Come, Kate, we'll sleep.
target: Come , Kate , we'll to bed .

input: Three people are married, but two of them are not.
target: We three are married , but you two are sped .

input: By your leave, she will be taken care of.
target: Tis a wonder , by your leave , she will be tamed so .

input: They say that I have dreamed and slept for fifteen years or more.
target: Madam wife , they say that I have dreamed And slept above some fifteen year or more .

input: The time seems thirty years old, being abandoned from your bed.
target: Ay , and the time seems thirty unto me , Being all this time abandoned from your bed .

input: Leave me and her alone, servants.
target: Tis much. , Servants , leave me and her alone .

input: Come now to bed, madam, undress you.
target: Madam , undress you and come now to bed .

input: Let me ask for a night or two of forgiveness from you, until the sun comes up.
target: Thrice noble lord , let me entreat of you To pardon me yet for a night or two , Or if not so , until the sun be set .

target: For your physicians have expressly charged , In peril to incur your former malady , That I should yet absent me from your bed .

input: I hope this is the reason for the excuse.
target: I hope this reason stands for my excuse .

input: I may not tarry so long because it stands so still.
target: Ay , it stands so that I may hardly tarry so long .

input: I wouldn't want to go back into my dreams again.
target: But I would be loath to fall into my dreams again .

input: Your Honor's players, hearing your amendment, are come to play a pleasant comedy, for so your doctors hold it very meet, and see too much sadness and congealed your blood, and melancholy is the nurse of frenzy.
target: Your Honor's players , hearing your amendment , Are come to play a pleasant comedy , For so your doctors hold it very meet , Seeing too much sadness hath congealed your blood , And melancholy is the nurse of frenzy .

input: They thought it was good that you hear a play and frame your mind to be merry and long life.
target: Therefore they thought it good you hear a play And frame your mind to mirth and merriment , Which bars a thousand harms and lengthens life .

target: Let them play it .

input: What are the household stuff?
target: What , household stuff ?

target: It is a kind of history .

input: Well, we'll see that.
target: Well , we'll see 't .

input: We will be younger than him.
target: We shall ne'er be younger .

target: Pisa , renowned for grave citizens , Gave me my being and my father first , A merchant of great traffic through the world , Vincentio , come of the Bentivolii .

input: I will pheaze you, in faith.
target: I'll pheeze you , in faith .

input: A pair of stocks, you rogue.
target: A pair of stocks , you rogue !

input: Slys are not rogues, they are a baggage.
target: Y'are a baggage , the Slys are no rogues .

input: You won't have to pay for the glasses that you have burst.
target: Therefore You will not pay for the glasses you have burst ?

input: I am not a denier.
target: No , not a denier .

target: Go by , Saint Jeronimy .

target: Go to thy cold bed and warm thee .

target: Master , some show to welcome us to town .

target: But if it were , doubt not her care should be To comb your noddle with a three-legged stool And paint your face and use you like a fool .

target: From all such devils , good Lord , deliver us !

target: And me too , good Lord !

target: Maid's mild behavior and sobriety .

target: Sister , content you in my discontent. , Sir , to your pleasure humbly I subscribe .

target: My books and instruments shall be my company , On them to look and practice by myself .

input: , Hark, and Tranio!
target: Hark , Tranio !

target: Signior Baptista , will you be so strange ?

target: And for I know she taketh most delight In music , instruments , and poetry , Schoolmasters will I keep within my house , Fit to instruct her youth .

target: And so farewell. , Katherina , you may stay , For I have more to commune with Bianca .

target: Why , and I trust I may go too , may I not ?

target: What , shall I be appointed hours as though , belike , I knew not what to take and what to leave , ha ?

target: You may go to the devil's dam !

input: The farewell is over.
target: Farewell .

target: Though the nature of our quarrel yet never brooked parle , know now upon advice , it toucheth us both , that we may yet again have access to our fair mistress and be happy rivals in Bianca's love , to labor and effect one thing specially .

target: What's that , I pray ?

target: Marry , sir , to get a husband for her sister .

target: I say a husband .

target: I say a devil .

target: Think'st thou , Hortensio , though her father be very rich , any man is so very a fool to be married to hell ?

target: Tush , Gremio .

input: Though it pass your patience and mine to endure her loud alarums, why, man, there be good fellows in the world, an a man could light on them, would take her with all of her faults, and money enough.
target: Though it pass your patience and mine to endure her loud alarums , why , man , there be good fellows in the world , an a man could light on them , would take her with all faults , and money enough .

target: I can not tell .

input: How do you say you are, Signior Gremio?
target: How say you , Signior Gremio ?

target: I am agreed , and would I had given him the best horse inv Padua to begin his wooing that would thoroughly woo her , wed her , and bed her , and rid the house of her !

target: I pray , sir , tell me , is it possible That love should of a sudden take such hold ?

target: O Tranio , till I found it to be true , I never thought it possible or likely .

input: Affection is not rated on a scale of 1 to 10.
target: Affection is not rated from the heart .

input: If you have been touched by love, naught remains, but go forward.
target: If love have touched you , naught remains but so : Gramercies , lad , go forward .

input: This is all that is contained in this contents.
target: This contents .

input: The rest will make you feel better, for counsel's sound.
target: The rest will comfort , for thy counsel's sound .

input: Perhaps you marked not what's the pith of all, Master, because you looked so longly on the maid.
target: Master , you looked so longly on the maid , Perhaps you marked not what's the pith of all .

input: The daughter of Agenor had a beautiful face, that made Jove to humble himself to her hand.
target: Oh yes , I saw sweet beauty in her face Such as the daughter of Agenor had , That made great Jove to humble him to her hand When with his knees he kissed the Cretan strand .

input: Did you see that you no longer exist?
target: Saw you no more ?

input: I saw her coral lips move, and she did perfume the air with her breath.
target: Tranio , I saw her coral lips to move And with her breath she did perfume the air .

target: Ah , Tranio , what a cruel father's he !

input: He took some care to get her schoolmasters to instruct her.
target: But art thou not advised , he took some care To get her cunning schoolmasters to instruct her ?

target: Ay , marry , am I , sir ; and now 'tis plotted !

input: I have it, you know what I mean.
target: I have it , Tranio !

input: Both of our inventions meet and jump in one.
target: Master , for my hand , Both our inventions meet and jump in one .

input: Tell me the first thing you can.
target: Tell me thine first .

input: You will be the schoolmaster, and teach the maid.
target: You will be schoolmaster And undertake the teaching of the maid : That's your device .

input: It is, indeed.
target: It is .

input: Is it possible that it will be done?
target: May it be done ?

input: It is not possible.
target: Not possible .

input: It will be so, and will be hatched.
target: Tis hatched , and shall be so .

input: When Biondello arrives, I will charm him first so that he will keep his tongue.
target: When Biondello comes , he waits on thee , But I will charm him first to keep his tongue .

input: What have I been doing?
target: Where have I been ?

input: Where are you right now?
target: Nay , how now , where are you ?

input: Sirrah, come hither, frame your manners to the time, because you don't have time to laugh.
target: Sirrah , come hither : 'tis no time to jest , And therefore frame your manners to the time .

input: You understand me, right?
target: You understand me ?

input: I agree, sir.
target: Aye , sir .

input: Not a single word of "Tranio" was written in your mouth.
target: And not a jot of "Tranio" in your mouth .

input: Would I be like that as well?
target: Would I were so too .

input: I could have the next wish after that, that Lucentio had Baptista's youngest daughter.
target: So could I , faith , boy , to have the next wish after , That Lucentio indeed had Baptista's youngest daughter .

input: I advise you to use your manners discreetly in all kinds of companies, but not for my sake.
target: But , sirrah , not for my sake , but your master's , I advise You use your manners discreetly in all kind of companies .

input: When I'm alone, I'm called tranio, but in all places other than your master Lucentio.
target: When I am alone , why then I am Tranio ; But in all places else , your master Lucentio .

input: Let's go, tranio.
target: Tranio , let's go .

input: To make one among these wooers, you have to execute, that's all.
target: One thing more rests , that thyself execute , to make one among these wooers .

input: My reasons are both good and heavy if you want to ask them.
target: If thou ask me why , sufficeth my reasons are both good and weighty .

input: Your lord, you nod.
target: My lord , you nod .

input: You don't mind what's happening.
target: You do not mind the play .

input: A good matter, surely.
target: A good matter , surely .

input: Does anyone have any more of it?
target: Comes there any more of it ?

input: madam lady, it is an excellent piece of work.
target: Tis a very excellent piece of work , madam lady .

input: Would be finished.
target: Would 'twere done .

input: I charge thee and tender well my hounds.
target: Huntsman , I charge thee , tender well my hounds .

input: Clowder and Merriman are together, and the poor Cur is embossed.
target: Breathe Merriman , the poor cur is embossed , And couple Clowder with the deep-mouthed brach .

input: My lord, Belman is just as good as he is.
target: Why , Belman is as good as he , my lord .

input: Trust me, I will take him for the better dog.
target: Trust me , I take him for the better dog .

input: Thou does not know what he is doing.
target: Thou art a fool .

input: I would value him worth a dozen such if he were a fleet.
target: If Echo were as fleet , I would esteem him worth a dozen such .

input: Take care of them and look at them all.
target: But sup them well and look unto them all .

input: I intend to hunt again tomorrow.
target: Tomorrow I intend to hunt again .

input: My lord, I will, I will.
target: I will , my lord .

input: What's happening here?
target: What's here ?

input: Do you mean one dead or drunk?
target: One dead , or drunk ?

input: Do the man breathe?
target: See , doth he breathe ?

input: My lord, he is breathing.
target: He breathes , my lord .

input: This was a bed that was cold to sleep in, but he was warmed with beer.
target: Were he not warmed with ale , This were a bed but cold to sleep so soundly .

input: Grim death, how foul is it?
target: Grim death , how foul and loathsome is thine image !

input: Sirs, I will practice on this drunk man.
target: Sirs , I will practice on this drunken man .

input: For a while, I take my leave to see my friends in Padua, but also my best friend, Hortensio.
target: Verona , for a while I take my leave , To see my friends in Padua , but of all My best beloved and approved friend , Hortensio .

input: This is his house, I trow that.
target: And I trow this is his house .

input: Here is sirrah Grumio.
target: Here , sirrah Grumio .

input: Knock, I say.
target: Knock , I say .

input: Sir, do you want to Knock?
target: Knock , sir ?

input: Whom should I knock on the door?
target: Whom should I knock ?

input: Do you know if any man has rearranged your worship?
target: Is there any man has rebused your Worship ?

input: Is it possible to knock you here, sir?
target: Knock you here , sir ?

input: I say knock me at this gate, or I'll knock your knave's pate.
target: Villain , I say , knock me at this gate And rap me well , or I'll knock your knave's pate .

input: My master is not happy with me.
target: My master is grown quarrelsome .

input: What's the matter right now?
target: How now , what's the matter ?

input: Is there a good friend of my old friend Grumio and a good friend of my good friend Petruchio?
target: My old friend Grumio and my good friend Petruchio ?

input: What are you doing at Verona?
target: How do you all at Verona ?

input: Come on, signior Hortensio, join the fight?
target: Signior Hortensio , come you to part the fray ?

input: I don't care, sir, what he "leges" in Latin.
target: Nay , 'tis no matter , sir , what he 'leges in Latin .

input: I could not get him to knock on the gate for me.
target: I bade the rascal knock upon your gate And could not get him for my heart to do it .

input: Do you want to knock at the gate.
target: Knock at the gate ?

input: The heavens are o heavens.
target: O heavens !

input: Don't say "sirrah, knock me here, rap me here, knock me well, and knock me soundly"?
target: Spake you not these words plain : "Sirrah , knock me here , rap me here , knock me well , and knock me soundly" ?

input: "Knocking at the gate", come you now.
target: And come you now with "knocking at the gate" ?

input: There is a man named Petruchio, and he is patience.
target: Petruchio , patience .

input: I am the pledge of the man.
target: I am Grumio's pledge .

input: Why, this is a heavy chance, and you and your ancient, pleasant servant, Grumio.
target: Why , this ' a heavy chance 'twixt him and you , Your ancient , trusty , pleasant servant Grumio .

input: Tell me what happy gale Blows you to Padua here from old Verona.
target: And tell me now , sweet friend , what happy gale Blows you to Padua here from old Verona ?

input: The wind scatters young men through the world to seek their fortunes farther than at home.
target: Such wind as scatters young men through the world To seek their fortunes farther than at home , Where small experience grows .

input: I travel abroad to see the world because I have crowns in my purse and goods at home.
target: Crowns in my purse I have and goods at home , And so am come abroad to see the world .

input: I'll promise thee that she will be very rich, even though I'd like to thank you for my counsel.
target: Thou'dst thank me but a little for my counsel ; And yet I'll promise thee she shall be rich , And very rich .

input: I will not wish thee to my friend.
target: But thou'rt too much my friend , And I'll not wish thee to her .

input: Few words suffice, Signior Hortensio, "twixt such friends as we".
target: Signior Hortensio , 'twixt such friends as we Few words suffice .

input: I can help thee to a wife with wealth and young and beautiful beings. Brought up as best as possible becomes a gentle woman.
target: I can , Petruchio , help thee to a wife With wealth enough , and young and beauteous , Brought up as best becomes a gentlewoman .

input: I would not wed her for a mine of gold because she is the only fault, she is intolerable and shrewd and froward, so beyond all measure.
target: Her only fault , and that is faults enough , Is that she is intolerable curst , And shrewd and froward , so beyond all measure That , were my state far worser than it is , I would not wed her for a mine of gold .

input: Peace and Hortensio.
target: Hortensio , peace .

input: The gold's effect is not something that Thou know about.
target: Thou know'st not gold's effect .

input: Baptista Minola is an amiable and courteous gentleman and her father.
target: Her father is Baptista Minola , An affable and courteous gentleman .

input: Her name is Katherina Minola and she is renowned for her tongue.
target: Her name is Katherina Minola , Renowned in Padua for her scolding tongue .

input: I know her father, though I don't know her, and he knew my dead father well.
target: I know her father , though I know not her , And he knew my deceased father well .

input: Hortensio, I will not sleep until I see her, so let me be bold with you, unless you will accompany me.
target: I will not sleep , Hortensio , till I see her , And therefore let me be thus bold with you To give you over at this first encounter , Unless you will accompany me thither .

input: I must go with thee, for in Baptista's keep my treasure is.
target: Tarry , Petruchio , I must go with thee , For in Baptista's keep my treasure is .

input: He has the jewel of my life in hold, his youngest daughter, beautiful Bianca, and her withholdings from me and other more, Suitors to her and rivals in my love, Supposing it is a thing impossible.
target: He hath the jewel of my life in hold , His youngest daughter , beautiful Bianca , And her withholds from me and other more , Suitors to her and rivals in my love , Supposing it a thing impossible , For those defects I have before rehearsed , That ever Katherina will be wooed .

input: The title for a maid of all titles is the worst.
target: Katherine the curst ! " A title for a maid of all titles the worst .

input: I want to be a schoolmaster and teach Bianca, so I will be hidden in sober robes, by this device, at least.
target: Now shall my friend Petruchio do me grace , And offer me disguised in sober robes To old Baptista as a schoolmaster Well seen in music , to instruct Bianca , That so I may , by this device at least , Have leave and leisure to make love to her And , unsuspected , court her by herself .

input: There's no knavery here.
target: Here's no knavery !

input: Look about you, Master.
target: Master , master , look about you .

input: Who goes there, ha?
target: Who goes there , ha ?

input: Peace and good fortune, Grumio.
target: Peace , Grumio .

input: It is the opposite of my love.
target: It is the rival of my love .

input: Stand by a while, Petruchio.
target: Petruchio , stand by a while .

input: What a thing it is, O this learning!
target: O this learning , what a thing it is !

input: Signior Hortensio, and you are well met.
target: And you are well met , Signior Hortensio .

input: Trow you, I am going.
target: Trow you whither I am going ?

input: To the Baptista Minola.
target: To Baptista Minola .

input: Well done, Tis well.
target: Tis well .

input: I was promised by Hath that he would help me to another musician who would teach our mistress.
target: And I have met a gentleman Hath promised me to help me to another , A fine musician to instruct our mistress .

input: Gremio, now is not a good time to express our love.
target: Gremio , 'tis now no time to vent our love .

input: So done, it is well.
target: So said , so done , is well .

input: Hortensio, have you told him all the things she did wrong?
target: Hortensio , have you told him all her faults ?

input: She is an irksome brawling scold.
target: I know she is an irksome brawling scold .

input: I don't hear any harm if that is all.
target: If that be all , masters , I hear no harm .

input: No, that's not true.
target: No ?

input: Say'st me so, my friend?
target: Say'st me so , friend ?

input: What countryman is that?
target: What countryman ?

input: My fortune lives for me even though my father is dead.
target: My father dead , my fortune lives for me .

input: Good days and long to see, that's what I hope.
target: And I do hope good days and long to see .

input: Such a life with a wife like that were strange.
target: O sir , such a life with such a wife were strange !

input: If you have a stomach, God's name is: You will have me assisting you in all.
target: But if you have a stomach , to 't , i ' God's name : You shall have me assisting you in all .

input: Will you be able to woo this wildcat?
target: But will you woo this wildcat ?

input: Why did I hither, to that intent?
target: Why came I hither but to that intent ?

input: Have I not heard the sound of the sea, puffed up with winds, and Rage like an angry boar?
target: Have I not heard the sea , puffed up with winds , Rage like an angry boar chafed with sweat ?

input: Heaven's artillery thunder in the skies, but have I not heard great ordnance in the field?
target: Have I not heard great ordnance in the field , And heaven's artillery thunder in the skies ?

input: Hortensio, hark.
target: Hortensio , hark .

input: We will if he succeeds in winning her.
target: And so we will , provided that he win her .

input: I would be certain of a good dinner.
target: I would I were as sure of a good dinner .

input: He has two fair daughters, is that correct?
target: He that has the two fair daughters , is 't he you mean ?

input: I pray that she isn't that chides, sir.
target: Not her that chides , sir , at any hand , I pray .

input: Sir, a word, you go.
target: Sir , a word ere you go .

input: Are you a suitor to the maid, yes or no?
target: Are you a suitor to the maid you talk of , yea or no ?

input: Is it an offense if I do that?
target: An if I be , sir , is it any offense ?

input: No, if you don't have more words, you will get me.
target: No , if without more words you will get you hence .

input: She's the choice love of Signior Gremio, for this reason.
target: For this reason , if you'll know : That she's the choice love of Signior Gremio .

input: She is the chosen one by Signior Hortensio.
target: That she's the chosen of Signior Hortensio .

input: My masters were soft.
target: Softly , my masters .

input: If you are a gentleman, do me this right, and listen to me with patience.
target: If you be gentlemen , Do me this right : hear me with patience .

input: My father's daughter is not all known, but Baptista is a noble gentleman, and she may have more suitors than I do.
target: Baptista is a noble gentleman , To whom my father is not all unknown , And were his daughter fairer than she is , She may more suitors have , and me for one .

input: I believe he can not choose.
target: Believe me , lord , I think he can not choose .

input: It would seem strange to him when he woke up.
target: It would seem strange unto him when he waked .

input: Even as a flatt'ring dream or worthless fancy.
target: Even as a flatt'ring dream or worthless fancy .

input: Take him up and make sure he is well taken care of.
target: Then take him up and manage well the jest .

input: He should be carried to my fairest chamber and hung with all of my wanton pictures.
target: Carry him gently to my fairest chamber And hang it round with all my wanton pictures .

input: To make the lodging sweet, burn sweet wood and balm his foul head in warm distilled waters.
target: Balm his foul head in warm distilled waters And burn sweet wood to make the lodging sweet .

input: He is no less than what we say he is and we will play our part as he will think.
target: My lord , I warrant you we will play our part As he shall think by our true diligence He is no less than what we say he is .

input: Fair Leda's daughter had a lot of wooers, then one more may be fair for Bianca.
target: Fair Leda's daughter had a thousand wooers ; Then well one more may fair Bianca have .

input: This gentleman will speak to us all.
target: This gentleman will out-talk us all .

input: Hortensio, to what end are all these words?
target: Hortensio , to what end are all these words ?

input: Leave that labor to Hercules, and let it be more than Alcides twelve.
target: Yea , leave that labor to great Hercules , And let it be more than Alcides ' twelve .

input: Sir, you say well, and you do have a child.
target: Sir , you say well , and well you do conceive .

input: Excellent motion, O!
target: O excellent motion !

input: Let's be gone, fellows.
target: Fellows , let's be gone .

input: The motion is good and I will be yours,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
target: The motion's good indeed and be it so. , Petruchio , I shall be your

input: To make a bondmaid and a slave of me is wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong
target: Good sister , wrong me not nor wrong yourself , To make a bondmaid and a slave of me .

input: That is something I don't like.
target: That I disdain .

input: See that he doesn't say that.
target: See thou dissemble not .

input: Thou liest, the minion.
target: Minion , thou liest .

input: Is 't not Hortensio'.
target: Is 't not Hortensio ?

input: You should be like you want more wealth.
target: Oh , then belike you fancy riches more .

input: Gremio will be there to keep you balanced.
target: You will have Gremio to keep you fair .

input: Is it for him that you are so jealous of me?
target: Is it for him you do envy me so ?

input: Bianca, get thee in, what, in my sight?
target: What , in my sight ? , Bianca , get thee in .

input: Will you not let me suffer?
target: What , will you not suffer me ?

input: Don't say anything to me.
target: Talk not to me .

input: But who comes here?
target: But who comes here ?

input: Good tomorrow, neighbor Baptista.
target: Good morrow , neighbor Baptista .

input: Good morning, Gremio, God save you.
target: Good morrow , neighbor Gremio. , God save you , gentlemen !

input: Good sir, and you.
target: And you , good sir .

input: Do you not have a daughter called Katherina, fair and righteous?
target: Pray , have you not a daughter Called Katherina , fair and virtuous ?

input: I have a daughter called Katherina, sir.
target: I have a daughter , sir , called Katherina .

input: You are mistaken, Signior Gremio.
target: You wrong me , Signior Gremio .

input: Give me leave, I am a gentleman of Verona, I heard of her beauty and her wit, Her affability and bashful modesty, and I am bold to show myself a forward guest within your house.
target: Give me leave. , I am a gentleman of Verona , sir , That hearing of her beauty and her wit , Her affability and bashful modesty , Her wondrous qualities and mild behavior , Am bold to show myself a forward guest Within your house , to make mine eye the witness Of that report which I so oft have heard .

input: You are welcome, sir, and he is for your good sake.
target: You're welcome , sir , and he for your good sake .

input: For my daughter, she is not for your turn, the more my grief, I know.
target: But for my daughter Katherine , this I know , She is not for your turn , the more my grief .

input: I see that you don't want to part with her, but I don't want you to join my company.
target: I see you do not mean to part with her , Or else you like not of my company .

input: It was a mistake me not.
target: Mistake me not .

input: I speak, but I find something else.
target: I speak but as I find .

input: What are you doing, sir?
target: Whence are you , sir ?

input: I don't know what to call your name.
target: What may I call your name ?

input: A man well known throughout all Italy is my father's son, Antonio's son.
target: Petruchio is my name , Antonio's son , A man well known throughout all Italy .

input: I have known him for a long time.
target: I know him well .

input: For his sake, you are welcome.
target: You are welcome for his sake .

input: I would be doing that, signior Gremio.
target: Oh , pardon me , Signior Gremio , I would fain be doing .

input: You will curse your wooing, sir, but I am sure that this is a very grateful gift.
target: I doubt it not , sir , but you will curse your wooing. , Neighbor , this is a gift very grateful , I am sure of it .

input: To express the kindness of myself, that I have been more kindly beholding to you than any other person.
target: To express the like kindness , myself , that have been more kindly beholding to you than any , freely give unto you this young scholar

input: Signior Gremio, thank you for a thousand.
target: A thousand thanks , Signior Gremio .

input: Good to see you, Welcome, good Cambio.
target: Welcome , good Cambio .

input: The name Lucentio is yours.
target: Lucentio is your name .

input: I pray, of whence.
target: Of whence , I pray ?

input: The man of Pisa is mighty.
target: A mighty man of Pisa .

input: I know him well by the report.
target: By report I know him well .

input: Sir, you are very welcome.
target: You are very welcome , sir .

input: We are going to go for a walk and then have dinner.
target: We will go walk a little in the orchard , And then to dinner .

input: I am praying that you all think yourselves after you are welcomed.
target: You are passing welcome , And so I pray you all to think yourselves .

input: I can't come to woo every day, Signior Baptista.
target: Signior Baptista , my business asketh haste , And every day I can not come to woo .

input: You knew my father and I was heir to all of his lands and goods, which I have bettered rather than decreased.
target: You knew my father well , and in him me , Left solely heir to all his lands and goods , Which I have bettered rather than decreased .

input: If I get your daughter's love, what should I give her to her husband?
target: Then tell me , if I get your daughter's love , What dowry shall I have with her to wife ?

input: The one half of my lands were in possession of twenty thousand crowns after my death.
target: After my death , the one half of my lands , And , in possession , twenty thousand crowns .

input: The covenants may be kept on either hand if specialties were drawn between us.
target: Let specialties be therefore drawn between us , That covenants may be kept on either hand .

input: When the special thing is well obtained, that is her love, for that is all that matters.
target: Ay , when the special thing is well obtained , That is , her love , for that is all in all .

input: That is not something.
target: Why , that is nothing .

input: They do consume the thing that feeds their fury when two raging fires meet together, I tell you.
target: For I tell you , father , I am as peremptory as she proud-minded ; And where two raging fires meet together , They do consume the thing that feeds their fury .

input: I am rough and not like a girl, so she gives me to her.
target: So I to her and so she yields to me , For I am rough and woo not like a babe .

input: Happy be your speed, mayst Thou woo.
target: Well mayst thou woo , and happy be thy speed .

input: But be prepared for some angry words.
target: But be thou armed for some unhappy words .

input: As mountains are for winds, that shakes not, though they blow constantly.
target: Ay , to the proof , as mountains are for winds , That shakes not , though they blow perpetually .

input: My friend, why dost you look pale now?
target: How now , my friend , why dost thou look so pale ?

input: Will my daughter prove to be a good musician?
target: What , will my daughter prove a good musician ?

input: She'll prove a soldier sooner than I think.
target: I think she'll sooner prove a soldier .

input: Why didn't you break her to the lute?
target: Why , then thou canst not break her to the lute ?

input: She struck me on the head with that word, and through the instrument, my pate made way.
target: I'll fume with them ! " And with that word she struck me on the head , And through the instrument my pate made way ,

input: By the world, it is a lusty wench.
target: Now , by the world , it is a lusty wench .

input: I adore her ten times more than I did.
target: I love her ten times more than e'er I did .

input: How long will it be for me to have a chat with her.
target: Oh , how I long to have some chat with her !

input: I want you to do that.
target: I pray you do .

input: When she arrives, I'll woo her with some spirit.
target: I'll attend her here And woo her with some spirit when she comes .

input: I'll tell her that she sings as sweetly as a nightingale if she says that she rail.
target: Say that she rail ; why then I'll tell her plain She sings as sweetly as a nightingale .

input: Say that she frowns, I'll say she looks as clear as the morning roses.
target: Say that she frown ; I'll say she looks as clear As morning roses newly washed with dew .

input: I'll commend her volubility and say she uttereth piercing eloquence if she's mute and will not speak a word.
target: Say she be mute and will not speak a word ; Then I'll commend her volubility , And say she uttereth piercing eloquence .

input: I'll give her my thanks if she bids me a pack, as though she wanted me to stay a week.
target: If she do bid me pack , I'll give her thanks , As though she bid me stay by her a week .

input: If she doesn't marry me, I'll want the day when I can ask the banns and be married.
target: If she deny to wed , I'll crave the day When I shall ask the banns and when be married .

input: Take him up and then sleep with him in his office when he wakes up.
target: Take him up gently , and to bed with him , And each one to his office when he wakes .

input: Sirrah, look at the trumpet and see what it sounds like.
target: Sirrah , go see what trumpet 'tis that sounds .

input: To be like a noble gentleman and travel some journey to bring him to this place.
target: Belike some noble gentleman that means , Traveling some journey , to repose him here .

input: The players that offer service to your Lordship please your honor.
target: An't please your Honor , players That offer service to your Lordship .

input: They will come near if you bid.
target: Bid them come near .

input: You are welcome now, fellows.
target: Now , fellows , you are welcome .

input: We thank you for your service.
target: We thank your Honor .

input: Do you plan on staying with me tonight?
target: Do you intend to stay with me tonight ?

input: Please accept our duty, so please, your Lordship.
target: So please your Lordship to accept our duty .

input: With all of my heart.
target: With all my heart .

input: I remember him playing a farmer's eldest son.
target: This fellow I remember Since once he played a farmer's eldest son .

input: You wooed the gentle woman so well.
target: Twas where you wooed the gentlewoman so well .

input: I have forgotten your name, but that part was perfectly fitted and performed naturally.
target: I have forgot your name , but sure that part Was aptly fitted and naturally performed .

input: Good morrow, Kate, for that's your name, I hear.
target: Good morrow , Kate , for that's your name , I hear .

input: Something hard of hearing has been heard, but have you heard it yet?
target: Well have you heard , but something hard of hearing .

input: In good time, moved, " in good time.
target: Moved , " in good time .

input: You were a person that I knew at the beginning.
target: I knew you at the first You were a moveable .

input: Why, what is a moving object?
target: Why , what's a moveable ?

input: A stool with two people sitting on it.
target: A joint stool .

input: Thou has not missed it.
target: Thou hast hit it .

input: Come on, sit on me.
target: Come , sit on me .

input: You and yourses are made to bear.
target: Asses are made to bear , and so are you .

input: Women are made to bear, and so are you.
target: Women are made to bear , and so are you .

input: I don't think you have jade, if you mean that.
target: No such jade as you , if me you mean .

input: I will not burden thee, for knowing thee to be young and light, too light for such a swain as you to catch, and yet as heavy as my weight should be.
target: Alas , good Kate , I will not burden thee , For knowing thee to be but young and light , Too light for such a swain as you to catch , And yet as heavy as my weight should be .

input: It should be, should buzz.
target: Should be" , should buzz !

input: If I am waspish, beware my sting.
target: If I be waspish , best beware my sting .

input: My remedy is to get rid of it.
target: My remedy is then to pluck it out .

input: If the fool could find it where it is.
target: Ay , if the fool could find it where it lies .

input: Who knows where the wasp wears his sting?
target: Who knows not where a wasp does wear his sting ?

input: His tail was in his hand.
target: In his tail .

input: His tongue was in his mouth.
target: In his tongue .

input: Whose tongue is it?
target: Whose tongue ?

input: If you have tales to tell, yours.
target: Yours , if you talk of tales .

input: What is happening with my tongue in your tail?
target: What , with my tongue in your tail ?

input: Good Kate, come again.
target: Nay , come again , Good Kate .

input: That I will try.
target: That I'll try .

input: If you strike again, I will cuff you.
target: I swear I'll cuff you if you strike again .

input: Maybe you will lose your arms.
target: So may you lose your arms .

input: There was no cock in my house.
target: No cock of mine .

input: Come, Kate, come.
target: Nay , come , Kate , come .

input: You have to not look sour.
target: You must not look so sour .

input: When I see a crab, it is my fashion.
target: It is my fashion , when I see a crab .

input: Look not sour, here's no crab, and that's why.
target: Why , here's no crab , and therefore look not sour .

input: There is and there is.
target: There is , there is .

input: Show it to me first.
target: Then show it me .

input: I would have had a glass if I had it.
target: Had I a glass , I would .

input: What are you talking about my face?
target: What , you mean my face ?

input: It was well aimed at a young person.
target: Well aimed of such a young one .

input: Saint George said that he was too young for you.
target: Now , by Saint George , I am too young for you .

input: You are withered, yet.
target: Yet you are withered .

input: It is with cares.
target: Tis with cares .

input: I do not care about that.
target: I care not .

input: Let me get away.
target: Let me go .

input: I don't think so, not a whit.
target: No , not a whit .

input: I think you are passing in a gentle way.
target: I find you passing gentle .

input: I was told that you were rough and coy, and now I find that you are a liar.
target: Twas told me you were rough and coy and sullen , And now I find report a very liar .

input: Thou canst not frown, Thou canst not look askance, Thou canst not bite the lip as angry wenches will, and Thou canst not be cross in talk.
target: Thou canst not frown , thou canst not look askance , Nor bite the lip as angry wenches will , Nor hast thou pleasure to be cross in talk .

input: But with mildness, entertain'st the wooers, with gentle conference, soft and personable.
target: But thou with mildness entertain'st thy wooers , With gentle conference , soft and affable .

input: The world reports that Kate does not walk well.
target: Why does the world report that Kate doth limp ?

input: The world is a slanderous place.
target: O slanderous world !

input: Kate likes the hazel-twig because it is straight and slender, and brown in hue.
target: Kate like the hazel-twig Is straight and slender and as brown in hue As hazel nuts , and sweeter than the kernels .

input: Let me watch the walk.
target: Oh , let me see thee walk !

input: Did Dian ever become a grove as Kate did this chamber?
target: Did ever Dian so become a grove As Kate this chamber with her princely gait ?

input: A mother who is witty.
target: A witty mother !

input: Her son was Witless else.
target: Witless else her son .

input: I don't know if I am wise.
target: Am I not wise ?

input: He was born to tame you, Kate, and bring you from a wild Kate to a Kate Conformable as other household Kates.
target: For I am he am born to tame you , Kate , And bring you from a wild Kate to a Kate Conformable as other household Kates .

input: I should be aware of that voice.
target: I should know that voice .

input: These are devils, but he is drowned, and it should be.
target: It should be , But he is drowned , and these are devils .

input: Oh, defend me.
target: Oh , defend me !

input: The most delicate monster has four legs and two voices.
target: Four legs and two voices , a most delicate monster .

input: His voice is now to speak well of his friend.
target: His forward voice now is to speak well of his friend .

input: His voice is backwards and he makes foul speeches.
target: His backward voice is to utter foul speeches and to detract .

input: I will help his ague if all the wine in my bottle will recover him.
target: If all the wine in my bottle will recover him , I will help his ague .

input: Come and see it.

target: Coraggio , bully-monster , If these be true spies which I wear in my head , here's a goodly sight .

target: O Setebos , these be brave spirits indeed !

target: How fine my master is !

target: I am afraid He will chastise me .

target: What things are these , my lord Antonio ?

target: Will money buy 'em ?

target: I shall be pinched to death .

input: Stephano, my drunken butler, is not this.
target: Is not this Stephano , my drunken butler ?

target: He is drunk now .

target: Where had he wine ?

target: And Trinculo is reeling ripe .

target: Why , how now , Stephano ?

target: O , touch me not .

target: I am not Stephano , but a cramp .

input: You would be the king, sirrah.
target: You'd be king o ' th ' isle , sirrah ?

input: I shouldn't have been sore that day.
target: I should have been a sore one then .

input: He is as disproportioned in his manners as he is in his shape.
target: He is as disproportioned in his manners As in his shape. , Take with you your companions .

input: I will be wise and seek for grace.
target: And I'll be wise hereafter And seek for grace .

input: I took this for a god, and worshiped this dull fool.
target: What a thrice-double ass Was I , to take this drunkard for a god And worship this dull fool !

target: Go to , away .

input: Or, rather, stole it.
target: Or stole it , rather .

input: I will bring you to your ship and Naples in the morning, and then retire you to Milan, where every third thought will be my grave.
target: And in the morn I'll bring you to your ship and so to Naples , Where I have hope to see the nuptial Of these our dear-beloved solemnized , And thence retire me to my Milan , where Every third thought shall be my grave .

input: I want you to tell the story of your life, which must take the ear strangely.
target: I long To hear the story of your life , which must Take the ear strangely .

input: My charms are all o'erthrown, and what strength I have's mine is most faint.
target: Now my charms are all o'erthrown , And what strength I have's mine own , Which is most faint .

input: Release me from my bands with the help of your good hands, since I have my dukedom got and pardoned the deceiver, but dwell in this bare island by your spell.
target: Let me not , Since I have my dukedom got And pardoned the deceiver , dwell In this bare island by your spell , But release me from my bands With the help of your good hands .

input: Let your pardon set me free, as you from crimes would pardon me.
target: As you from crimes would pardoned be , Let your indulgence set me free .

input: I pray that thee will mark me.
target: I pray thee , mark me .

input: O'erprized all popular rate, in my false brother Awaked an evil nature, because I was neglecting worldly ends, all dedicated to closeness and the bettering of my mind.
target: I , thus neglecting worldly ends , all dedicated To closeness and the bettering of my mind With that which , but by being so retired , O'erprized all popular rate , in my false brother Awaked an evil nature .

input: My trust, like a good parent, did get of him a lie, but it was a lie that had no limit.
target: And my trust , Like a good parent , did beget of him A falsehood in its contrary as great As my trust was , which had indeed no limit , A confidence sans bound .

input: Dost you hear that his ambition is growing?
target: Hence his ambition growing , Dost thou hear ?

input: Sir, your story would cure deafness.
target: Your tale , sir , would cure deafness .

target: Me , poor man , my library Was dukedom large enough .

target: Oh , the heavens !

input: He should be marked his condition and the event.
target: Mark his condition and the event .

input: Let me know if this is a brother.
target: Then tell me If this might be a brother .

input: I should think negatively of my grandmother.
target: I should sin To think but nobly of my grandmother .

input: The King of Naples was an enemy to me and I don't know how much tribute I will get.
target: The King of Naples , being an enemy To me inveterate , hearkens my brother's suit , Which was that he , in lieu o ' th ' premises Of homage and I know not how much tribute , Should presently extirpate me and mine Out of the dukedom , and confer fair Milan With all the honors on my brother .

input: Alack, for pity.
target: Alack , for pity !

input: I don't remember how I cried out then, but I will cry it again.
target: I , not remembering how I cried out then , Will cry it o'er again .

input: I feel a hint that wrings my eyes to 't.
target: It is a hint That wrings mine eyes to 't .

input: I'll bring the story to the present business, without the one that was most important.
target: Hear a little further And then I'll bring thee to the present business Which now 's upon 's , without the which this story Were most impertinent .

target: Wherefore did they not That hour destroy us ?

target: Well demanded , wench .

input: My tale makes that question come to mind.
target: My tale provokes that question .

input: They durst not, so dear the love my people bore me, nor set a mark that was so bloody on the business, but with colors that were more fair painted their foul ends.
target: Dear , they durst not , So dear the love my people bore me , nor set A mark so bloody on the business , but With colors fairer painted their foul ends .

input: Was it trouble for me to be with you?
target: Alack , what trouble Was I then to you !

input: Oh, a cherubim, I wast that did protect me.
target: Oh , a cherubim Thou wast that did preserve me .

input: Under my burthen groaned, "which raised in me an undergoing stomach to bear up Against what should occur", as he smiled.
target: Thou didst smile Infused with a fortitude from heaven , When I have decked the sea with drops full salt , Under my burthen groaned ; which raised in me An undergoing stomach to bear up Against what should ensue .

input: How did we get to the beach?
target: How came we ashore ?

input: By divine intervention.
target: By providence divine .

input: We had some food and fresh water from a noble Neapolitan who was appointed Master of this design, and who gave us Rich garments, linens, stuffs, and necessaries.
target: Some food we had and some fresh water that A noble Neapolitan , Gonzalo , Out of his charity , who being then appointed Master of this design , did give us , with Rich garments , linens , stuffs , and necessaries , Which since have steaded much .

input: Knowing that I loved my books, he gave me from my own library some volumes that I prize above my dukedom.
target: So , of his gentleness , Knowing I loved my books , he furnished me From mine own library with volumes that I prize above my dukedom .

input: I would like to see that man someday.
target: Would I might But ever see that man !

input: Now I wake up.
target: Now I arise .

target: Heavens thank you for 't !

target: And now , I pray you , sir , For still 'tis beating in my mind , your reason For raising this sea storm ?

input: By accident, my enemies were brought to this shore, by most strange fortune.
target: Know thus far forth : By accident most strange , bountiful Fortune ( Now my dear lady ) hath mine enemies Brought to this shore .

target: Here cease more questions .

input: Give it way, and it will be a good dullness.
target: Tis a good dullness , And give it way .

target: I am ready now .

target: All hail , great master !

target: Grave sir , hail !

target: Hast thou , spirit , Performed to point the tempest that I bade thee ?

target: Sometime I'd divide , And burn in many places .

input: Sight-out running was not done because of Jove's lightning and the dreadful thunderclaps.
target: Jove's lightning , the precursors O ' th ' dreadful thunderclaps , more momentary And sight-outrunning were not .

target: My brave spirit !

input: The boatswain is here!
target: Boatswain !

target: Here , master .

target: What cheer ?

target: Good , speak to th ' mariners .

target: Fall to 't yarely , or we run ourselves aground .

target: Where's the Master ?

target: Play the men .

input: I pray that you will keep below.
target: I pray now , keep below .

target: Where is the Master , Boatswain ?

target: Not a soul But felt a fever of the mad and played Some tricks of desperation .

input: All but mariners quit the vessel, then all of a fire with me.
target: All but mariners Plunged in the foaming brine and quit the vessel , Then all afire with me .

target: The king's son , Ferdinand , With hair up-staring , then , like reeds , not hair , Was the first man that leaped , cried , "Hell is empty And all the devils are here." Why , that's my spirit !

target: But was not this nigh shore ?

target: Close by , my master .

target: But are they , Ariel , safe ?

target: Not a hair perished .

target: On their sustaining garments not a blemish , But fresher than before .

target: And , as thou badest me , In troops I have dispersed them 'bout the isle .

target: The king's son have I landed by himself , Whom I left cooling of the air with sighs In an odd angle of the isle , and sitting , His arms in this sad knot .

input: The mariners said how the king's ship has been dealt with.
target: Of the king's ship , The mariners , say how thou hast disposed , And all the rest o ' th ' fleet .

target: The mariners all under hatches stowed , Who , with a charm joined to their suffered labor , I have left asleep .

input: They all met again and are on the Mediterranean float, Supposing that the king's ship was damaged and he died.
target: And for the rest o ' th ' fleet , Which I dispersed , they all have met again And are upon the Mediterranean float , Bound sadly home for Naples , Supposing that they saw the king's ship wracked And his great person perish .

input: The charge is performed by an individual.
target: Ariel , thy charge Exactly is performed .

input: But there's more work to be done.
target: But there's more work .

input: What is the time of the day?
target: What is the time o ' th ' day ?

input: Past the middle of the season.
target: Past the mid season .

input: There are at least two glasses.
target: At least two glasses .

input: The time between now andtwixt six and now must be spent the most preciously by us.
target: The time 'twixt six and now Must by us both be spent most preciously .

input: Is there more work to be done.
target: Is there more toil ?

input: Let me remember what Thou hast promised, which is not yet performed me.
target: Since thou dost give me pains , Let me remember thee what thou hast promised , Which is not yet performed me .

target: How now ?

target: Moody ?

input: What is it that 't he canst demand'?

target: My liberty .

target: Before the time be out ?

target: No more !

target: Thou didst promise To bate me a full year .

input: Do you remember what a torment I did to free thee?
target: Dost thou forget From what a torment I did free thee ?

target: No .

target: Thou dost , and think'st it much to tread the ooze Of the salt deep , To run upon the sharp wind of the north , To do me business in the veins o ' th ' earth When it is baked with frost .

target: I do not , sir .

input: Thou liest, it is a malignant thing.
target: Thou liest , malignant thing !

target: Hast thou forgot The foul witch Sycorax , who with age and envy Was grown into a hoop ?

target: Hast thou forgot her ?

target: No , sir .

target: Where was she born ?

target: Speak .

target: Tell me .

target: Sir , in Argier .

input: Was she right?
target: Oh , was she so ?

target: This damned witch Sycorax , For mischiefs manifold and sorceries terrible To enter human hearing , from Argier , Thou know'st , was banished .

target: For one thing she did They would not take her life .

target: Is not this true ?

target: This blue-eyed hag was hither brought with child And here was left by th ' sailors .

input: I say so, it's Dull thing.
target: Dull thing , I say so .

input: He is the Caliban Whom I keep in service.
target: He , that Caliban Whom now I keep in service .

input: When I arrived, I heard the sound of The pine and let thee out.
target: It was mine art , When I arrived and heard thee , that made gape The pine and let thee out .

target: I thank thee , master .

target: If thou more murmur'st , I will rend an oak And peg thee in his knotty entrails till Thou hast howled away twelve winters .

target: Pardon , master .

input: I will be the correspondent to do my spiriting gently.
target: I will be correspondent to command And do my spiriting gently .

target: Do so , and after two days I will discharge thee .

target: Say , what ?

target: What shall I do ?

target: Go make thyself like a nymph o ' th ' sea .

target: Be subject To no sight but thine and mine , invisible To every eyeball else .

target: Go take this shape And hither come in 't .

target: Go hence with diligence .

target: Shake it off .

target: Come on .

target: We'll visit Caliban , my slave who never Yields us kind answer .

input: We cannot not miss him.
target: But as 'tis , We can not miss him .

input: He serves in offices that profit us, and makes our fire, fetch in our wood, and serves in offices that profit us.
target: He does make our fire , Fetch in our wood , and serves in offices That profit us. , What , ho !

target: Slave !

input: Caliban, Caliban!
target: Caliban !

target: Speak .

target: There's other business for thee .

target: Come , thou tortoise !

target: Fine apparition !

target: My quaint Ariel , Hark in thine ear .

target: My lord it shall be done .

target: As wicked dew as e'er my mother brushed With raven's feather from unwholesome fen Drop on you both !

target: A southwest blow on ye And blister you all o'er !

input: Tonight shalt have side-stitches that will pen your breath up, be sure, for this.
target: For this , be sure , tonight thou shalt have cramps , Side-stitches that shall pen thy breath up .

target: Urchins Shall , forth at vast of night that they may work , All exercise on thee .

target: Thou shalt be pinched As thick as honeycomb , each pinch more stinging Than bees that made 'em .

target: I must eat my dinner .

target: This island's mine , by Sycorax my mother , Which thou takest from me .

input: I was cursed that I did that.
target: Cursed be I that did so !

input: Whom stripes may move, not kindness, is the most lying slave.
target: Thou most lying slave , Whom stripes may move , not kindness !

target: I have used thee , Filth as thou art , with human care , and lodged thee In mine own cell till thou didst seek to violate The honor of my child .

input: Oh yes, oh yes!
target: Oh ho , oh ho !

input: It would have been done.
target: Would 't had been done !

input: I was prevented by Thou didst.
target: Thou didst prevent me .

input: Being capable of all ill is an Abhorred slave's worst nightmare.
target: Abhorred slave , Which any print of goodness wilt not take , Being capable of all ill !

input: I took pains to make thee speak, taught thee each hour, and I pitied thee.
target: I pitied thee , Took pains to make thee speak , taught thee each hour One thing or other .

input: The vile race had that in which good natures could not abide to be with.
target: But thy vile race , Though thou didst learn , had that in 't which good natures Could not abide to be with .

input: I was confined into this rock, who had deserved more than a prison.
target: Therefore wast thou Deservedly confined into this rock , Who hadst deserved more than a prison .

input: You taught me how to curse, and I made a profit from it.
target: You taught me language , and my profit on 't Is I know how to curse .

input: The red plague makes it impossible for you to learn your language.
target: The red plague rid you For learning me your language !

input: No, please pray thee.
target: No , pray thee .

input: Hence, slave, therefore!
target: So , slave , hence !

input: The watchdogs bark at something.
target: The watchdogs bark .

target: Hark , hark !

target: I hear The strain of strutting chanticleer Cry "Cock-a-diddle-dow." Where should this music be ?

input: Is the air or the earth what you are talking about?
target: I ' th ' air or th ' earth ?

input: It waits upon the island, and it sounds no longer.
target: It sounds no more , and sure , it waits upon Some god o ' th ' island .

input: Sitting on a bank, Weeping again the king my father's wrack, this music crept by me upon the waters,laying both their fury and my passion with its sweet air.
target: Sitting on a bank , Weeping again the king my father's wrack , This music crept by me upon the waters , Allaying both their fury and my passion With its sweet air .

input: I followed it, or it drew me to it.
target: Thence I have followed it , Or it hath drawn me rather .

input: But not gone.
target: But 'tis gone .

target: No , it begins again .

input: Hark, now I hear them.
target: Hark , now I hear them .

input: My drowned father is remembered by the ditty.
target: The ditty does remember my drowned father .

target: I hear it now above me .

input: What is this thing?
target: What is 't ?

target: A spirit ?

target: Lord , how it looks about !

target: Believe me , sir , It carries a brave form .

target: But 'tis a spirit .

input: Wench, no!
target: No , wench !

input: We have such senses as it eats and sleeps.
target: It eats and sleeps and hath such senses As we have , such .

target: He hath lost his fellows And strays about to find 'em .

input: Do you not hear what he is saying?
target: Do you not hear him ?

target: You mar our labor .

input: You should keep your cabins.
target: Keep your cabins .

input: You help out the storm.
target: You do assist the storm .

input: Be patient, good, be good.
target: Nay , good , be patient .

input: Therefore!
target: Hence !

input: Silence to the cabin!
target: To cabin , silence !

input: It's not a problem us not.
target: Trouble us not .

input: Good, but remember whom you havet aboard.
target: Good , yet remember whom thou hast aboard .

input: I more love myself than any of the others.
target: None that I more love than myself .

input: You are a member of the city council.
target: You are a councilor .

input: Don't use your authority to your advantage.
target: Use your authority .

input: I say out of our way, if you can not, give thanks, because you have lived so long and made yourself ready for the mistake of the hour.
target: If you can not , give thanks you have lived so long and make yourself ready in your cabin for the mischance of the hour , if it so hap. , Cheerly , good hearts ! , Out of our way , I say .

input: I have a lot of comfort from this fellow.
target: I have great comfort from this fellow .

input: I might call him a thing divine, for nothing natural, I ever saw so noble.
target: I might call him A thing divine , for nothing natural I ever saw so noble .

input: No wonder, sir, but definitely a maid.
target: No wonder , sir , But certainly a maid .

input: I speak my language.
target: My language !

target: Heavens , I am the best of them that speak this speech , Were I but where 'tis spoken .

input: How do you do it?
target: How ?

input: What is the best?
target: The best ?

input: If the King of Naples heard you, what do you think?
target: What wert thou if the King of Naples heard thee ?

target: A single thing , as I am now , that wonders To hear thee speak of Naples .

target: He does hear me , And that he does I weep .

input: I am Naples, Who with my eyes, never since at ebb, beheld the king my father wracked.
target: Myself am Naples , Who with mine eyes , never since at ebb , beheld The king my father wracked .

input: For mercy, alack!
target: Alack , for mercy !

input: The Duke of Milan has faith and all of his lords.
target: Yes , faith , and all his lords , the Duke of Milan And his brave son being twain .

input: Sir, it was soft.
target: Soft , sir !

input: There is one more word.
target: One word more .

input: Good things will try to dwell with the ill spirit if it is so fair.
target: If the ill spirit have so fair a house , Good things will strive to dwell with 't .

input: What are you talking about, I say?
target: What , I say ?

input: I can disarm thee with this stick and make the weapon drop if you come from my ward.
target: Come from thy ward , For I can here disarm thee with this stick And make thy weapon drop .

target: Beseech you , father .

input: Therefore!
target: Hence !

input: Don't hang on my clothing.
target: Hang not on my garments .

target: Sir , have pity , I'll be his surety .

target: One word more Shall make me chide thee , if not hate thee .

target: What , An advocate for an imposter ?

input: Hush, I think there is no more such shapes as he and Caliban.
target: Hush , Thou think'st there is no more such shapes as he , Having seen but him and Caliban .

input: To most of the men, this is a Caliban, and they are angels.
target: Foolish wench , To th ' most of men this is a Caliban And they to him are angels .

input: My affections are the most humble of all.
target: My affections Are then most humble .

target: I have no ambition To see a goodlier man .

input: So they are, right?
target: So they are .
